Dizzy Paleo Protein Milkshake

Jump To Recipe

This recipe came about merely because I was in the mood for dessert, but still needed to get some protein into my evening meal. There are a few things about this milkshake that will have your head spinning, hence the name Dizzy Paleo Protein Milkshake:

 

1. It is packed full of protein - Paleo Protein Powder is a grass-fed beef protein powder that contains 23 grams of protein in one scoop. (I know you're probably thinking that a protein powder made from beef sounds nasty, but this stuff is amazeballs!)
 

2. It is gluten-free, sugar-free, dairy-free, and low carb but definitely isn't flavor-free....it taste sinfully yummy!
 

And finally....you ready for this one???
 

3. It contains an entire cup of frozen SPINach (but doesn't taste like it at all) - Spinach is loaded with nutrients and antioxidants and has been linked to various health benefits. It has been shown to help decrease oxidative stress, improve eye health, aid in cancer prevention, and help regulate blood pressure levels.

 

Yes, you've read correctly, you can actually enjoy a sweet, chocolatey milkshake and not have anything to feel guilty about. So, stop your head from spinning, grab yourself a straw, and try not to get brainfreeze from sucking down this deliciousness too quicky!

Dizzy Paleo Protein Milkshake

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
215
Servings
1
Ingredients

1 scoop Vanilla Nut Paleo Protein Grass-fed Beef Protein Powder 
3/4 c. unsweetened almond milk
1/2 - 1 c. crushed ice
1 c. frozen chopped spinach
2 T. unsweetened cocoa powder

Directions
  1. Pulse 1/2 cup almond milk with frozen spinach in blender cup until well combined.
  2. Add protein powder, remaining almond milk, and cocoa powder and blend again.
  3. Blend in ice, 1/4 cup at a time, until desired consistency is reached. 

Kelly's Krazy Tortillas

Jump To Recipe

Ok, so here's the deal....

I'm becoming an obsessed, KRAZY person with this new batter I came up with! By making some slight tweaks in ingredient proportions and how it is cooked/baked, this stuff is super versitile. I have been playing with it so much in the past week and have been happy with everything I've tried out (which very rarely happens on a first attempt). 

 

I've already created a gluten-free, low-carb pizza crust, breadsticks, and tortillas with the Kelly's Krazy batter and ghe only problem I'm having with it is that I want to try every variation I think of right away (and there are SO many)! So, be on the lookout for a lot more gluten-free, low-carb "Kelly's Krazy" recipes to come because I'm gonna be testing this stuff out a lot in the near future. 

Kelly's Krazy Tortillas

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
125
Servings
3
Ingredients

2 eggs
1/2 c. cottage cheese
1/4 c. (1/2 scoop) unflavored whey protein powder
3 T. coconut flour
1/2 tsp. baking powder
1/8 tsp. pink salt
additional Spice Gal, Simple Girl, or other spices (optional)

Directions
  1. Combine eggs and cottage cheese together in blender. 
  2. Pulse in baking powder, salt, protein powder, coconut flour, and additional spices (if desired) until well combined, scraping sides with spatula.
  3. Grease 10.5 inch skillet and heat to medium-low heat.
  4. Pour 1/3 cup batter into skillet and spread, very thin, with spatula to cover entire bottom of skillet.
  5. Cook for a couple minutes, until bubbles form and top is no longer jiggly.
  6. Flip and cook another couple minutes.

Keto Krazy Pizza Crust

Jump To Recipe

OH MY GOSH YOU GUYS, I CANNOT EVEN BEGIN TO CONTAIN MY EXCITEMENT (hence the all-caps) ON THIS ONE!!! Developing an alternative pizza crust recipe that actually holds up and tastes like pizza crust has seriously been my Holy Grail quest for like 2 years now and........... I'VE FINALLY DONE IT!!! 

I mean, c'mon, who doesn't love pizza, right?! It's a no-fail dinner choice, definite go-to as a late night snack, and is even awesome as leftovers served cold for breakfast. On top of the fact that you can eat it anytime of day, pizza becomes even more versatile when you think of the never ending flavor options in terms of toppings.

The only thing NOT to love about traditional pizza is that it makes me feel like crap! I looked into it and here's the run-down on what I learned from registered dietitian-nutritionist Sonya Angelone on what exactly happens to your body when you eat pizza:

Sure, that first bite (or slice) is great! In fact, it activates the pleasure center in your brain and causes you to drool. This triggers the release of digestive enzymes in your mouth that start to break down the carbs from the crust into glucose (aka sugar) that your body can use as fuel. 

Within 10-15 minutes, these sugars start to hit your bloodstream and you may experience belly bloating from  your body continuing to digest and release gases.

In the next 5 minutes or so, your rising leptin levels will signal your body that you're getting full and tell you to stop eating as your cells absorb the sugar from your bloodsteam. If you continue eating anyway, your body will reject the fuel and instead send it to the liver to be turned into fat.

By the 30 minute mark, your stomach acids will be working to digest the fat from the cheese/toppings, releasing it into the bloodstream (therefore raising triglyceride levels) and eventually heading to the liver where it will be either sent to muscles to be used for fuel or stored as fat. This is also the same time that your body will stop releasing the hunger hormone, grehlin and you will feel satisfied.

If you're pretty healthy and stop eating when you start to feel satisfied after one slice, your triglyceride levels should taper off within about six hours. But grabbing a few more slices (and let's face it, it's often hard to stop at just one) will cause you to feel sluggish and your triglyceride levels will continue to rise even more, which can contribute to clogged arteries....ummmm, no thanks, I'll pass!

On top of making me feel crappy, "regular" pizza is extremely heavy on the calorie count and low on actual nutritional value. Just one slice of Papa John's cheese pizza packs on a whopping 295 calories and 38 grams of carbs.

In comparison, cheese pizza made with Kelly's Krazy Pizza Crust comes in at 155 calories, 7 grams of carbs (of which 3 grams are dietary fiber), and 15 grams of protein per slice.....AND it doesn't make me feel crappy since it's gluten-free and low-carb.  

I am extremely happy to say that, for me, the hunt for a truly delicious alternative pizza crust is officially over!!

Keto Krazy Pizza Crust

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
85 (+toppings)
Servings
8
Ingredients

1 c. cottage cheese
3 eggs
1/4 c. + 2 T. coconut flour
3/4 tsp. baking powder
1/4 tsp. pink salt
1 scoop unflavored whey protein powder

Directions
  1. Preheat oven to 400 degrees and place parchment paper on pizza pan. 
  2. Combine eggs and cottage cheese together in blender. 
  3. Pulse or stir in baking powder, salt, protein powder, and coconut flour until well combined, scraping sides with spatula.
  4. Scoop batter onto pizza pan and spread into thin, even circle with spatula.
  5. Bake for 12-15 minutes.
  6. Remove from oven and add desired toppings (sauce, cheese, etc).
  7. Pull parchment paper to slide pizza off of pizza pan and onto oven rack then bake for a few more minutes.  

Personal Peanut Butter Cup Sponge Cake

Personal Peanut Butter Cup Sponge Cake

Dietary
Low Carb
Calories per serving
285
Servings
1
Ingredients

2 eggs
1 tsp. coconut oil, melted
3 T. unsweetened almond milk
2 T. almond flour
1/2 T. coconut flour
1/2 T. whey protein powder
1 T. unsweetened cocoa powder
3 dropperfuls SweetLeaf english toffee stevia
1/4 tsp. baking powder
1/2 tsp. peanut butter

Directions
  1. Grease large ramekin, mug, or small bowl.
  2. Whisk together eggs, almond milk, and coconut oil.
  3. Whisk in baking powder, stevia, and cocoa powder.
  4. Stir in almond flour, coconut flour, and coconut flour until well-combined.
  5. Pour batter into greased ramekin.
  6. Microwave for 2 1/2 minutes.
  7. Transfer cake to plate.
  8. Drizzle peanut butter on top.

Cinnamon Banana Bread

Cinnamon Banana Bread

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
190
Servings
10
Ingredients

3 ripe bananas
7 eggs
1 scoop whey protien powder
1/4 c. coconut oil, melted
2 tsp. vanilla
1/2 c. almond flour
1/4 c. coconut flour
1 T. cinnamon
1/2 tsp. pink salt
3/4 tsp. baking soda

Directions
  1. Preheat oven to 350 degr.ees
  2. Grease 9x5 inch loaf pan.
  3. Combine bananas and eggs in blender.
  4. Pulse in coconut oil, vanilla, salt, and baking soda until well incorporated.
  5. Add coconut flour, almond flour, and protein powder and blend until combined.
  6. Pulse in cinnamon.
  7. Pour batter into loaf pan.
  8. Bake for 45-55 minutes.
  9. Allow to cool before slicing with sharp knife.

Fajita Fritatta

Jump To Recipe

Flipping this yummy oil-free Fajita Frittata can be as tricky as trying to say it's name five times fast, but I have a frittata flipping secret hack that I like to use and am gonna share with you...

 

I find it is incredibly hard to flip eggs with a spatula because they tend to break of where they aren't being supported by the spatula. And I don't even want to think about how disasterous it would be if I tried to do the flip with just a flick of the wrist like the pros do! 

 

The way I like to perform the flip is by placing a lid on top of the skillet then carefully but quickly turning the skillet over (which transfers the eggs onto the lid) and then gently sliding the eggs off the lid and back into skillet. Works like a charm every time for an egg flip that actually holds together!!

Fajita Fritatta

Dietary
Oil Free
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
215
Servings
1
Ingredients

2 bell peppers, sliced thin
1 egg
1/2 c. liquid egg whites
1 T. Taco Seasoning
2 T. salsa

Directions
  1. Cook pepper slices, covered, in skillet with a few tablespoons of water until softened.
  2. Whisk together egg and egg whites with Taco Seasoning then pour over peppers in skillet.
  3. Cover and cook until bubbling.
  4. Carefully flip frittata.
  5. Cover and cook another minute or two on the other side.
  6. Transfer to plate and top with salsa.
  7. Sprinkle with additional Taco Seasoning, if desired.

Kelly's Krazy Breadsticks

Try out these delicious low carb, sugar free breadsticks! I think you will love them. Dunk them into my "cheesy" tomato sauce if you are looking for a great side dish for your pasta or salad. In this recipe we used Viva Natural Coconut Powder and grass fed whey protein powder. Let us know in the comment section how it turns out!

Jump To Recipe

This was actually my second attempt at perfecting this recipe since the first batch I tried turned out to taste slightly eggy and the consistency just wasn't quite what I was hoping for. Don't get me wrong, they were still delicious (and every single one got eaten quickly) but they needed a bit of tweaking. 

This time, I think got it right and let me tell ya I'm crazy about Kelly's Krazy Breadsticks!!! I chose to sprinkle a little bit of garlic powder and black pepper on top and used marinara sauce as a dip, but you could easily play around with additional spices and toppings. The Spice Gal's Homestyle Ranch or Taste of Italy would both be super yummy options to try! 

As I was taste testing, I almost forgot that these Krazy Breadsticks are gluten-free, low carb, and packed with protein. In just 2 breadsticks, you get almost 20 grams of protein and only 8 grams of carbs...KRAZY ;) I am brainstorming now how I may be able to possibly convert this into a pizza crust recipe as well....I'll keep ya posted. In any event, I'm pretty sure this is a recipe that will be getting remade often in my house! 

Kelly's Krazy Breadsticks

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
95
Servings
20
Ingredients
  • 2 c. cottage cheese,
  • 7 eggs,
  • ¾ c. coconut flour,
  • 1 ½ tsp. baking powder,
  • ¾ tsp. pink salt,
  • 2 scoops whey protein powder,
  • 1 T. coconut oil,
  • 1/4 c. parmesan cheese,
  • Optional: pepper, pink salt, garlic powder, oregano, etc,
Directions
  1. Preheat oven to 400 degrees and grease 2 (11x7 inch) pans.
  2. In blender, combine eggs and cottage cheese until smooth.
  3. Pulse in baking powder, salt, coconut flour and protein powder, scraping down sides as needed.
  4. Pour half of batter into each pan.
  5. Bake for 15 minutes.
  6. Remove from oven and brush 1/2 tablespoon of coconut oil on top of each pan.
  7. Sprinkle 2 tablespoons of parmesan cheese evenly on top along with any additional desired spices.
  8. Place back into oven for 3-5 minutes.
  9. Remove from oven and cut with sharp knife or pizza cutter.

Chocolate Pecan Protein Fluff

Jump To Recipe

The Black Raspberry Protein Fluff I made for dessert the other night was such a delightful sugar-free treat that I decided to make it again last night, but with one twist little twist: I wanted to see if there was a way to omit fruit from the recipe, but still have a similar fluffy finished product.

 

I attempted to use frozen chopped spinach instead of frozen fruit and.... it worked!!! I had to process it a little bit longer than when I use fruit, but the spinach did eventually incorporate in pretty well. I also threw in some chopped pecans to add a little more texture and bit of crunch to this batch. 

 

Most people have heard of potassium and know our bodies need it, but do you know why?

 

Well, potassium is an electrolyte, a substance that conducts electricity in the body. It is crucial to heart function and plays a key role in muscle contraction, which makes it important for normal digestive and muscular function. Sounds pretty important, right?! Along with reducing the sugar content in the recipe, adding spinach made this a potassium packed treat since 1 cup of frozen spinach contains almost 600 mg of potassium. That makes this recipe a winnder in my book!

Chocolate Pecan Protein Fluff

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
200
Servings
1
Ingredients

1/4 c. unsweetened almond milk
1 c. frozen chopped spinach
1/4 c. chocolate whey protein powder
1/8 c. chopped pecans
cocoa powder, optional

Directions
  1. Pulse spinach in food processor until broken up.
  2. Add almond milk and continue to process until well combined.
  3. Add protein powder and process another couple minutes until fluffy and smooth.
  4. Pulse in additional cocoa powder, if desired.
  5. Fold in chopped pecans. 

Basil Chicken Soup

Jump To Recipe

Although it is officialy Spring, it has been damp and cold in State College recently. When this type of weather strikes, I am often motivated to make a healthy, hearty soup of some sort. I love soups because they can be filled with nutritious veggies, fill ya up, and not be super high on the caloric intake.


For this oil-free, sugar-free, gluten-free soup, I raided my freezer and kitchen cabinets (mainly because my fridge was looking a bit sparse and I was feeling too lazy to make a trip to the grocery store in the yucky weather). I decided to throw the pearl onions into the mix at the last minute, which I think was a good call! I know a lot of people aren't onion fans though, so they could easily be omitted and you'd still be left with a delicious end product. 

 

I paired my soup with a slice of Pumpkin Thyme Bread which was perfect to soak up every last drop of deliciousness in my bowl. I'm thinking I will probably have some of the leftovers (which there were a lot of because I can never seem to make small batches of soup) with Zucchini Biscuits later on this week.....yay for leftovers!!!

 

Basil Chicken Soup

Dietary
Oil Free
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
170 (180 w/ onions)
Servings
4
Ingredients

10 oz. frozen chopped spinach
1 (28 oz.) can diced tomatoes, undrained
1 (13 oz.) can chicken breast, undrained
1 T. basil
2 tsp. minced garlic flakes
1 tsp. Simple Girl Dry Bouillon Base
1 c. water
1 c. frozen pearl onions, optional

Directions
  1. Heat spinach in saucepan over medium-high heat until softened and broken apart.
  2. Stir in tomatoes, chicken, basil, bouillon, garlic, and water.
  3. Turn burner to high heat and bring to a boil.
  4. Add onions, if desired, then reduce heat and cover with lid.
  5. Allow to simmer at least 10 minutes.

Creamy Lemon Herb Sauce

Jump To Recipe

The other night, I cooked up some bay scallops in my NuWave the for dinner. I simply seasoned the scallops with pink salt and pepper then sauteed a pile of coleslaw mix in some coconut oil to use as a bed underneath and whipped up a delicious sugar-free Creamy Lemon Herb Sauce to go with it.

 

This meal turned out to be extremely satisfying and filling with the total calorie count coming in under 400! I actually wish I had made a double batch so I would have had leftovers to take to work with me sometime during the week.

 

Side Note: If you have never heard of the NuWave before, you should definitely look into it. This is, by far, my favorite kitchen gadget and it the easiest way I've found to cook my scallops and shrimp without them coming out undercooked or overcooked and rubbery. You just throw your frozen scallops on the rack (I put down a piece of foil to make for easier cleanup) and set the timer for 8-10 minutes, flipping halfway through. 

Creamy Lemon Herb Sauce

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
130
Servings
3
Ingredients

1/2 c. coconut cream
1/4 c. nutritional yeast
1/2 tsp. Simple Girl Lemon Herb Seasoning
1/2 tsp. garlic powder
pink salt and pepper, to taste
1/2-1 T. lemon juice
water, as needed

Directions
  1. Heat coconut cream skillet over medium-low heat.
  2. Stir in nutritional yeast and spices.
  3. Add water if thinner consistency is desired.
  4. Keep on burner, stirring occasionally, until heated through.
  5. Whisk in lemon juice and adjust seasonings, to taste.

Carrot Tortillas

Jump To Recipe

My husband came across the Red Pepper Tortillas recipe when he was looking through Inside Kelly's Kitchen and asked if I could make them for dinner last night. I told him I would, but didn't realize at the time that we only had one red pepper left in the fridge. So, when I got home from work, I had to get the creative juices flowing. I decided to try to sub the red peppers for carrots and the result was these Carrot Tortillas. The fact that they are gluten-free and have veggies hidden in them is a huge plus to me!

 

I had to tweak the original recipe a little bit because the carrots turned the batter into more of a puree than a liquid consistency. I figured that adding some extra egg whites would do the trick to thin out the batter and help hold the tortillas together. After that, I was worried the mixture may taste too eggy so I also added in a little bit of coconut flour.

 

I recently found Tortilla Pans at the Dollar Tree, so I figured I'd try them out and make our meal even more exciting by making some tortilla bowls. To do this, placed a tortilla in the pan, popped it into the toaster oven, and set the dial for Dark. To be honest, I'm not sure exactly how long it toasted for. I recommend to just keep an eye on the toaster oven and remove it once the edges are starting to crisp up. 

 

The tortilla bowls held up quite nicely and I filled them with a Spicy Shrimp Taco mixture. (I think they could actually pass for taco shells as well if you don't fill them up quite as much as I did and then just gently fold them around the mixture you put inside!)

Carrot Tortillas

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
120
Servings
4
Ingredients

1 can (~1 1/2 c) sliced carrots
1/2 c. liquid egg whites
1 egg
2 T. whey protein powder
2 T. golden flax meal
1 T. coconut flour

Directions
  1. Spray skillet or grease with coconut oil.
  2. Pulse all ingredients in blender cup until well combined.
  3. Pour 1/2 cup of batter into skillet and shape into thin circle with spatula.
  4. Place lid on skillet and cook over medium heat until bubbly.
  5. Carefully flip tortilla then cover and cook other side.
  6. Press down with spatula to flatten.
  7. Repeat with remaining batter.

Black Raspberry Protein Fluff

Jump To Recipe

I love, love, LOVE the consistency of Cool Whip! I'll even shamefully admit that I used to buy the tub when I was in college and eat it like ice cream. Unfortunately, store-bought whipped topping is loaded with a bunch of nasty chemicals and toxins that we really should not be ingesting...

 

WATER, HYDROGENATED VEGETABLE OIL (COCONUT & PALM KERNEL OILS), HIGH FRUCTOSE CORN SYRUP, CORN SYRUP, SKIM MILK, CONTAINS LESS THAN 2% OF LIGHT CREAM, SODIUM CASEINATE, NATURAL AND ARTIFICIAL FLAVOR, XANTHAN AND GUAR GUMS, POLYSORBATE 60, SORBITAN MONOSTEARATE, SODIUM POLYPHOSPHATE, BETA CAROTENE (COLOR).

 

I don't know about you, but I am not really too hip on raising my cholesterol (thank you vegetable oils), spiking my blood sugar (hat's off to the high fructose corn syrup), and eating wax (yes, you read that right...sorbitan monostearate is a chemically-derived substance commonly referred to as “synthetic wax”) to enjoy a little bit of this light, fluffy treat.

 

Instead, I've found a way to create a version in my own kitchen that is delicious, sugar-free, and even full of protein! Black Raspberry Protein Fluff can made in a matter of minutes, is extremely satisfying, and is guilt-free. Doesn't get much better than that!!!

 

(But, actually, IT DOES because you can make this recipe using a varity of flavor combos. You can use different frozen fruits, flavored protein powders, cocoa powder, cinnamon, or even add in some nuts, chocolate chips, nut butter, or fruit pieces. The possibilities of fluffy goodness are endless!)

Black Raspberry Protein Fluff

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
150
Servings
1
Ingredients

2/3 c. frozen blackberries
1/3 c. frozen raspberries
1/4 c. unsweetened almond milk
1/4 c. vanilla whey protein powder

Directions
  1. Pulse berries in food processor until broken up.
  2. Add almond milk and continue to process until well combined.
  3. Add protein powder and process another couple minutes until fluffy and smooth.

Pumpkin Thyme Bread

Pumpkin Thyme Bread

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
160
Servings
1
Ingredients

1 c. canned pumpkin
5 eggs
1/4 c. coconut oil, melted
1/4 c. coconut flour
½ c. almond flour
2 scoops whey protein powder
1 tsp. nutmeg
2 tsp. thyme
½ tsp. pink salt
2 tsp. baking powder
 

Directions
  1. Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
  2. Grease loaf pan.
  3. Place coconut oil, eggs, and pumpkin in blender and blend until combined.
  4. Add baking powder, nutmeg, thyme, and pink salt.
  5. Pulse in almond flour, protein powder, and coconut flour.
  6. Transfer batter into loaf pan.
  7. Bake for 50 minutes.
  8. Remove from oven and allow to cool before slicing.

Lemon Dill Dressing

Lemon Dill Dressing

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
30
Servings
4
Ingredients

1/4 c. canned coconut cream
1 T. apple cider vinegar
2 tsp. lemon juice
1 tsp. dill
1 dropperful stevia (or more, to taste)
4-8 T. water
pink salt and pepper (optional)

 

Directions
  1. Combine all ingredients in small bowl and whisk together (or blend in blender cup).
  2. Add additional water, as needed, for a thinner consistency.
  3. Adjust seasonings, to taste.

Soft-Baked Maple Spice Cookies

Soft-Baked Maple Spice Cookies

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
75
Servings
24
Ingredients

3 ripe bananas
⅓ c. + 1 T. nut butter of choice
1 ½ c. almond flour
2 tsp. maple extract
1 tsp. ginger
1/4 tsp. cloves

Directions

Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Line baking sheet with parchment paper.
Mash bananas with fork or pulse in food processor until smooth.
Mix in nut butter until completely smooth.
Add almond flour, maple extract, and spices.
Drop onto baking sheet 1 tablespoon at a time and shape into circle with back of spoon.
Bake for 20 minutes or until edges start to brown.
Remove from oven and transfer cookies to wire cooling rack.

Banana Bread Cookies

Banana Bread Cookies

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
75
Servings
24
Ingredients

3 ripe bananas
⅓ c. + 1 T. nut butter of choice
1 ½ c. almond flour
2 tsp. vanilla extract
2 tsp. cinnamon
 

Directions
  1. Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
  2. Line baking sheet with parchment paper.
  3. Mash bananas with fork or pulse in food processor until smooth.
  4. Mix in nut butter until completely smooth.
  5. Add almond flour, cinnamon, and vanilla.
  6. Drop onto baking sheet 1 tablespoon at a time and shape into circle with back of spoon.
  7. Bake for 20 minutes or until edges start to brown.
  8. Remove from oven and transfer cookies to wire cooling rack.

Chocolate Brownie Bite Protein Nice Cream

Chocolate Brownie Bite Protein Nice Cream

Dietary
Low Carb
Calories per serving
215
Servings
6
Ingredients

Brownie Bites
1 c. black beans, drained and rinsed
2 T. IMO fiber 
2 T. whey protein powder 
2 T. egg white protein powder 
1/8 tsp. pink salt
1/4 tsp. baking powder
1 1/2 T. cocoa powder 
1 T. coconut oil 

Chocolate Protein Nice Cream
6 frozen bananas
6 T. unsweetened cocoa powder
2 scoops whey protein powder

Directions
  1. Preheat oven to 350 degrees and grease loaf pan.
  2. Process black beans, IMO fiber, and coconut oil in food processor until smooth.
  3. Add baking powder, cocoa powder, pink salt, and protein powders then process again.
  4. Pour batter into loaf pan.
  5. Bake for 20-25 minutes.
  6. Remove from oven and allow to cool.
  7. Process bananas in food processor until smooth, scraping sides down as needed.
  8. Add cocoa powder and process until well incorporated.
  9. Add protein powder and process until smooth and fluffy.
  10. Cut brownies into 1/4 inch cubes.
  11. Fold brownie bites into Nice Cream.
  12. Transfer to tupperware container and place in freezer until ready to serve.

Not Quite Veggie Burgers

Not Quite Veggie Burgers

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
165
Servings
4
Ingredients

6 oz. ground turkey
1 c. steamed broccoli
2 eggs
2 c. diced mushrooms
1/4 c. almond flour
2 T. nutritional yeast
1/4 tsp. thyme
1/2 tsp. sage
1/4 tsp. garlic powder
1/2 tsp. paprika
1/2 tsp. onion powder
1/2 tsp. pink salt
 

Directions
  1. Preheat oven to 350 degrees. 
  2. Drain broccoli in collander and wring out excess liquid.
  3. Combine turkey, broccoli, eggs, and mushrooms in food processor until well incorporated.
  4. Add in almond flour, spices, and nutritional yeast and process again.
  5. Form into 4 patties and place on cookie sheet.
  6. Bake for 10 minutes.
  7. Remove from oven, flip, then bake another 5 minutes. 
  8. Remove from oven, flip again, then bake another 5 minutes. 

Broccoli Cheese Sausage Poppers

Broccoli Cheese Sausage Poppers

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
250 (~40 per popper)
Servings
4 (6 poppers each)
Ingredients

1 lb. ground turkey (or other meat of choice)
4 c. steamed broccoli
2 eggs
1 1/2 tsp. sage
1 tsp. garlic powder
1 tsp. fennel seeds
1 tsp. thyme
1/2 tsp. pink salt
1/4 c. nutritional yeast

Directions
  1. Preheat oven to 350 degrees and line cookie sheet with parchment paper.
  2. Drain steamed broccoli in collander and wring out excess water.
  3. Place broccoli and ground meat in food processor and process until well-combined.
  4. Add eggs, nutritional yeast, and spices and continue to process.
  5. Form into 24 mounds on cookie sheet.
  6. Bake for 25-30 minutes until beginning to brown.

Buffalo Chicken Meatloaf

Buffalo Chicken Meatloaf

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
160
Servings
8
Ingredients

1 1/2 lbs. ground chicken
1 c. diced mushrooms
1/2 c. diced celery
1/4 c. diced onion
1/3 c. feta cheese (or bleu cheese) + 2 T. for topping
1/2 c. unsweetened almond milk
1/2 c. hot sauce + 3 T. for topping 
3 eggs
1/2 tsp. pink salt
1/4 tsp. garlic powder
1/2 tsp. parsley
1/4 tsp. dill
1/8 tsp. pepper

Directions
  1. Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
  2. In food processor, combine chicken, mushrooms, celery, onion, and cheese.
  3. Whisk together eggs, milk, hot sauce, and spices in large bowl. 
  4. Add meat mixture to bowl and mix with hands until well incorporated.
  5. Transfer mixture into loaf pan and press down firmly.
  6. Brush top with remaining 3 T. hot sauce.
  7. Bake for 1 hour.
  8. Remove from oven and sprinkle with remaining 2 T. cheese and bake another 5 minutes.
  9. Remove from oven and let sit for at least 10 minutes before slicing.

    *Alternatively, roll into meatballs and bake on cookie sheet for 15-20 minutes.

Shaky No-Parm Cheese

40

Directions

  3. Store in refrigerator or at room temperature.

Veggie Sesame Ginger Orange Lo Mein

Veggie Sesame Ginger Orange Lo Mein

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
195
Servings
2
Ingredients

1 T. coconut oil
2 large portabella caps
1 orange
2 tsp. sesame oil
1 ½ tsp. ground ginger
1/2 tsp. garlic powder
6 c. coleslaw mix
pink salt, to taste

Directions
  1. Heat coconut oil in skillet over med-high heat.
  2. Cut mushroom and orange into bite sized pieces and add to skillet.
  3. Cover and cook until mushrooms are soft.
  4. Stir in coleslaw mix then cover and continue cooking until coleslaw mix is soft and noodle-like.
  5. Add sesame oil, ginger, and garlic powder and stir until well-coated.
  6. Top with pink salt.

Balsamic Herbed Apples

Balsamic Herbed Apples

Dietary
Oil Free
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
110
Servings
1
Ingredients

Directions

Southwest Turkey Meatball Stir Fry

Southwest Turkey Meatball Stir Fry

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
465
Servings
1
Ingredients

4 oz ground turkey breast
1/2-1 tsp. McCormick Southwest Seasoning
1 small zucchini
1 large porabella mushroom cap
1 c. coleslaw mix
1 (14.5 oz) can diced tomatoes, drained
1 T. coconut oil
1/4 tsp. garlic powder
1/2 tsp. onion powder
1 tsp. minced dried onion
pink salt, to taste

Directions
  1. Preheat oven to 375 degrees.
  2. Mix turkey and southwest seasoning together and form into 6 balls.
  3. Place meatballs on cookie sheet and bake for 15 minutes.
  4. Heat coconut oil in large skillet.
  5. Cut zucchini and mushroom into bited sized pieces and add to skillet.
  6. Stir in coleslaw mix, garlic powder, onion powder, and minced onion. 
  7. Cover and cook, stirring occasionally, until veggies are tender.
  8. Stir in tomatoes and meatballs and cook until warmed through.
  9. Top with pink salt.

Easy Deep Dish Cookie

Easy Deep Dish Cookie

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
160 calories + add-ins
Servings
2
Ingredients

¼ c. almond flour
½ banana, mashed
1 T. nut butter of choice
Optional add-ins: chocolate chips, raisins, nuts, coconut flakes, cacao/cocoa powder, peppermint extract, etc

Directions
  1. Grease microwave/oven safe bowl.
  2. Combine almond flour, banana, and nut butter until well incorporated.
  3. Stir in any desired add-ins.
  4. Spoon batter into bowl and spread evenly into circle (may not cover entire bottom of bowl).
  5. Microwave for 3 minutes or bake at 350 degrees for 20-30 minutes.
  6. Remove cookie from bowl with fork or spatula.
  7. Slice in half (or eat the entire cookie).

PB&J Protein Nice Cream

PB&J Protein Nice Cream

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
195
Servings
2
Ingredients

2 c. frozen blueberries
1 scoop (~½ c.) whey protein powder
1 T. nut butter of choice

Directions
  1. Place blueberries in food processor and pulse a few times until mixture is all chopped up
  2. Turn food processor on med-high to high and process until blueberries combine and becomes the consistency of ice cream, scraping sides as needed.
  3. Add protein powder and process until smooth and creamy.
  4. Pulse in peanut butter (or other nut butter of choice).
  5. Place in freezer for a few minutes if thicker consistency is desired.

Chocolate Peanut Butter Chocolate Chunk Protein Nice Cream

Chocolate Peanut Butter Chocolate Chunk Protein Nice Cream

Dietary
Low Carb
Calories per serving
240
Servings
2
Ingredients

1 frozen banana
1 T. unsweetened cacao/cocoa powder
1 scoop unflavored whey protein powder (or other protein powder of choice)
1 T. natural peanut butter
1 T. coconut oil chocolate chunks

Directions
  1. Process banana in food processor until smooth creamy consistency is reached, scraping sides as needed.
  2. Add protein powder and cacao powder then process again until well combined.
  3. Pulse in peanut butter.
  4. Stir in chocolate chunks.
  5. Place in freezer to harden, if desired.

Nacho-Average Cheese Sauce

Nacho-Average Cheese Sauce

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
150 calories
Servings
8 servings (¼ c. each)
Ingredients

1 c. raw cashews
½-1 c. water
½ orange pepper, chopped
¼ c. nutritional yeast
½ tsp. garlic powder
¼ tsp. chili powder
¼ tsp. smoked paprika
1 tsp. pink salt
½ c. unsweetened almond milk
¼ tsp. xanthan gum

Directions
  1. Place cashews in bowl and cover with water.
  2. Allow to sit for at least 30 minutes.
  3. Rinse cashews and transfer to blender cup with ½ cup water, chopped pepper, nutritional yeast, spices, and almond milk.
  4. Process until very smooth, adding more water if too thick.
  5. Add xanthan gum and process again.

Chocolate Cake Donuts

Chocolate Cake Donuts

Dietary
Low Carb
Calories per serving
230 (260 w/ honey)
Servings
6
Ingredients

1 ½ c. almond flour
⅓ c.  FiberYum IMO syrup (or honey)
3 eggs
1 T. vanilla
½ tsp. baking soda
2 T. cocoa powder

Directions
  1. Preheat oven to 350 degrees.

Trail Bars

Dietary
Sugar Free

Calories per serving
205
Servings
24

Eggplant Parm

Eggplant Parm

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
245
Servings
4
Ingredients

1 eggplant
1 T. coconut flour
¼ c. golden flax meal
2 tsp. Italian seasoning
½ tsp. garlic powder
1 egg
¼ c. coconut oil
¼ c. tomato paste
¼ - ⅓ c. water
2 T. nutritional yeast
pink salt, to taste
 

Directions
  1. Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
  2. Whisk egg in bowl.
  3. Combine coconut flour, flax meal, italian seasoning, and garlic powder in separate bowl.
  4. Slice eggplant into ¼ inch rounds.
  5. Melt coconut oil in skillet over med-high heat.
  6. Dip eggplant slice in egg then transfer to other bowl and coat with breading mixture.
  7. Transfer to skillet and cook evenly on both sides, until golden brown.
  8. Repeat with remaining eggplant slices and place on greased baking sheet.
  9. Stir together tomato paste, water, nutritional yeast, and pink salt until thick sauce is formed.
  10. Top each eggplant slice with sauce and spread to coat.
  11. Bake for 5-10 minutes.

Cherry Chocolate Protein Cookies

Cherry Chocolate Protein Cookies

Dietary
Low Carb
Calories per serving
35
Servings
12
Ingredients

¼ c. whey protein powder
½ c. unsweetened cocoa powder
¼ c. honey
1 tsp. almond extract

Directions

Almond Grahams

Almond Grahams

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
70
Servings
25
Ingredients

2 1/4 c. almond meal
1 tsp. baking powder
1 tsp. cinnamon
1/2 tsp. pink salt
1 egg
2 T. coconut oil, melted
3 dropperfuls vanilla creme stevia

Directions
  1. Preheat oven to 325 degrees.
  2. Line cookie sheet with parchment paper.
  3. In large bowl, whisk almond meal, baking powder, cinnamon and salt.
  4. Add egg, coconut oil and stevia, stirring until blended into dough (can also do this in food processor).
  5. Cover bowl and chill for 30 min.
  6. Transfer chilled dough to large sheet of parchment paper; top with a second sheet of parchment paper.
  7. Using rolling pin, roll the dough to ⅛-inch thickness.
  8. Using knife or pizza cutter, cut into squares/rectangles.
  9. Transfer to cookie sheet.
  10. Bake for 12-15 minutes, until golden brown (will still look slightly soft and will harden as they cool).
  11. Cool 5 minutes then transfer to a wire rack to cool completely.
  12. Store in airtight container.

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving

Servings
8 (1/4 c. each)

Mexican Goulash

Mexican Goulash

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
305
Servings
2
Ingredients

8 oz. lean ground beef
12 oz. frozen chopped peppers
1 chopped onion

Directions

Sesame Garlic Cauliflower

Sesame Garlic Cauliflower

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
140
Servings
3
Ingredients

1 small head cauliflower, chopped 
1/3 c. liquid aminos
1/4 c. water
1/4 c. date paste
1/4 c. rice vinegar
1 T. minced garlic
1 1/2 tsp. toasted sesame oil
1/2 tsp. ginger
1/2 tsp. xanthan gum
1 tsp. sesame seeds
scallions (optional) for garnish

Directions
  1. Preheat oven to 450 degrees. 
  2. Line baking sheet with parchment paper.
  3. Cut cauliflower into florets then place in single layer on baking sheet.
  4. Bake 10 minutes.
  5. Whisk together aminos, water, date paste, vinegar, garlic, sesame oil, and ginger in saucepan until beginning to boil.
  6. Whisk in xanthan gum then lower heat and cook 2 minutes.
  7. Flip cauliflower and bake 8 additional minutes.
  8. Pour sauce over cauliflower then bake another 3 minutes. 
  9. Remove from oven then top with sesame seeds and scallions.

Mushroom Cream Sauce

Mushroom Cream Sauce

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
85
Servings
8 (1/2 c. each)
Ingredients

1 T. coconut oil
8 oz. sliced mushrooms
12 oz. steamed cauliflower (about 4 c.)
1 T. minced garlic
1/2 c. chopped onion
2/3 c. coconut cream
2 T. nutritional yeast
pink salt and pepper, to taste

Directions
  1. Melt coconut oil in skillet over med-high heat.
  2. Saute mushrooms, garlic, and onions until softened.
  3. Pulse steamed cauliflower, coconut cream, nutritional yeast, pink salt, and pepper in blender until smooth and well combined. 
  4. Add cauliflower mixture to skillet and stir.

12
Ingredients

1¼ c. almond flour
¼ c. oat flour
3 T. coconut flour
⅛ tsp. pink salt
1 tsp. cinnamon (divided)
½ tsp. ginger (divided)
⅓ c. date paste
3 T. coconut oil (divided)
2 T. plain Greek yogurt
½ c. chopped pecans
½ tsp. baking soda
½ tsp. baking powder
2 eggs
1 tsp. vanilla extract
2 T. orange zest (from about two oranges)
½ c. orange puree (1 orange blended)
2 dropperfuls orange stevia
1 c. fresh cranberries

Directions
  1. Preheat oven to 325 degrees.
  2. Grease 8"x8" baking pan or line with parchment paper.
  3. In food processor, pulse almond flour, oat flour, coconut flour, salt, ½ teaspoon cinnamon, and ¼ teaspoon ginger until combined.
  4. Add 2 Tablespoons melted coconut oil, date paste, and Greek yogurt, and pulse until well combined.
  5. Transfer mixture to large bowl and set aside.
  6. For the topping, return ½ cup of flour mixture to food processor.
  7. Add pecans, remaining 1 Tablespoon coconut oil, and additional cinnamon and ginger, and pulse to combine and form loose crumbs.
  8. Stir baking soda and baking powder into large bowl of dry mixture.
  9. Add eggs, vanilla, orange zest, orange stevia and orange puree and stir until smooth.
  10. Fold in cranberries.
  11. Pour batter into prepared pan.
  12. Sprinkle pecan crumb mixture evenly over top of batter and press down slightly.
  13. Bake 50-60 minutes, until toothpick inserted in middle comes out clean.
  14. Cool cake completely.
  15. Store, covered, in the refrigerator for up to 4 days.

Oatmeal Banana Bars

Oatmeal Banana Bars

Dietary
Low Carb
Calories per serving
75 (85 w/ honey)
Servings
20
Ingredients

2 1/4 c. oats
1/2 tsp. baking powder
1/2 tsp. baking soda
1/4 tsp. pink salt
1 tsp. cinnamon
3 medium ripe bananas
1 dropperful vanilla stevia
1/4 c. unsweetened applesauce
1/4 c. IMO syrup (or honey)
1/3 c. Dark Chocolate Enjoy Life chocolate chips

Directions
  1. Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
  2. Grease 8x8 inch baking pan.
  3. Place oats in blender or food processor and pulse until flour consistency is reached.
  4. Transfer to medium bowl and whisk in baking powder, baking soda, salt and cinnamon then set aside.
  5. Place bananas, vanilla, applesauce, and honey into blender and blend until smooth.
  6. Pour banana mixture into oat flour mixture and mix until just combined.
  7. Gently fold in chocolate chips.
  8. Pour batter into pan and spread evenly with spatula.
  9. Bake 15 minutes or until knife inserted into center comes out clean.
  10. Cool 10-15 minutes then cut into squares.

Golden Flax Pizza Crust

Golden Flax Pizza Crust

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
410 (Personal Pan) or 160 (Full Size)
Servings
1 (Personal Pan) or 8 (Full Size)
Ingredients

Personal Pan Size:
⅓ c. golden flax meal
1 ½ T. coconut flour
1 egg
½ tsp. baking powder
pinch of pink salt
1 T. coconut oil, melted

Full Size:
1 c. golden flax meal
¼ c. + 1 ½ tsp. coconut flour
3 eggs
1 ½ tsp. baking powder
½ tsp. pink salt
3 T. coconut oil, melted

Directions
  1. Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
  2. Whisk together egg, coconut oil, baking soda, and salt.
  3. Stir in flax meal and coconut flour until dough forms.
  4. Spread dough out on parchment lined baking sheet, leaving edges slightly thicker for crust.
  5. Bake 15 minutes or until turns golden brown.

Date Paste

Date Paste

Dietary
Low Carb
Calories per serving
35
Servings
12 (1 T each)
Ingredients

1 c. lightly packed pitted dates  (14-16 dates)
2/3 c. boiling water

Directions
  1. Combine dates and hot water in a bowl and let sit for 1 minute. Massage with fingers to help soften.
  2. Place dates and all the liquid in a blender and process for 30 seconds or until completely smooth.
  3. Store in a closed container in the fridge.

Pumpkin Chocolate Chip Oatmeal Cookies

Pumpkin Chocolate Chip Oatmeal Cookies

Dietary
Low Carb
Calories per serving
110
Servings
20

Minty Thin Cookies

Dietary
Low Carb
Calories per serving
35
Servings
12
Ingredients

¼ c. FiberYum IMO syrup
3 dropperfuls SweetLeaf peppermint stevia
2 T. Enjoy Life chocolate chips

Directions
  1. Preheat oven to 395 degrees.
  2. Line baking sheet with parchment paper.
  3. Combine protein powder, cocoa powder, IMO syrup, and stevia in bowl with spoon until soft dough forms.

This recipe is a perfect way to dress up your next pasta dinner or just a great simple dipping sauce for Kellys Krazy Breadsticks. The star of this recipe is Anthony's Nutritional Yeast Flakes. They are what gives the sauce it's cheesy flavor even though it's still dairy free! Organic Northern Italian Seasoning has that perfect Italian taste, and for the garlic powder you can never go wrong with McCormick Classic Garlic Powder.

Creamed Greens Dip

Creamed Greens Dip

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
95
Servings
12
Ingredients

3 T. coconut oil (divided)
½ small yellow onion
1 clove garlic, minced
1 c. kale, chopped
1 c. collard greens, chopped
1 c. swiss chard, chopped
1 c. spinach, chopped
¾ -1 tsp. xanthan gum
1 c. unsweetened almond milk
1 c. canned coconut milk
½ tsp. nutmeg
¼ c. parmesan cheese (or other cheese of choice)
pink salt and pepper, to taste

Directions
  1. Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
  2. Melt 1 tablespoon coconut oil in skillet.
  3. Cook onion and garlic until translucent.
  4. Add greens and cook until beginning to wilt.
  5. Transfer mixture to baking dish.
  6. In saucepan, melt remaining 2 tablespoons coconut oil.
  7. Stir in almond milk, coconut cream, nutmeg, and xanthan gum.
  8. Remove sauce from stovetop and stir into greens.
  9. Top with cheese, salt, and pepper.
  10. Bake for 10 minutes or until cheese starts to brown

Kale Veggie Soup

Kale Veggie Soup

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
185
Servings
2
Ingredients

1 tsp. coconut oil
4 c. water
2 tsp. Simple Girl Dry Bouillon Base
15 baby carrots
1 clove garlic, minced
2 c. kale
⅔ c. frozen roasted corn
½ c. frozen shelled edamame
pink salt and pepper, to taste

Directions
  1. Melt coconut oil in large saucepan.
  2. Chop carrots and kale then place in saucepan along with garlic.

  6. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.

Cruciferous Seafood Risotto

Cruciferous Seafood Risotto

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
135
Servings
4
Ingredients

1 T. coconut oil
2 c. finely chopped (riced) cauliflower
2 c. finely chopped (riced) broccoli

½ tsp. xanthan gum

Doughy Gluten-Free Pizza Crust

Doughy Gluten-Free Pizza Crust

Dietary
Low Carb
Calories per serving
160
Servings
8
Ingredients

2 c. oat flour
2 tsp. baking powder
1 c. warm water
1 T. coconut oil, melted
2 T. golden flax meal
¼ c. coconut flour

Directions
  1. Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
  2. Whisk together coconut oil, baking powder, and warm water.
  3. In separate bowl, combine oat flour, flax meal, and coconut flour.
  4. Stir wet ingredients into dry until dough forms.
  5. Form into a ball and refrigerate for at least 5 minutes.
  6. Knead dough for a minutes then press out in thin layer to desired shape, leaving crust region double the thickness.
  7. Bake the crust for 10-15 minutes, until beginning to turn golden brown.
  8. Top with desired ingredients and bake another 5-10 minutes.

Fluffy Focaccia

Fluffy Focaccia

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
185
Servings
12
Ingredients

1 1/2 c. flax meal
1/2 c. coconut flour
1 T. baking powder
1 tsp. pink salt
5 eggs, beaten
1 c. water
1/3 c. coconut oil, melted
spices of choice (optional)

Directions
  1. Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
  2. Line 9x13 inch baking sheet with parchment paper or silicone baking mat.
  3. Combine eggs, coconut oil, and water in blender.
  4. Pulse in pink salt and baking powder. 
  5. Pulse in flax meal and coconut flour (alternatively combine in large bowl), scraping sides down as needed.
  6. Scoop mixture onto baking sheet (Do NOT let sit too long or it will get very thick).
  7. Spread evenly with spatula.
  8. Sprinkle with spices, if desired.
  9. Bake for 25 minutes or until starting to brown.
  10. Cut into slices with pizza cutter or knife.

Chocolate Strawberry Dream Bars

Chocolate Strawberry Dream Bars

Dietary
Low Carb
Calories per serving
100
Servings
20
Ingredients

Base:
1 (14 oz.) can black beans
2 eggs
1/2 c. unsweetened applesauce
1/2 c. pitted dates
1 tsp. vanilla extract
1/2 c. unsweetened cocoa powder
1/4 tsp. pink salt
1/2 tsp. baking soda
1 tsp. instant coffee granules

Filling: 
2 c. (4% fat) Daisy cottage cheese
3 c. frozen sliced strawberries
1/3 c. canned coconut cream
3/4 tsp. almond extract
1 tsp. xanthan gum
4 dropperfuls SweetLeaf vanilla creme stevia

Topping:
1 batch Crispy Crunchy Chocolate Cookies

Directions
  1. Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
  2. Line 13x9 inch baking dish with parchment paper or grease lightly.
  3. Soak dates in hot water for 10 minutes.
  4. Drain dates and add to blender or food processor.
  5. Add all black beans, eggs, applesauce, dates, vanilla extract, cocoa powder, pink salt, baking soda, and instant coffee and process until smooth.
  6. Pour batter into baking dish and smooth out evenly.
  7. Bake for 20 minutes.
  8. Remove from oven and press down with spatula to make more compact.
  9. Place pan in refrigerator.
  10. Combine cottage cheese, strawberries, coconut cream, vanilla stevia, and almond extract in food processor and process until smooth.
  11. Sprinkle xanthan gum on top of mixture and process again.
  12. Spoon mixture onto brownie base and spread evenly with spatula.
  13. Place cookies in food processor and pulse until crumble consistency is reached.
  14. Sprinkle cookie crumbles on top of filling mixture.
  15. Place in freezer for at least 1 hour then transfer to fridge (or store in freezer and allow to defrost at least 20 minutes before serving).

Spicy Sesame Orange Shrimp

Sugar Free

Servings

Fudgy Black Bean Brownies

Fudgy Black Bean Brownies

Dietary
Low Carb
Calories per serving
145
Servings
16
Ingredients

1 (14 oz.) can black beans
2 eggs
1/2 c. unsweetened applesauce
1/2 c. pitted dates
1 tsp. vanilla extract
1/2 c. unsweetened cocoa powder
1/4 tsp. pink salt
1/2 tsp. baking soda
1 tsp. instant coffee granules
1/2 c. Lily's chocolate chips

Directions
  1. Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
  2. Line 8 x 8 square baking dish with parchment paper or foil and grease lightly.
  3. Soak dates in hot water for 10 minutes.
  4. Drain dates and add to blender or food processor.
  5. Add all ingredients, except chocolate chips, to blender or food processor and process until smooth.
  6. Stir in 1/2 cup chocolate chips. 
  7. Pour batter into baking dish and smooth out evenly.
  8. Bake for 30 minutes.
  9. Remove from oven allow to cool for 5 minutes.
  10. Transfer to a cooling rack and let cool completely before slicing.

Spicy Orange Shrimp w/ Asparagus

Spicy Orange Shrimp w/ Asparagus

Dietary
Oil Free
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
280
Servings
1
Ingredients

6 oz raw shrimp
1 orange
2 T. water
1 T. minced garlic
1/8 tsp. cayenne pepper
1/3 tsp. Homemade Old Bay Seasoning
8 oz asparagus
liquid aminos, to taste (optional)
 

Directions
  1. Place peeled orange, garlic, cayenne pepper, and Old Bay Seasoning in blender and blend until smooth.
  2. Heat water in skillet over medium heat.
  3. Pour orange mixture into skillet and bring to simmer for about 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
  4. Steam shrimp and asparagus while sauce is simmering.
  5. Stir cooked shrimp into sauce then serve over asparagus.
  6. Top with liquid aminos, if desired.

Stuffing Balls

Stuffing Balls

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
210
Servings
20
Ingredients

12 c. Focaccia Flax Bread or other bread of choice, cubed (~18 slices)
1 c. diced celery
1/2 c. diced vidalia onion
1 c. peeled, finely chopped apple
1/2 c. coconut oil
1/4 c. water, if needed
1/2 tsp. sage
1 tsp. thyme
pink salt and pepper, to taste

Directions
  1. Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
  2. Melt coconut oil in large saucepan.
  3. Add onion, celery, sage, thyme, pink salt, and pepper.
  4. Cook, stirring occasionally, until onion is translucent.
  5. Add bread cubes to saucepan and stir to absorb all liquid.
  6. Stir in apples.
  7. Portion out about 1/2 cup, forming ball with hands (add water to mixture if bread is not sticking together).
  8. Place stuffing ball onto baking sheet/pan.
  9. Repeat with remaining mixture to form 20 stuffing balls.
  10. Cover pan with with foil.
  11. Bake for 30-45 minutes.
  12. Uncover and bake another 15-20 minutes.

Coconut Flour Focaccia

Coconut Flour Focaccia

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
155
Servings
12
Ingredients

4 eggs
13.5 oz. can full-fat coconut milk, room temperature
½ tsp. xanthan gum
¼ c. coconut oil, melted
1 T. apple cider vinegar
1 T. unsweetened applesauce
1 c. coconut flour, sifted
1 tsp. baking soda
½ tsp. pink salt

Directions
  1. Preheat oven to 350F.
  2. Line 9×13 inch baking sheet with parchment paper.
  3. Place eggs in large bowl and mix, at medium speed, for 2 minutes, until frothy.
  4. Add coconut milk and xanthan gum to blender and blend for 20 seconds, until smooth.
  5. Add coconut milk mixture, coconut oil, vinegar, and applesauce to eggs and mix until just combined.
  6. In separate bowl, mix sifted coconut flour, baking soda and salt.
  7. Add flour mixture into the egg mixture and mix until combined.
  8. Transfer dough to baking sheet.
  9. Spread out and press down with the back of a spoon.
  10. Bake for 45-50 minutes, until toothpick inserted comes out clean.
  11. ​Allow to cool completely.
  12. Cut into slices with pizza cutter or sharp knife. (Individual slices will be thick enough to slice in half again to make a sandwich top and bottom)

Simple Pumpkin Pie

Simple Pumpkin Pie

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
260
Servings
8
Ingredients

15 oz. can pumpkin
3 eggs
1/3 c. canned full fat coconut cream
½ c. unsweetened applesauce
1 T. cinnamon
1 tsp. nutmeg
⅛ tsp. pink salt
⅛ tsp. xanthan gum
1 prebaked Coconut Flour Pie Crust

Directions
  1. Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
  2. In blender, combine pumpkin puree, and eggs.
  3. Pulse in coconut milk, applesauce, cinnamon, nutmeg, salt, and xanthan gum.
  4. Pour filling into crust.
  5. Cover edges of crust with foil.
  6. Bake for 45 minutes.
  7. Remove from oven and allow to cool.
  8. Refrigerate for 2 hours to set.

Pumpkin Banana Oat Bread

Pumpkin Banana Oat Bread

Dietary
Low Carb
Calories per serving
190
Servings
10
Ingredients

2 ripe bananas
4 eggs
1 c. pumpkin puree
1/4 c. honey
1 tsp. vanilla extract
1 3/4 c. oat flour
1/2 c. tapioca flour
1 tsp. baking soda
1/2 tsp. pink salt
1 1/2 tsp. cinnamon
1/4 tsp. nutmeg
1/4 tsp. allspice
1/4 tsp. cloves
1/4 tsp. ginger

 

Directions
  1. Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
  2. Line 9x5 inch loaf pan with parchment paper.
  3. Place bananas, eggs, pumpkin, honey, and vanilla in blender and mix until smooth.
  4. In a large bowl, combine oat flour, tapioca flour, baking soda, salt, and spices.
  5. Pour wet ingredients into dry and stir to combine.
  6. Pour batter into loaf pan.
  7. Bake for 60 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.

Grain-Free Soft Pretzels

Grain-Free Soft Pretzels

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
330
Servings
6
Ingredients

Pretzels:
½ c. water
½ c. coconut oil
½ tsp. pink salt 
2 T. apple cider vinegar
½ c. almond meal
½ tsp. baking soda
½ tsp. baking powder
1 c. coconut flour
3 eggs
Glaze:
1 ½ tsp. melted coconut oil (or butter)
pink salt (or cinnamon/stevia or nutritional yeast), to taste

Directions
  1. Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
  2. In small saucepan, melt coconut oil over medium heat.
  3. Add water, salt, and vinegar and bring to a boil.
  4. Remove pan from heat.
  5. Add almond flour and stir for 2 minutes until wet paste is formed.
  6. Add baking soda and powder and stir while mixture foams - roughly 3 seconds.
  7. Mix in coconut flour and eggs until dough forms.
  8. Place dough on a piece of parchment paper and knead for 30 seconds to 1 minute.
  9. Separate into 6 equal sized dough balls.
  10. Roll each dough ball into 6 inch log, about ½ inch wide.
  11. Twist into pretzel shape and place on parchment lined baking sheet or pretzel pan.
  12. Bake for 25 - 30 minutes.
  13. Remove pretzels from oven. 
  14. Brush each pretzel with 1/4 teaspoon melted coconut oil (or butter).
  15. Sprinkle with pink salt (or cinnamon/stevia or nutritional yeast).

Sausage Apple Cornbread Muffins

Sausage Apple Cornbread Muffins

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
100
Servings
24
Ingredients

1 lb. ground chicken
2 T. red wine
1 tsp. minced garlic
2 tsp. fennel seeds
1 tsp. pepper
2 tsp. pink salt (divided)
½ tsp. oregano
1/16 tsp. allspice
1 lb. diced apples
1 c. coconut flour
1/2 tsp. powdered stevia or 12 drops liquid stevia
3 1/2 tsp. baking powder
5 eggs
1/2 c. unsweetened almond milk
1/3 c. coconut oil, melted

Directions
  1. Preheat oven to 400 degrees.
  2. Place liners in 24 muffin tins.
  3. Combine chicken, wine, 1 teaspoon pink salt, garlic, fennel seeds, pepper, oregano, and allspice in bowl with hands.
  4. Transfer mixture to skillet oven med-high heat and cook until beginning to brown.
  5. Drain fat from skillet. 
  6. Transfer sausage to large bowl along with diced apples.
  7. In separate bowl, combine coconut flour, stevia, and baking powder. 
  8. Whisk together eggs, almond milk, and coconut oil.
  9. Pour liquid into coconut flour mixture and stir until dough comes together.
  10. Add dough to apple/sausage bowl and stir until mixed.
  11. Portion heaping 1/4 c. into each muffin tin, packing down with back of spoon.
  12. Bake for 15-20 minutes, until tops start to brown.

Orange Cranberry Sauce

Orange Cranberry Sauce

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
20
Servings
14 (2T per serving)
Ingredients

12 oz. fresh cranberries (~3 c.)
¼ c. unsweetened applesauce
1 orange, cubed
1 cinnamon stick
4 dropperfuls SweetLeaf valencia orange stevia
zest of 1 orange

Directions
  1. Heat applesauce and stevia in saucepan over medium heat.
  2. Stir in cranberries, oranges, orange zest, and cinnamon stick.
  3. When cranberries start to pop, reduce to simmer.
  4. Cover and cook 15-20 minutes.
  5. Remove cinnamon stick.
  6. Stir sauce until well mixed together.
  7. Add additional stevia if sauce is too tart.
  8. Transfer to glass jar then refrigerate.

Strawberry Walnut Cheesecake Bites (Bars)

Strawberry Walnut Cheesecake Bites (Bars)

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
135
Servings
24
Ingredients

Crust:
2 c. ground walnuts
4 T. coconut oil
4-6 packets SweetLeaf stevia

Filling:
8 oz. cream cheese, room temp
1/4 c. coconut oil
1/2 c. strawberries
1 tsp. vanilla extract
4 dropperfuls SweetLeaf vanilla creme stevia

 

Directions
  1. Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
  2. Mix walnuts, butter, and powdered stevia together well.
  3. Press crust mixture into 24 silicone or paper lined muffin tins.
  4. Bake for 15 minutes.
  5. Remove from oven and chill in refrigerator.
  6. Mix cream cheese and coconut oil together until smooth.
  7. Blend strawberries, vanilla, and vanilla stevia together.
  8. Stir into cream cheese mixture.
  9. Scoop filling mixture evenly into each crust.
  10. Freeze.

Mini Pizzas

Mini Pizzas

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
145
Servings
2
Ingredients

1 egg
1 tsp. coconut flour
1/2 tsp. baking powder
1 T. coconut oil, melted
1/4 tsp. Italian seasoning
1 T. tomato sauce
1 mozzarella string cheese
additional Italian seasoning, to taste

Directions
  1. Mix coconut flour, egg, and baking powder together in microwavable container.
  2. Stir in coconut oil (or butter) and 1/4 teaspoon italian seasoning until well combined.
  3. Microwave for 90 seconds.
  4. Cool for a minute.
  5. Slice in half.
  6. Lightly toast in toaster oven or lightly brown each side in skillet over med-high heat.
  7. Spread 1/2 tablespoon tomato sauce on each slice of bread.
  8. Cut cheese into small pieces and sprinkle on top of sauce.
  9. Return pizzas to toaster oven for a few minutes, until cheese is melted.
  10. Sprinkle with additional italian seasoning. 

Healthy Elvis Sandwich

Healthy Elvis Sandwich

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
295
Servings
2
Ingredients

1 egg 
1/2 c. egg whites
1 T. coconut flour
1/4 c. golden flax meal
1/2 tsp. baking powder
stevia, to taste
1 banana
2 T. almond butter
cinnamon, to taste

Directions
  1. Heat skillet over medium heat and grease lightly.
  2. Mix egg, egg whites, flax meal, coconut flour, baking powder, and stevia until well combined.
  3. Pour half of batter into skillet and cook until starting to bubble. 
  4. Flip pancake and cook other side until golden (will take awhile b/c pancake will be quite thick).
  5. Repeat with second half of batter.
  6. Allow pancakes to cool.
  7. Slice each pancake with sharp knife into 2 thin circles (for top and bottom of sandwich).
  8. Toast pancake slices, if desired. 
  9. Slice banana into thin rounds.
  10. Spread 1/2 tablespoon almond butter on each of the 4 pancake circles.
  11. Place banana slices on 2 pancake circles.
  12. Sprinkle with cinnamon.
  13. Top with remaining pancake circles.
  14. Cut an X to make each sandwich into 4 equal triangles.

Servings
12
Ingredients

Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
435
Servings
1
Ingredients

1 c grape tomatoes
1/2 red bell pepper,chopped
1 green pepper, chopped
1/2 c onion, chopped 
2 c romaine lettuce
4 oz lean ground beef
2 T nutritional yeast
1/4 c plain greek yogurt
1/4 c + 2 T salsa
1-2 t Taco Seasoning

Directions
  1. Cook ground beef in skillet over med-high heat until beginning to brown
  2. Add in onion, peppers, and taco seasoning
  3. Cover and cook until veggies begin to soften
  4. Stir in 1/4 c salsa and tomatoes, cover, and cook another couple minutes
  5. Transfer mixture to large bowl with lettuce and toss 
  6. Sprinkle with nutritional yeast
  7. Top with yogurt and remaining salsa

Walnut Surprise Muffins

Walnut Surprise Muffins

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
165
Servings
12
Ingredients

2 t vanilla extract
1 t pink salt
3/4 t baking soda
1/4 c coconut oil, melted
3/4 c coconut flour
4 bananas
7 eggs
12 walnut halves
1 T cinnamon

Directions
  1. Preheat oven to 350 degrees
  2. Place liners in 12 muffin tins
  3. Combine bananas, coconut oil, vanilla, and eggs in food processor
  4. Mix in coconut flour, cinnamon, salt, and baking soda
  5. Allow to sit for 3-4 minutes for batter to thicken
  6. Pour batter into muffin tins equally
  7. Press 1 walnut half inside center of each muffin
  8. Bake 25-30 minutes, until toothpock inserted in center comes out clean

Fudgy Chocolate Protein Bars

Fudgy Chocolate Protein Bars

Dietary
Low Carb
Calories per serving
165 (or 180 w/ maple syrup)
Servings
8
Ingredients

1/2 c oats
1 (15 oz) can black beans, drained and rinsed
1/8 t pink salt
1/2 c whey protein powder (or other protein powder of choice)
3 T unsweetened cocoa powder
1/3 c IMO prebiotic fiber (or maple syrup)
30 drops stevia
3 1/2 T coconut oil, melted
1 T vanilla extract
1/2 t baking powder
1/3 c add-ins* (chocolate chips, raisins, nuts, etc), optional

Directions
  1. Preheat oven to 350 degrees
  2. Line 8x8 inch pan with foil and grease lightly
  3. Place oats in food processor and pulse until flour consistency is reached
  4. Add all remaining ingredients to food processor (except for optional add-ins) and process until smooth
  5. Stir in add-ins*, if desired (*Will need to calculate in additional calories)
  6. Bake for 20 minutes (Will look slightly underdone when taken out of oven)
  7. Let cool a few minutes then press down with pancake spatula to make more compact
  8. Refrigerate overnight
  9. Cut into 8 bars
  10. Store leftovers in refrigerator

90 Second Coconut Bread

90 Second Coconut Bread

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
200 (or 180 w/ butter)
Servings
1
Ingredients

1 egg
1 t coconut flour
1/2 t baking powder
1 T coconut oil (or butter), melted
spices and stevia, if desired

Directions
  1. Mix coconut flour, egg, and baking powder together in microwavable container
  2. Stir in coconut oil (or butter) and spices, if desired, until well combined
  3. Microwave for 90 seconds
  4. Cool for a minute
  5. Slice in half
  6. Toast in toaster or lightly brown each side in skillet over med-high heat 

Cauliflower Clam Chowder

Cauliflower Clam Chowder

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
230
Servings
4
Ingredients

1 c onion, chopped
1 carrot, chopped
1 rib celery, chopped
2 cloves garlic, minced
1 T coconut oil
1 (10 oz) can clams, not drained
1 c water + 1/2 t Simple Girl Bouillon Base (or 1 c chicken broth)
1 c full-fat canned coconut milk
3 c cauliflower, cut into small florets
1/4-1/2 t xanthan gum
pink salt and pepper, to taste

Directions
  1. Heat coconut oil in large pot
  2. ​Saute onions, celery, and carrots until onions are translucent and tender
  3. Add garlic and cook for another minute
  4. Add clams (with liquid from can), clam juice, and coconut milk
  5. Add cauliflower florets
  6. Place lid on pot and simmer 10-15 minutes, until cauliflower is tender
  7. Remove pot from heat
  8. Sprinkle 1/4 t xanthan gum over soup
  9. Whisk and allow to thicken for 1 minute
  10. Add additional xanthan gum, if needed
  11. Season with pink salt and pepper

Cherry Cola Chocolate Bark

Cherry Cola Chocolate Bark

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
145
Servings
1
Ingredients

1 T coconut oil
2 T frozen cherries
1/2 T unsweetened cocoa/cacao powder
1-2 dropperfuls SweetLeaf cola stevia

Directions
  1. Chop frozen cherries and place in thin layer on parchment-lined baking sheet or in tupperware
  2. Melt coconut oil
  3. Stir in cocoa powder and stevia
  4. Pour coconut oil mixture over cherry pieces, coating evenly
  5. Place in freezer until hardened
  6. Break into pieces

Focaccia French Toast

Focaccia French Toast

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
395
Servings
2
Ingredients

4 slices Focaccia Flax Bread
1 egg
1/2 t cinnamon
1 t vanilla extract
1/4 c unsweetened almond milk
SweetLeaf english toffee stevia, to taste
Powdered stevia, if desired

Directions
  1. Heat and lightly grease skillet over medium heat 
  2. Stir together egg, cinnamon, and vanilla extract in shallow bowl
  3. Whisk in almond milk
  4. Soak slice of bread in mixture
  5. Transfer to skillet and lightly brown on each side
  6. Repeat with remaining slices of bread
  7. Place a few drops of english toffee stevia on each slice and sprinkle with a little powdered stevia

Apple BBQ Burger

Apple BBQ Burger

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
215
Servings
4
Ingredients

1 lb 90% lean ground beef
1/2 t rubbed sage
1/2 t fennel seeds
1/4 t pepper
1/4 t pink salt
1/2 t parsley flakes
1/8 t nutmeg
2 pinches cayenne pepper
2 T Simple Girl Carolina Style BBQ Sauce
1 c diced apple

Directions
  1. Preheat oven to 325 degrees
  2. Combine spices and diced apple together in mixing bowl
  3. Add meat to bowl and combine with hands until well mixed
  4. Add BBQ sauce and continue to mix
  5. Form mixture into 4 equal sized patties
  6. Place on baking sheet
  7. Bake for 15 to 20 minutes or until done in center of patty
  8. Remove from oven and brush tops of patties with additional BBQ sauce, if desired

Cherry Spiced Chicken

Cherry Spiced Chicken

Dietary
Oil Free
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
200
Servings
1
Ingredients

3.5 oz chicken 
1/2 c cherries
1 t Cinnamon Spice Rub
1 T water

Directions
  1. Preheat oven to 450 degrees
  2. Line baking sheet with parchment paper
  3. Place chicken on baking sheet and sprinkle lightly with 1/2 t Cinnamon Spice Rub
  4. Bake chicken for 20 minutes then slice and sit on plate
  5. Heat water in small skillet over medium heat
  6. Add cherries and remaining spice rub
  7. Cook a few minutes until cherries have softened
  8. Pour cherries and sauce over sliced chicken

Frozen Apple Pie Bites

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
160
Servings
6
Ingredients

5 T coconut oil
1 1/2 t pumpkin pie spice
1 packet SweetLeaf stevia
 

Directions
  1. Heat diced apple in microwave for 1 minute then transfer to food processor
  2. Add coconut oil, cream cheese, pie spice, and stevia
  3. Process until well combined
  4. Spoon 2 tablespoons of mixture 6 molds (or ice cube tray)
  5. Place in freezer until hardened

Fiesta Ranch Skillet

Fiesta Ranch Skillet

Dietary
Oil Free
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
295
Servings
1
Ingredients

3.5 oz lean ground beef
4 oz green pepper
4 oz red pepper
4 oz tomato

2 T tomato paste

Directions
  1. Brown ground beef in skillet over med-high heat

French Onion Soup Poppers

French Onion Soup Poppers

Dietary
Oil Free
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
260
Servings
1
Ingredients

3.5 oz lean ground beef
6 oz onion, chopped
1/4 t onion powder
1/4 t garlic powder
1/16 t celery seed
1/16 t pepper
1/4 t parsley 
1/4 t pink salt 
1/4 t turmeric (optional)

Directions
  1. Preheat oven to 400 degrees
  2. Line baking sheet with parchment paper
  3. Cook onions in small amount of water in skillet until translucent
  4. Drain liquid and stir in spices
  5. Transfer onions to bowl with beef and combine all ingredients together with hands
  6. Scoop mixture out by the spoonful into 6 mounds onto lined pan and flatten into nugget shape
  7. Bake 20-25 minutes, or until cooked through

Beefy Mushroom Poppers

Beefy Mushroom Poppers

Dietary
Oil Free
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
235
Servings
1
Ingredients

8 oz mushrooms
1/2 t onion powder
1 t lemon juice
1 t liquid aminos
1/2 t fennel seeds
1/4 t ginger
1/4 t garlic powder
1/8 t pepper
1/4 t curry powder
3.5 oz 90% lean ground beef

Directions
  1. Preheat oven to 400 degrees
  2. Line baking sheet with parchment paper

  5. Add beef to bowl and combine all ingredients together with hands

Honey Mustard Chicken Stuffed Mushrooms

Honey Mustard Chicken Stuffed Mushrooms

Dietary
Oil Free
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
235
Servings
1
Ingredients

3.5 oz chicken
8 oz mushrooms
1/2 t onion powder
2 T yellow mustard
1 dropperful stevia
1/2 t italian seasoning
1/2 t minced onion flakes

Directions
  1. Preheat oven to 400 degrees
  2. Line baking sheet with parchment paper
  3. Remove stems from mushrooms and pulse in food processor
  4. Place mushroom caps on baking sheet
  5. Cook chicken then add to food processor
  6. Processs with onion powder, mustard, stevia, italian seasoning, and onion flakes
  7. Fill mushroom caps with chicken mixture
  8. Bake 10-12 minutes or until starting to look a little juicy

Chinese Chicken and Broccoli

Chinese Chicken and Broccoli

Dietary
Oil Free
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
245
Servings
1
Ingredients

8 oz broccoli
4 oz ground chicken
1 T liquid aminos
1/2 T minced garlic
½ t minced onion flakes
¼ c water
1 T stone ground dijon mustard

Directions
  1. Cook chicken in skillet over med-high heat with liquid aminos, onion flakes, and garlic
  2. Add water and broccoli to skillet
  3. Reduce heat to low, cover, and cook for 5 minutes
  4. Remove lid and stir in mustard
  5. Cook a few more minutes, until broccoli is desired tenderness
  6. Top with additional liquid aminos, if desired

Calories per serving

Servings
18
Ingredients

Directions

  6. Bake 12-15 minutes

Firecracker Shrimp II

Firecracker Shrimp II

Dietary
Oil Free
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
170
Servings
1
Ingredients

5 oz shrimp
1-2 T Canadian style steak seasoning
1-2 t hot sauce

Directions
  1. Preheat oven to 400 degrees
  2. Line baking sheet with parchment paper
  3. Peel and remove tails from shrimp
  4. Place shrimp in baggie or container with steak seasoning and toss until coated
  5. Place shrimp onto baking sheet
  6. Drizzle with hot sauce
  7. Bake 6-8 minutes
  8. Remove from oven and drizzle with additional hot sauce, if desired

Tomato Salad Sandwich

Tomato Salad Sandwich

Dietary
Oil Free
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
245
Servings
1
Ingredients

8 oz riced cauliflower
1/2 c egg whites
1 egg
1 t basil
1/4 t garlic powder
1/8 t pink salt
4 oz tomato
2 T tomato paste
1 T stone ground dijon
1/4 t italian seasoning

Directions
  1. Preheat oven to 350 degrees
  2. Whisk together egg and egg whites
  3. Stir in cauliflower, garlic powder, basil, and pink salt
  4. Transfer to small parchment lined baking sheet
  5. Bake 15 minutes
  6. Remove from oven and allow to cool
  7. Cut around edges to make a rectangle and cut into 2 pieces (Reserve edge trimmings for tomato salad)
  8. Combine tomato paste, dijon mustard, and italian seasoning in small bowl
  9. Chop tomato into small pieces and add to bowl along with chopped edge trimmings 
  10. Spread tomato salad onto one slice of bread and top with remaining slice then cut in half

Tuna Zoodle Casserole

Tuna Zoodle Casserole

Dietary
Oil Free
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
215
Servings
1
Ingredients

12 oz zucchini
1 can albacore white tuna
1 c water
1/8 t celery seed
1/2 t onion powder
1/4 t garlic powder
1 T dijon mustard
1/4 t xanthan gum
1/4 t smoked paprika
pink salt and pepper, to taste

Directions
  1. Preheat oven to 350 degrees
  2. Spiralize or slice zucchini into strips the size of noodles
  3. Place 8 oz zucchini and tuna into pyrex baking dish and mix until combined
  4. Steam remaining 4 oz zucchini until soft
  5. Transfer steamed zucchini to blender with water, mustard, spices, and xanthan gum
  6. Blend until sauce-like consistency is reached
  7. Pour sauce into bowl and stir well
  8. Bake for 25 minutes

Lemon Chicken Asparagus Soup

Dietary
Oil Free
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
200
Servings
1
Ingredients

Creamy Zucchini Zoodle Soup

Creamy Zucchini Zoodle Soup

Dietary
Oil Free
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
55
Servings
1
Ingredients

8 oz zucchini
1 c water
1/8 t celery seed
1/2 t onion powder
1/4 t garlic powder
1 T dijon mustard
1/4 t xanthan gum
1/4 t smoked paprika
pink salt and pepper, to taste

Directions
  1. Cut zucchini into thin strips or spiralize
  2. Steam zucchini until softened
  3. Set aside 2 oz of zucchini and place the other 6 oz in blender

Black Bean Brownies

Black Bean Brownies

Dietary
Low Carb
Calories per serving
105 (125 w/ honey)
Servings
12
Ingredients

Sweet 'n Spicy Pumpkin Cookies

Sweet 'n Spicy Pumpkin Cookies

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
25
Servings
12
Ingredients

3/4 c pumpkin
1 egg
2 droppers Sweet Leaf English Toffee stevia
1/2 t allspice
1/4 t pepper
1/4 t thyme
1 t baking powder
2 T coconut flour
1 T cashews
1 T almonds  
pink salt 

Directions
  1. Preheat oven to 350 degrees
  2. Line baking sheet with parchment paper or silicone baking mat
  3. Combine pumpkin, egg, stevia, allspice, pepper, thyme, and baking powder together in bowl with whisk or in food processor
  4. Stir in coconut flour and allow to thicken for a couple minutes
  5. Fold in cashews and almonds
  6. Spoon 12 mounds (about 1 heaping tablespoon each) onto baking sheet
  7. Press each mound into a flat circle
  8. Sprinkle lightly with pink salt
  9. Bake for 15 minutes or until starting to brown slightly
  10. Remove from oven and allow to cool
  11. Store in paper bag

Chewy Chocolate Oatmeal Bars

Chewy Chocolate Oatmeal Bars

Dietary
Low Carb
Calories per serving
145
Servings
12
Ingredients

1/4 c almond butter (or other nut/seed butter of choice)
1/2 c dates
3/4 c unsweetened almond milk
1 t vanilla
1/2 c egg white protein powder (or other protein powder of choice)
1/4 c unsweetened cocoa powder
1/8 t pink salt
1 3/4 c oats
1/3 c Lily's chocolate chips (or cacao nibs or coconut oil chocolate chips)

Directions
  1. Preheat oven to 350 degree
  2. Line 8x8 baking dish with parchment paper or foil
  3. Combine almond butter, dates, almond milk, and vanilla in food processor or blender until smooth and well-combined
  4. Mix in protein powder, cocoa powder, and pink salt until fully incorporated.
  5. Add oats and pulse until just combined
  6. Stir in chocolate chips
  7. Spoon into baking dish and spread the mixture evenly with hands or spatula
  8. Bake 15 minutes, until edges and top have set
  9. Remove from oven and allow to cool
  10. Cut into 12 bars

Chickizza

Chickizza

Dietary
Oil Free
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
240
Servings
4
Ingredients

1 lb ground chicken
1 (8 oz) can tomato sauce
1 T Flavor God Pizza Seasoning (or other pizza seasoning of choice)
2 c sliced mushrooms
7 drops plain stevia
1/2 t onion powder
1 T minced onion

Directions
  1. Add pizza seasoning and stevia to tomato sauce and refrigerate for a few hours
  2. Preheat oven to broil
  3. Press and spread chicken evenly on foil-lined baking sheet

Oat-Free Granola Bars

Oat-Free Granola Bars

Dietary
Low Carb
Calories per serving
250
Servings
12
Ingredients

1 c Trader Joe's Super Seed & Ancient Grain Blend (or 1/4 c each buckwheat groats, chia seeds, flax seeds, quinoa)
1/2 c peanuts (or other nut of choice)
1/2 c shredded unsweetened coconut
3/4 c almond flour
1 t vanilla
1/4 c honey
1/4 c coconut oil
2 T unsweetened cocoa powder
1/2 c egg white protein powder (or other protein powder of choice)
1 T water

Directions
  1. Preheat oven to 350 degrees 
  2. Grease 8x12 baking pan 
  3. Grind super seeds/ancient grains, peanuts, and coconut in food processor until coarse flour consistency is reached
  4. Add almond meal, protein powder, cocoa powder, vanilla, honey, and coconut oil and process until well mixed
  5. Add water (more or less, as needed)
  6. Transfer mixture into pan and press down to spread until it is even and spreads to all corners of baking pan
  7. Bake for about 15-20 minutes
  8. Remove from oven and cut into 12 bars
  9. Let cool completely before removing from pan 

Apple Pie Protein Cookies

Apple Pie Protein Cookies

Dietary
Low Carb
Calories per serving
125
Servings
12
Ingredients

20 pitted dates
1/4 c cashews
1/4 c almonds
1 T prebiotic fiber (FiberYum IMO syrup)
1/4 c water
1 bag (34 g) freeze dried apples
1/2 t cinnamon
1 c egg white protein powder (or other protein powder of choice)
1/4 c almond flour +1/2 t cinnamon (combined in small bowl)

Directions
  1. Preheat oven to 350 degrees
  2. Combine dates, cashews, almonds in food processor until well broken down
  3. Add in apples, cinnamon, prebiotic fiber, and protein powder
  4. Slowly add in water, up to 1/4 c, until mixture comes together
  5. Divide mixture into 12 balls
  6. Roll each ball in cinnamon almond flour
  7. Place onto parchment lined baking sheet and flatten into circle about 1/4 inch thick
  8. Bake for 10 minutes then flip cookies and bake 5 more minutes

Dietary

  2. Melt coconut oil and almond butter together 
  3. Stir in english toffee stevia
  4. Dip each bite of apple into mixture then place on parchment lined baking sheet
  5. Place baking sheet into freezer until coating hardens on apples
  6. Remove baking sheet from freezer and dip apples again (repeat until all mixture is used)
  7. Store in fridge

Cheeseless Queso

Cheeseless Queso

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
50
Servings
12 (1/3 c per serving)
Ingredients

1 T coconut oil, melted
pink salt
1 medium eggplant
2 carrots
3 c unsweetened almond milk
1/3 c nutritional yeast
1/2 t minced garlic 
2 t cumin
2 t chili powder
1/2 t xanthan gum, optional (to thicken sauce)
1 c chunky salsa, drained
smoked paprika and/or hot sauce, optional

Directions
  1. Slice eggplant in 1/4 inch rounds
  2. Sprinkle eggplant rounds lightly with salt and place in colander for 10-15 minutes
  3. Peel carrots and cut into 1/2 inch rounds
  4. Bring medium saucepan of water to boil and add carrots
  5. Preheat oven to Broil and place oven rack on top level
  6. Rinse eggplant with cool water and pat dry 
  7. Arrange eggplant rounds on foil-lined, lightly greased baking sheet
  8. Brush both sides of eggplant rounds lightly with coconut oil and sprinkle with pink salt
  9. Broil on 2 1/2 minutes, flip rounds, broil another 2 1/2 minutes
  10. Remove boiled carrots from heat, drain, rinse with cool water, then set aside
  11. Remove eggplant from oven and wrap loosely in foil to steam for 5 minutes
  12. Unwrap foil and peel skin off rounds 
  13. Blend eggplant (should be about 2 cups), carrots, almond milk, nutritional yeast, garlic, cumin, chili powder and xanthan gum in blender until smooth and creamy
  14. Taste and adjust seasonings, xanthan gum, and almond milk, as needed
  15. Transfer to medium saucepan and warm over medium heat 5 minutes or until slightly thick and bubbly 
  16. Remove from heat and stir in drained salsa
  17. Top with smoked paprika and/or hot sauce, if desired
