Balsamic Tomato Mussels

Balsamic Tomato Mussels

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
210
Servings
2
Ingredients

8 oz pack frozen, cooked mussels
1 pint grape tomatoes, halved
1 T coconut oil
2 t minced garlic
1/2 small onion, chopped
1 T balsamic vinegar
1 T tomato paste
1 (5 oz) bag baby spinach
 

Directions
  1. Melt coconut oil in skillet over med-high heat
  2. Saute garlic and onion until transleucent
  3. Stir in tomatoes, balsamic vinegar, and mussels
  4. Place lid on skillet and cook, stirring occasionally, until mussels are heated through (about 8-10 minutes)
  5. Remove from heat and stir in tomato paste and basil
  6. Stir in spinach, cover, return to burner, and cook, stirring occasionally, until spinach is wilted

Roasted Garlic & Zucchini Alfredo

Roasted Garlic & Zucchini Alfredo

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
525
Servings
4
Ingredients

2 heads garlic
6 zucchini, spiralized or sliced into thin strips
2 onions, sliced thin
2 t olive oil (divided)
4 T butter
1/4 c coconut cream or heavy cream
8 oz cream cheese
4 oz shredded parmigiano 

Directions
  1. Preheat oven to 400 degrees
  2. Peel loose paper off garlic and leave the head itself intact with all cloves connected
  3. Trim 1/4 inch off top of head of garlic to expose cloves
  4. Drizzle 1 teaspoon olive oil over exposed surface of garlic, so it sinks down into the cloves
  5. Wrap in foil and bake for 40 minutes
  6. In large skillet over medium heat, toss roasted garlic, onion, zucchini in 1 teaspoon olive oil
  7. Remove from pan
  8. Reduce heat, add butter, cream cheese, parmigiano, cream and incorporate, simmering (don't boil or it will separate)
  9. Add veggies back, toss and serve

Creamy Faux Mashed Potatoes

Creamy Faux Mashed Potatoes

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
50
Servings
4
Ingredients

1 head cauliflower
1/4 c canned coconut cream 
pink salt and pepper to taste

Directions
  1. Wash cauliflower and remove leaves
  2. Cut in half then cut out core at an angle
  3. Coarsley chop, removing any additional core
  4. Add 1 cup water and trivet to pot to Instant Pot (or use remaining liquid from Garlic Herb Instant Pot Roast)*
  5. Place steamer basket on top of trivet and add chopped cauliflower
  6. Secure lid and choose "Manual" on high for 5 minutes
  7. Use 'quick release' method to release steam before removing lid
  8. Combine cauliflower, coconut cream, pink salt, and pepper in food processor or with potato masher and blend to desired smoothness
    *Alternatively, can steam cauliflower in saucepan or in microwave, if desired

Garlic Herb Instant Pot Roast

Garlic Herb Instant Pot Roast

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
450
Servings
4
Ingredients

2 lbs sirloin steak (or other beef of choice)
1/2 t pink salt
1/2 t pepper 
1/2 t garlic powder
1 1/2 t Italian Seasoning 
1 T coconut oil 
1 (16 oz bag) frozen peppers & onions
1/2 c water
1/8 c red wine
6 medium carrots, peeled and chopped into 1 inch pieces
8 oz mushrooms, quartered

Directions
  1. Cut beef into 2-inch or smaller cubes
  2. Place on plate and sprinkle evenly with spices then set aside
  3. Turn Instant Pot on "Saute" setting and melt coconut oil in pot
  4. Add peppers and onions and saute for 5 minutes until tender 
  5. Deglaze the pan with the red wine
  6. Add roast pieces in a single layer on top of the onions.
  7. Pour the broth over the roast.
  8. Put lid on Instant pot, lock and seal
  9. Press cancel or unplug Instant Pot to stop the Saute setting and then press "Manual" button and set time to 40 minutes
  10. When finished, push "cancel" button and turn lock to "venting" until the pressure is released
  11. When pressure releases, remove lid and quickly add carrots and mushrooms
  12. Replace lid, press "Manual" button and set time to 10 minutes
  13. When finished, press "cancel" and turn lock to "venting" until pressure is released
  14. Let cool slightly and serve (Excellent with Creamy Faux Mashed Potatoes)

Bison Vegetable Medley

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
505
Servings
1
Ingredients

5 oz ground bison
1 (12 oz) bag frozen broccoli, cauliflower, carrot mix
2 T dijon mustard
1 T Braggs nutritional yeast
1 t Simple Girl BBQ Seasoning
pink salt, to taste

Directions
  1. Form bison meat into burger patty and cook until done
  2. Steam veggies until tender
  3. Stir mustard, nutritional yeast, BBQ seasoning, and pink salt into veggies
  4. Cut burger into bite sized pieces and stir into veggies

Almond Joy Mousse

Almond Joy Mousse

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
280
Servings
1
Ingredients

1/2 c cottage cheese
2 T unsweetened shredded coconut, divided
2 T chopped almonds, divided
1-2 dropperfuls SweetLeaf chocolate stevia
2 t unsweetened cocoa/cacao powder

Directions
  1. Place cottage cheese, cocoa/cacao powder, and stevia in mini chopper or food processor
  2. Process until curds have disappeared and cottage cheese is well whipped
  3. Stir in 1 T almonds and 1 T coconut
  4. Transfer to bowl
  5. Top with remaining almond and coconut

Whey Protein Mug Cake

Whey Protein Mug Cake

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
135
Servings
1
Ingredients

1 scoop whey protein powder of choice
1/4 c unsweetened almond or coconut milk
1/2 t baking powder
water, as needed 

Directions
  1. Stir all ingredients together until consistency is like pancake batter 
  2. Microwave 30-60 seconds, until cake poofs up 
  3. Sprinkle with toppings, if desired
     

Creamy BBQ Cauli-Rice Bowl

Creamy BBQ Cauli-Rice Bowl

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
495
Servings
2
Ingredients

2 eggs
1 T coconut oil
1 c steamed broccoli florets 
12.5 oz (1 can) Premium Chunk White Chicken in water
2 small tomatoes, chopped
2 t Simple Girl BBQ Seasoning
2 T coconut cream (canned)
6 c riced cauliflower
1 T butter
1/2 c water

Directions
  1. Steam cauliflower in water over med-high heat
  2. Drain then return saucepan to stovetop
  3. Stir in butter, broccoli, chicken, tomatoes, BBQ seasoning, and coconut cream then cover with lid
  4. In small skillet, melt coconut oil
  5. Scramble eggs and cook in skillet
  6. Stir eggs into saucepan

Thai Iced Tea

Thai Iced Tea

Dietary
Low Carb
Calories per serving
120
Servings
8
Ingredients

2 quarts water
6-8 black tea bags
4 star anise
6 whole cloves
10 oz coconut cream (canned)
12 dates
2-3 dropperfuls SweetLeaf english toffee stevia
4-5 dropperfuls SweetLeav vanilla creme stevia
ice

Directions
  1. Boil water in medium saucepan
  2. Add teabags, star anise, clove and dates
  3. Remove saucepan from heat and steep 10-15 minutes
  4. Remove teabags, star anise, and cloves with large spoon or strainer
  5. Stir in coconut cream and stevia
  6. Transfer to blender and pulse a few times
  7. Pour into mason jars
  8. Cool completely 
  9. Serve over ice or store in refrigerator up to 1 week

Cabbage Roll Soup

Low Carb

190
Servings
6
Ingredients

Directions

  2. Stir in cabbage until well combined
  3. Add tomato sauce, tomatoes, cauliflower, spices, and water
  4. Cook on high for 3-4 hours (or low 6-8 hours)

Zucchini Coconut Flour Pizza Crust

Zucchini Coconut Flour Pizza Crust

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
215
Servings
1 crust
Ingredients

1 medium zucchini, finely shredded (about 2 cups)
1 egg
1/3 c egg whites
2 T coconut flour
1/2 t baking powder
1/2-1 t italian seasoning
1/8 t garlic powder
1/8 t pink salt
 

Directions
  1. Preheat oven to 450 degrees
  2. Line baking sheet or pizza pan/stone with parchment paper
  3. Steam zucchini on stovetop for a 2-3 minutes or microwave for 1 minute
  4. Wring as much moisture as possible out of zucchini with tea towel
  5. In medium bowl, whisk together egg, egg whites, baking powder, and spices
  6. Stir in zucchini and coconut flour
  7. Spoon mixture onto baking sheet and flatten evenly into circle or rectangle about 1/4 inch thick
  8. Bake about 10-12 minutes, until starting to brown
  9. Remove from oven to add sauce, cheese, and desired toppings then baking another few minutes until cheese is melted

Cappuccino Chia Pudding

Cappuccino Chia Pudding

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
235
Servings
1
Ingredients

1/4 c chia seeds
3/4 c unsweetened almond milk
1 t instant coffee
1 dropperful SweetLeaf stevia (or hazelnut/english toffee/vanilla creme/chocolate)

Directions
  1. Combine all ingredients in a mason jar or other container with lid
  2. Stir or shake well until mixed together
  3. Place lid on jar
  4. Refrigerate for 6 or more hours
  5. Stir and add toppings, if desired (nuts, fruits, unsweetened coconut, cacao nibs, etc)
  6. May be stored in fridge for up to 5 days

Salted Toffee Apples

Salted Toffee Apples

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
215
Servings
1
Ingredients

1 apple, sliced thin
2 T water
1 T coconut oil
1/2 t cinnamon
1 dropperful SweetLeaf english toffee stevia
pink salt
 

Directions
  1. Melt coconut oil in small skillet over med-high heat
  2. Stir in apple and water
  3. Cover and allow to cook until apple are tender
  4. Stir in stevia and cinnamon
  5. Continue cooking and allow liquid to reduce to desired sauce consistency (can add more water for a thinner sauce)
  6. Spoon apples onto plate
  7. Drizzle remaining sauce onto apples
  8. Sprinkle with pink salt

Cauliflower Salad

Cauliflower Salad

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
155
Servings
4
Ingredients

1 medium head cauliflower, cut into bite sized pieces
6 hard boiled eggs
1/3 c plain Greek yogurt
3 T dijon mustard
1/4 c finely chopped/diced cucumber
1 T apple cider vinegar
2 T chopped onion
pink salt and pepper, to taste
2 green onions, chopped
1 t dill
 

Directions
  1. Steam cauliflower until tender
  2. Separate egg yolks from whites and place in bowl then mash
  3. Cut egg whites into bite sized pieces then stir into yolks
  4. Stir in yogurt, mustard, acv, onion, cucumber, pink salt, pepper, and dill
  5. Scoop mixture into cauliflower and stir until well coated
  6. Garnish with green onions

Chicken & Broccoli with Cabbage

Chicken & Broccoli with Cabbage

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
600
Servings
1
Ingredients

1 T coconut oil
6 oz chicken breast, cut into strips
1/2 small head cabbage, sliced thin
1 c broccoli
1/4 c coconut aminos
1 t fresh ginger, grated
2 cloves garlic, minced
1 t Red Boat fish sauce
4 drops stevia
1/4 t chili flakes, optional
1/2 t sesame seeds

Directions
  1. In small bowl, combine coconut aminos, fish sauce, and stevia
  2. Heat oil in large skillet or wok over med-high heat
  3. Add chicken and cook until cooked through
  4. Remove chicken from pan and set aside on paper towel lined plate
  5. Add ginger to skillet and cook about 20 seconds
  6. Add broccoli and cabbage and stir fry 3-5 minutes, until slightly wilted
  7. Add garlic and chili flakes, if desired, and cook another minute
  8. Add chicken back to skillet with veggies
  9. Stir liquid ingredients into skillet
  10. Turn heat to high and allow liquid to reduce for a couple minutes 
  11. Transfer to plate
  12. Garnish with sesame seeds

IMO Pancake Syrup

IMO Pancake Syrup

Dietary
Low Carb
Calories per serving
90
Servings
1
Ingredients

1 T FiberYum IMO Syrup
1/2 T coconut oil
1/4 t cinnamon (more or less, to taste)
water, if needed to thin to desired consistency

Directions
  1. Combine syrup and coconut oil in small saucepan over med heat
  2. Stir in cinnamon
  3. If too thick, stir in water
  4. Remove from heat

Grain-Free Pancakes

Grain-Free Pancakes

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
290
Servings
1
Ingredients

1 egg 
1/2 c egg whites
1 T coconut flour
1/4 c golden flax meal
1/2 t baking powder
stevia, to taste

Directions
  1. Combine all ingredients together with fork, whisk, or in Magic Bullet
  2. Heat large skillet over med-high heat
  3. Grease skillet
  4. Pour batter into 4" circles into skillet
  5. Wait until bubbles form in pancakes
  6. Flip and cook another minute
  7. Repeat with remaining batter

Dairy-Free Crustless Brownie Cheesecake

Dairy-Free Crustless Brownie Cheesecake

Dietary
Low Carb
Calories per serving
85 (95 w/ honey)
Servings
8
Ingredients

1/2 c coconut flour
1/2 c unsweetened applesauce
1 c water
2 T flax meal
1 t vanilla extract
2 T coconut oil, melted
6 T unsweetened cocoa powder
1/4 t pink salt
1/4 t baking soda
3 T FiberYum IMO Syrup (or honey)

Directions
  1. Preheat oven to 350 degrees
  2. Line a 8 inch round cake pan with parchment paper
  3. Whisk applesauce, water, vanilla, coconut oil, and IMO syrup together in bowl
  4. In separate bowl, stir together coconut flour, flax meal, cocoa powder, pink salt, and baking soda
  5. Pour dry ingredients into wet and stir well
  6. Pour batter into cake pan and smooth evenly with spatula
  7. Bake for 15 minutes (Batter will still look very underdone)
  8. Let cool then transfer to refrigerator until firm
  9. Slice into 8 even triangles
     

'Cheesy' Prince Edward Medley

'Cheesy' Prince Edward Medley

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
155
Servings
2
Ingredients

2 c Prince Edward medley (frozen green beans, yellow beans, carrots)
1/3 c water
1 T butter
2 T Braggs nutritional yeast
2 T coconut cream (canned)
1 T minced onion flakes
1-2 cloves minced garlic
additional spices of choice, to taste

Directions
  1. Steam veggies in water in large skillet
  2. Stir in garlic, onion flakes, and spices and cook until garlic begins to brown
  3. Stir in butter, coconut cream, and nutritional yeast until veggies are covered
  4. Simmer until liquid boils down and sauce desired sauce consistence is reached

Zucchini Biscuits (Dinner Rolls)

Zucchini Biscuits (Dinner Rolls)

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
80
Servings
12
Ingredients

2 T flax meal
1/4 c warm water
4 eggs
1/2 c coconut flour
1 medium zucchini (160 g), finely grated
2 T coconut oil
2 T apple cider vinegar
1/4 c water
1 T basil (or italian seasoning)
1 T baking powder
1/2 t pink salt

Directions
  1. Preheat oven to 350 degrees
  2. Grease cookie sheet
  3. In medium bowl, stir flax meal and warm water together until well combined
  4. In large bowl, combine coconut flour, baking powder, herbs, and salt
  5. Stir eggs, apple cider vinegar, oil, water, and shredded zucchini into flax meal mixture
  6. Add dry ingredients to wet and mix with electric mixer on medium speed to fully combine
  7. Grease hands and scoop dough out by golfball-sized mound
  8. Roll gently and place on baking sheet 
  9. Brush roll tops with additional oil and transfer to oven
  10. Bake 35-45 minutes or until golden brown

Cabbage Noodles & Veggies with Coconut Cream Sauce

Cabbage Noodles & Veggies with Coconut Cream Sauce

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
250
Servings
3
Ingredients

1 small head green cabbage, sliced into strips
1 pint grape tomatoes, cut in half
8 oz mushrooms, sliced thin
1/3 c canned coconut cream
1 T coconut oil
3 T Braggs nutritional yeast
1/4 c water
2 T minced onion flakes
2 T minced garlic
2 t italian seasoning
1/4 t fennel seeds
pink salt and pepper, to taste

Directions
  1. Heat coconut oil and water in wok over med-high heat
  2. Add cabbage and mushrooms
  3. Cover and cook until starting to soften
  4. Drain half of liquid 
  5. Return to stovetop
  6. Stir in coconut cream, tomatoes, onion flakes, garlic, italian seasoning, fennel seeds, and nutritional yeast
  7. Cook 5 more minutes, adding more water if more sauce is desired

Hot Wing Soup

Hot Wing Soup

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
220
Servings
4
Ingredients

1 large (12.5 oz) can Premium Chunk White Chicken in Water
1-2 c water
16 oz frozen, chopped kale
6 medium celery sticks, chopped
1/3 c canned coconut cream
3 T Simple Girl hot sauce (or other hot sauce of choice)
4 T crumbled goat cheese

Directions
  1. Combine kale, celery, and 1/2 c water in saucepan over med-high heat
  2. Cover and cook until celery starts to soften
  3. Stir in can of chicken (including liquid from can), coconut cream, hot sauce, and any additional water desired
  4. Allow to simmer until heated through
  5. Portion into 4 bowls
  6. Top each with 1 T goat cheese and a drizzle of additional hot sauce

S'mores Toaster Tart

S'mores Toaster Tart

Dietary
Low Carb
Calories per serving
245
Servings
1
Ingredients

1 S'mores Better Than Quest Bar (ingredients listed below):

2 T prebiotic fiber (FiberYum IMO syrup)
1/4 c egg white protein powder (or other protein powder of choice)
1 T almond flour
1 dropperful vanilla creme or chocolate stevia
1/2 t vanilla extract 
1/2 T COcolate Chips (or chocolate chips)

Directions
  1. In small bowl, combine protein powder, almond flour, stevia, vanilla extract, and chips
  2. Heat prebiotic fiber (FiberYum IMO syrup) in small saucepan over med-high heat until starting to bubble
  3. Pour prebiotic fiber into small bowl
  4. Stir until doughy mixture is formed (if mixture is too sticky, add additional protein powder)
  5. Add in cocolate (or chocolate) chips once dough is slightly cooled
  6. Transfer dough to wax or parchment paper
  7. Form into bar shape
  8. Place in refrigerator until cooled and set
  9. Place in toaster oven at 350 degrees
  10. Bake for 5-6 minutes, until starting to brown on edges
  11. Flip and bake another 1-3 minutes, leaving center slightly soft still

Crab Puppies

Crab Puppies

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
200 (25 calories per puppy)
Servings
2
Ingredients

8 oz lump crab meat, rinsed and drained
2 T flax meal 
2 T almond flour (may sub 2T additional flax meal instead)
1 1/2 T plain greek yogurt
1 egg
2 t Homemade Old Bay Seasoning 
1/4 t garlic powder
1/4 t lemon pepper 
1/4 t pink salt salt 
1/2-1 t liquid or coconut aminos (optional)

Directions
  1. Preheat oven to 425 degrees
  2. Line baking sheet with parchment paper
  3. In small mixing bowl, combine crab, flax meal, almond flour, yogurt, and egg with hands
  4. Add spices and mix again
  5. Roll mixture into 16 1 inch diameter balls (about 1 rounded tablespoon each) 
  6. Bake for 25 minutes until browned on the outside

Red Pepper Cucumber Salad

Red Pepper Cucumber Salad

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
90
Servings
1
Ingredients

1 red bell pepper
1 cucumber
1/2 t dill
1/4 t Simple Girl BBQ seasoning
2 T Bragg's apple cider vinegar
1/2 t onion flakes
1/2 t minced garlic
pink salt, to taste
stevia, to taste
water

Directions
  1. Chop cucumber and pepper into bite sized pieces and place in bowl
  2. Stir in  onion, garlic, dill, BBQ seasoning, and pink salt
  3. Add vinegar and enough water to cover veggies
  4. Add stevia, to taste
  5. Cover and refrigerate until ready to eat
  6. Drain off desired amount of liquid and serve

* May add olive or avocado oil as well

Buffalo Spinach Skillet

Buffalo Spinach Skillet

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
345
Servings
2
Ingredients

8 oz buffalo
9 oz baby spinach
8 oz mushrooms, quartered
1 green pepper, cut into bite-sized pieces
1/2 c cottage cheese
1 t onion flakes
1/4 c Simple Girl Carolina Style BBQ Sauce
1 T minced garlic
1/2 t xanthan gum

Directions
  1. Cook garlic and buffalo in skillet over med-high heat
  2. Drain liquid then return to stovetop
  3. Stir in onion flakes, green pepper, mushrooms, and spinach 
  4. Cover and cook until veggies soften
  5. Stir in BBQ sauce and cottage cheese
  6. Push veggies to edges of skillet and stir xanthan gum into liquid to thicken sauce
  7. Remove from heat and stir veggies into sauce

Mushroom Chive Breakfast Sandwich

Mushroom Chive Breakfast Sandwich

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
290
Servings
1
Ingredients

1 Paleo English Muffin

1/2 t onion flakes
pink salt, to taste

Directions

Yogurt Parfait

Yogurt Parfait

Dietary
Low Carb
Calories per serving
205
Servings
1
Ingredients

1 container Oikos Triple Zero greek yogurt
1/4 c chopped strawberries
1 T Lily's chocolate chips
2 T Ezekiel Golden Flax cereal

Directions
  1. Place yogurt in bowl
  2. Top with strawberries, chocolate chips, and cereal

Vermicilli Bowl

Vermicilli Bowl

Dietary
Low Carb
Calories per serving
350
Servings
2
Ingredients

2 bunches Pure Mung Bean Vermicilli (aka Cellophane noodles, Chinese vermicelli, bean threads, bean thread noodles, crystal noodles, or glass noodles)
8 small (1-2"diameter) vine-ripe tomatoes
4 oz cooked chicken breast, cut into bite-sized piece
1/3 c canned pumpkin
2 c broccoli
4 oz mushooms, sliced thin
1/4 c edamame
1/4 c chopped, frozen spinach
2 T Bragg's nutritional yeast
1 t minced garlic
1 t onion flakes
1 t smoked paprika
1 t oregano
1/8 t (more or less, to taste) cayenne pepper
pink salt, to taste
 

Directions
  1. Combine tomatoes, mushrooms, spinach, edamame, broccoli, garlic, and onion in skillet over med-high heat
  2. Cover and cook until veggies are soft
  3. Stir in spices, chicken, and pumpkin then cover and simmer
  4. Heat water to a boil in saucepan
  5. Add vermicilli and boil a few minutes, until soft
  6. Drain vermicilli then transfter back to saucepan
  7. Pour sauce over top of vermicillia and stir to combine
  8. Portion into 2 bowls

Chocolate Covered Banana Cookies

Chocolate Covered Banana Cookies

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
125
Servings
12
Ingredients

4 ripe bananas
2 c coconut flour
2 T coconut oil, melted (divided)
2 T unsweetened cocoa/cacao powder (divided)
SweetLeaf chocolate stevia, to taste

Directions
  1. Preheat oven to 350 degrees
  2. Blend bananas, coconut flour, 1 T coconut oil, and 1 T cacao/cocoa powder in food processor/blender
  3. Add stevia, to taste
  4. Spoon mixture evenly into greased mini cupcake tin
  5. Bake for 25 minutes

No-Cheese Cheese Sauce

No-Cheese Cheese Sauce

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
150
Servings
8
Ingredients

2 T butter
1 small yellow squash, chopped
2 carrots, peeled and diced
1/2 small onion, diced
1 t pink salt
1 t garlic powder
1/2 t dry mustard
1 can coconut milk
1 egg yolk
pepper, to taste

Directions
  1. Heat butter in saucepan over medium/high heat
  2. Add squash, carrots, onion, garlic powder, mustard, and salt
  3. Saute 5 minutes, or until onion is translucent
  4. Add coconut milk and bring to simmer
  5. Allow to simmer for 10 minutes, or until vegetables are tender and coconut milk has reduced by 1/2 and is thick
  6. Pour veggies and coconut milk into blender/food processor and puree until smooth
  7. Add egg yolk to puree and blend well
  8. Check seasonings and add more salt or pepper to taste
  9. Serve over veggies or protein of choice

Better Than Quest Bars

Better Than Quest Bars

Dietary
Low Carb
Calories per serving
185 + add-ins
Servings
1
Ingredients

2 T prebiotic fiber (FiberYum IMO syrup)
1/4 c egg white protein powder (or other protein powder of choice)
1 T almond flour
1/2 - 1 dropperful stevia (plain or flavor of choice)
Additional add-ins of choice (cinnamon, vanilla extract, shredded coconut, cacao/cocoa powder, freeze-dried/dried fruit, nuts, raisins, chocolate chips, etc)*

 

Directions
  1. In small bowl, combine protein powder, almond flour stevia, and additional add-ins (see variations below)
  2. Heat prebiotic fiber (FiberYum IMO syrup) in small saucepan over med-high heat until starting to bubble
  3. Pour prebiotic fiber into small bowl
  4. Stir until doughy mixture is formed (if mixture is too sticky, add additional protein powder)
  5. Transfer dough to wax or parchment paper
  6. Form into bar shape
  7. Place in refrigerator until cooled and set
  8. Store in baggie or wax paper at room temp or in refrigerator

*Add-in Variations: 

- Cinnamon Roll: 1/2 t vanilla extract, vanilla creme stevia, 1/4 t cinnamon

- Vanilla Almond: 1/2 t vanilla extract, vanilla creme stevia, 1/2 T coarsely crushed almonds

- Coconut Cashew: 1 t shredded unsweetened coconut, 1/2 T coarsely crushed cashews

- Chocolate: 1 t cacao/cocoa powder, chocolate stevia

- Chocolate Chunk: 1 t cacao/cocoa powder, chocolate stevia, 1/2 T chocolate chips (or COcolate Chips)

- Banana Bread: 1/4 t cinnamon, english toffee stevia, 1/2 crushed freeze-dried bananas

- Banana Nut Muffin: 1/4 t cinnamon, vanilla creme stevia, 1/2 T crushed freeze-dried (or dried) bananas, 1/2 T coarsely chopped walnuts

- Chocolate Strawberry/Raspberry: 1 t cacao/cocoa powder, 1 T crushed freeze-dried (or dried) strawberries/raspberries, chocolate stevia

- Blueberries/Strawberries/Raspberries N Cream: 1/2 t vanilla extract, vanilla creme stevia, 1 T crushed freeze-dried (or dried) blueberries/strawberries/raspberries

- PB&J or AB&J: 1t peanut/almond butter, grape stevia

- Crunchy PB&J (or AB&J): 1 t peanut/almond butter, grape stevia, 1 t crushed peanuts/almonds

- Mint Chocolate Chunk: peppermint stevia, 1 t cacao/cocoa powder, 1/2 T chocolate chips (or COcolate Chips)

- Apple Pie: vanilla creme or english toffee stevia, 1 T crushed freeze-dried (or dried) apples, 1/4 t cinnamon

- Chocolate Covered Raisin: 1 t cacao/cocoa powder, 1 T raisins, chocolate stevia

- S'mores: chocolate or vanilla creme stevia, 1/2 t vanilla extract, 1/2 T COcolate Chips (or cocolate chips)

Spicy Turkey Cauli Rice

Spicy Turkey Cauli Rice

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
350
Servings
4
Ingredients

1 lb ground turkey, browned in skillet
4 c cauliflower florets
2 T olive oil
1 onion, chopped
3-4 cloves garlic, minced
4 medium tomatoes, chopped
1 fresh chili pepper, deseeded and chopped
1/2 t chili flakes
1/2 t cumin
1 t oregano
1/2 t garlic powder
1 c chicken stock or water
1/2 c fresh cilantro, chopped
1 t lime juice
pink salt and pepper, to taste
10 jalapeno pepper slices (more or less, to taste)

Directions
  1. Place cauliflower florets in food processor and pulse a few times until rice-like consistency is reached
  2. Heat olive oil in large skillet over medium heat
  3. Add onion, garlic, and chili and saute 5 minutes
  4. Stir in tomatoes, stock, oregano, cumin, and chili flakes
  5. Bring to simmer and cook for 20 minutes
  6. Add cooked turkey, garlic powder, salt and pepper
  7. Top with jalapeno slices, cilantro and lime juice before serving

Turkey Frittata

Turkey Frittata

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
269
Servings
6
Ingredients

1 lb lean ground turkey
7 eggs
1/8 c cream (or half and half/milk/coconut cream)
1 onion, thinly sliced
3 cloves of garlic, chopped
5 oz mushrooms, roughly chopped
7 oz (1 standard bag) fresh spinach
1/4 cup chicken stock
1 T olive oil
1 T lemon juice
1 T fennel seeds
1 T dill
1 t pink salt
1 t pepper
1 t garlic powder 
1/2 t cayenne pepper or red pepper flakes
1/4 t allspice
additional salt and pepper for seasoning
1/2 c crumbled feta cheese

Directions
  1. Preheat the oven to 350 degrees and heat 2 frying pans on the stove over medium-high heat
  2. In a bowl, mix ground turkey with fennel, salt, pepper, garlic powder, cayenne, dill and allspice
  3. Saute in frying pan until browned and cooked through, then remove and set aside in a bowl
  4. While turkey cooks, chop vegetables
  5. Add sliced onion to 1 T of olive oil in the second frying pan
  6. Season well with salt and pepper and cook until dark brown and soft (this will take at least 10 minutes)
  7. Add garlic and cook an additional 3 minutes
  8. Add mushrooms and chicken stock, then cook until softened
  9. Add spinach and lemon juice to cook down
  10. Taste and add any additional salt and pepper needed
  11. Remove and set aside in a bowl
  12. Grease 8x8 glass baking dish then fill with alternating layers of crumbled turkey and sautéed vegetables until almost full 
  13. Whisk together eggs and cream, then pour into the dish
  14. Bake for 35 minutes, or until cooked through
  15. Top with feta cheese then broil for a couple minutes for a crusty top

Coconut No Bake Cookies

Coconut No Bake Cookies

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
105
Servings
6
Ingredients

4-6 dropperfuls stevia (more or less, to taste)

Directions

  4. Place mixture into 12 even mounds on parchment paper
  5. Place in freezer about 15 minutes, until set
  6. Store in refrigerator

Graham Cracker Nut Butter

Dietary

120 (per tablespoon)

Mozzarella-free Personal Pizza

Mozzarella-free Personal Pizza

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
275
Servings
1
Ingredients

1 egg
1/3 c egg whites
1 T flax meal
1 1/2 T coconut flour
1/4 t garlic powder
1/2 t oregano, divided
2-3 T tomato sauce
1/4 c cottage cheese
1/2 T Bragg's Nutritional Yeast

Directions
  1. Whisk together egg, egg whites, coconut flour, flax meal, garlic powder, and 1/4 t oregano
  2. Pour mixture into greased skillet over medium heat
  3. Cover and allow to cook for 3-4 minutes
  4. Flip, cover again, and cook another 2 minutes
  5. Place crust onto piece of foil
  6. Spread thin layer of tomato sauce on crust, stopping 1/4" from edge
  7. Process cottage cheese, nutritional yeast, and remaining oregano in mini chopper/food processor
  8. Drop cheese mixture by the tablespoon on top of sauce and spead into circles
  9. Transfer pizza to toaster over and toast for 5 minutes
  10. Remove and cut into triangles with pizza cutter

Faux Mac and Cheese

Faux Mac and Cheese

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
250
Servings
4
Ingredients

1 1/2 head cauliflower
4 T butter or coconut oil
1 1/2 t pink salt
1/4 c water
1 small yellow squash (or butternut squash), cut into small cubes
1 carrot, peeled and diced
1/2 small onion, diced
1/2 t garlic powder
1/4 t dry mustard
1 can coconut milk
1 egg yolk
pepper, to taste

Directions
  1. Break cauliflower into small pieces
  2. Add the cauliflower to a large saucepan with 2 T butter, ½ t salt, and water over medium/high heat and cover with a lid
  3. Cook cauliflower for about 5 minutes, until mostly tender
  4. Remove lid and let cauliflower saute for a minute or two, or until lightly caramelized 
  5. Turn heat off, cover, and keep warm until ready to toss with the cheese sauce
  6. Heat remaining 2 T butter in a saucepan over medium/high heat
  7. Add squash, carrot, onion, garlic powder, mustard, and remaining salt to saucepan
  8. Saute 5 minutes, or until onion is translucent
  9. Add coconut milk to the saucepan and bring to a simmer
  10. Allow to simmer for about 10 minutes, or until vegetables are tender and coconut milk has reduced by ⅔ and is thick
  11. Pour veggies and coconut milk into blender/food processor and puree until smooth
  12. Add egg yolk to puree and blend well
  13. Check seasonings and add more salt or pepper to taste
  14. Pour sauce over hot cauliflower and toss to coat

Pesto Aioli

Pesto Aioli

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
125
Servings
4
Ingredients

2 garlic cloves
1 egg yolk
2 t lemon juice
1/2 t dijon mustard
1/4 c olive oil
1 bunch fresh basil
1/4 t pink salt, or more to taste
pepper, to taste

Directions
  1. Mince garlic to a paste with pink salt 
  2. Add garlic mixture, egg yolk, lemon juice, and mustard to blender/food processor
  3. Add oil and pulse until oil is incorporated and mixture is emulsified
  4. Add basil and continue to process
  5. Season with pink salt and pepper, to taste
  6. Whisk in some water if mixture is too thick
  7. Chill, covered, until ready to eat

Broiled Artichokes

Broiled Artichokes

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
110
Servings
4
Ingredients

2 artichokes
1 onion, minced
1 carrot, sliced 
4 cloves garlic, minced
2 T butter, melted
pink salt, to taste

Directions
  1. Clean and trim artichokes
  2. Boil artichokes, onion, carrot, and garlic about 45 minutes
  3. Drain veggies 
  4. Slice artichokes in half
  5. Transfer veggies to cast iron skillet and add butter and pink salt
  6. Broil in oven about 5 minutes
  7. Turn artichokes and broil another 5 minutes

(Excellent served with Pesto Aioli)

Healthy Egg Rolls

Healthy Egg Rolls

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
105
Servings
3
Ingredients

3 Julian Bakery Paleo Wraps
1/2 T coconut oil
1/2 c green cabbage, shredded thin
1/2 c carrot, shredded
1/2 c zucchini, shredded
1/4 c fresh chopped basil
1/4 c chopped cilantro (or parsley)

Directions
  1. Preheat oven to 350 degrees
  2. Melt coconut oil in skillet over medium heat
  3. Add veggies and herbs and cook about 5 minutes, until softened
  4. Place Paleo Wraps on flat surface so they look like a diamond, not square
  5. Spoon 1/3 of veggie mixture onto each Paleo Wrap 
  6. Fold bottom corner up, sides in, then roll toward top corner to close egg roll
  7. Transfer to greased or parchment-lined baking sheet
  8. Bake about 5 minutes or until golden brown

(Alternatively, you can pan fry egg rolls in a greased skillet turning every 30 seconds until golden brown)

Thyme Gravy

Thyme Gravy

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
45
Servings
4 (3/4 c each)
Ingredients

2 c cauliflower florets
2 c chicken stock
1 T butter
1/2 c onion, chopped

pink salt and pepper, to taste

Directions

Enoki Shrimp Scampi

Enoki Shrimp Scampi

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
475
Servings
1
Ingredients

4 oz mushrooms, sliced thin
1 T butter
juice of 1/2 lemon

parsley, as garnish
 

Directions

Boil & Roast Carnitas

Boil & Roast Carnitas

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
400
Servings
20
Ingredients

1 pork butt (5 bs)
3 carrots, chopped
3 onions, chopped
2 bunches cilantro (1 bunch whole, 1 bunch chopped)
6 cloves garlic
1 t coriander 
1 t oregano
1/2 t chili powder
1/2 t cumin
6-8 c water
1 1/2 c green chile salsa
1 c roasted, diced green chiles
1/2 c green onion, sliced thin (including tops)

Directions
  1. In large pot, add pork, carrots, onions, garlic, cumin, coriander, oregano, chili powder, and whole cilantro
  2. Add enough water to cover and bring to a boil
  3. Reduce heat, cover, and simmer until tender (about 3.5 hours)
  4. Remove roast from broth once tender
  5. Place in baking pan, fat side up, and bake at 350 degrees until well-browned, about 1 hour
  6. Drain off fat and shread meat, disregarding fat and bones
  7. Stir in salsa, green chilis, green onions, and chopped cilantro
  8. Bake another 15-20 minutes, until hot

(Great served with Cauliflower Tortillas)

Shred-Shred Salad

Shred-Shred Salad

Italian Chicken Asparagus

Italian Chicken Asparagus

Dietary
Oil Free
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
280
Servings
1
Ingredients

3/4 c tomato sauce
8 oz asparagus
3.5 oz ground chicken
1 t italian seasoning
1/4 t rosemary
1/4 t chili powder
pink salt, to taste

Directions
  1. In saucepan, combine tomato sauce and spices and simmer a few minutes
  2. Add ground chicken and cook a few minutes until chicken is cooked through
  3. Chop asparagus into bite sized pieces
  4. Steam asparagus until desired softness is reached
  5. Pour sauce over asparagus
  6. Sprinkle with pink salt

Tiramisu Bites

Tiramisu Bites

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
355 (12 per bite)
Servings
1 batch
Ingredients

1 Grain-free Waffle
1/2 c Daisy cottage cheese
3 t instant coffee 
2 droppersful SweetLeaf vanilla creme stevia
1/2 - 1 t unsweetened cacao/cocoa powder

Directions
  1. Cut waffle sections into bite-sized pieces by cutting along the lines (mine cut into 32 bites)
  2. In mini food processor/chopper or magic bullet, combine cottage cheese, instant coffe, and stevia until very well combined and fluffy
  3. Transfer mixture into plastic baggie and cut off small portion of corner
  4. Pipe mixture evenly into each waffle bite section
  5. Sprinkle cocoa powder of each section

Ultimate Turkey Taco Salad

Ultimate Turkey Taco Salad

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
590
Servings
1
Ingredients

2 c spring mix
1/4 c salsa
1 c frozen chopped onions & peppers mix
1/2 c edamame
8 oz ground turkey
6 grape tomatoes, sliced
1/2 c plain Greek yogurt
1 T Taco Seasoning
2 jalapeno ring slices, chopped fine

Directions
  1. Brown turkey in skillet
  2. Place spring mix and tomatoes in large bowl and drizzle with salsa
  3. Add edamame, pepper, onions & peppers to skillet then cover and cook, stirring occasionally
  4. When veggies are softened, stir in taco seasoning
  5. Transfer mixture from skillet into salad bowl
  6. Top with Greek yogurt

Twisted Mexican Chili

Twisted Mexican Chili

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
445
Servings
1
Ingredients

Indian Spiced Cabbage

Indian Spiced Cabbage

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
120
Servings
2
Ingredients

1/2 T butter
1/2 T coconut oil
4 c green cabbage, chopped/sliced
1/2 onion, chopped
1 carrot, grated
2 jalapeno ring slices, chopped
1/2 t curry powder
1/2 t cumin
1/8 t turmeric
1 T lemon juice

Directions
  1. Melt butter and coconut oil in skillet over med-high heat
  2. Add onion, cabbage, carrot, and jalapeno
  3. Cover with lid and cook, stirring occasionally, until veggies are soft
  4. Stir in curry, cumin, and turmeric and cook another couple minutes
  5. Transfer to bowl and stir in lemon juice

Strawberries w/ Chocolate Strawberry Sauce

Strawberries w/ Chocolate Strawberry Sauce

Dietary
Oil Free
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
75
Servings
1
Ingredients

8 oz strawberries
3 T water
1 dropperful SweetLeaf chocolate stevia, more/less to taste
(may sub vanilla creme stevia, if desired)
 

Directions
  1. Slice strawberries and set aside
  2. Place 1 oz strawberry slices and water in magic bullet or blender and pulse until combined
  3. Pour into skillet and heat to a simmer
  4. Stir in stevia
  5. Cook, stirring as needed, until liquid reduces to sauce consistency
  6. Pour sauce over strawberry slices
  7. Serve warm or refrigerate and serve cold

Cinnamon Candied Grapefruit Bites

Cinnamon Candied Grapefruit Bites

Dietary
Oil Free
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
65
Servings
1
Ingredients

1/2 grapefruit
3 T water
1-2 t cinnamon
1/2-1 dropperful stevia

Directions
  1. Heat skillet over med-high heat
  2. Cut bottom off of grapefruit half (about 1/2")
  3. Peel remaining grapefruit and cut into sections
  4. Brown all sides of individual grapefruit sections, transferring to plate once browned
  5. Squeeze juice from bottom of grapefruit into skillet with water, stevia, and cinnamon
  6. Simmer liquid, stirring as needed, until sauce consistency is reached
  7. Spoon sauce over carmelized grapefruit sections
  8. Serve warm or chilled
  9.

Mushrooms w/ Spicy Garlic Sauce

Mushrooms w/ Spicy Garlic Sauce

Dietary
Oil Free
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
60
Servings
1
Ingredients

8 oz mushrooms, quartered
1 T Simple Girl Carolina Style BBQ Sauce
1 t yellow mustard
1 t minced garlic
1/2 t Bragg's liquid aminos
water

Directions
  1. Heat enough water to cover entire skillet over med-high heat
  2. Add mushroom and garlic then cover and cook until mushrooms are soft
  3. Remove mushrooms with slotted spoon and set aside
  4. Stir BBQ sauce, mustard, and liquid aminos in remaining liquid in skillet
  5. Allow to simmer, stirring occasionally, until liquid is reduced to sauce consistency
  6. Spoon sauce over mushrooms

Apple Chicken Sandwich w/ Sweet Slaw

Apple Chicken Sandwich w/ Sweet Slaw

Dietary
Oil Free
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
305
Servings
1
Ingredients

1 apple
3 oz cooked chicken breast
4 oz purple cabbage
4 oz green cabbage
2 T Simple Girl Sweet Vinaigrette Dressing
1 1/2 T dijon mustard, divided
1/2 T lemon juice
1/4 t basil 
2 mint leaves, finely chopped
6 drops stevia
1 T apple cider vinegar
1/4 t celery seed

Directions
  1. In medium bowl, mix together 1 T dijon, apple cider vinegar, celery seed, lemon juice, and dressing
  2. Flip apple upside down and cut straight down on both sides of core then set pieces aside
  3. Cut off other 2 remaining slices of apple and chop into bite sized piece then add to bowl
  4. Chop/slice cabbage and add to bowl
  5. Stir until well coated then place in fridge to marinate
  6. Cut the 2 large apple slices into slices of equal thickness to make "buns"
  7. Slice chicken in half and place on 2 apple slices
  8. Mix 1/2 T dijon, basil, stevia, and mint together then spread on chicken
  9. Top with remaining apple slices

MohCO Chips (*ONLY on CO Day in P2)

MohCO Chips (*ONLY on CO Day in P2)

Dietary
Oil Free
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
120
Servings
1
Ingredients

1 T coconut oil
1 dropperful SweetLeaf chocolate stevia (more or less, to taste)
1 t coffee grinds
 

Directions
  1. Place silicone trivet on plate or small baking sheet
  2. Melt coconut oil in measuring cup with pour spout

Lemon Pepper Double Cabbage Shrimp

Lemon Pepper Double Cabbage Shrimp

Dietary
Oil Free
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
270
Servings
1
Ingredients

5 oz shrimp, steamed
6 oz green cabbage, chopped
2 oz purple cabbage, sliced thin
2 small lemons (or 1 large)
1/2 t garlic powder
1/2 t minced onion
1 clove minced garlic
2/3 c water
pink salt
1 tsp (more or less, to taste) black pepper
 

Directions
  1. Heat water in skillet over med-high heat
  2. Add cabbage and minced garlic then cover and cook, stirring occasionally
  3. Peel lemons, cut into 1/4" rounds, and remove any seeds
  4. Add lemons, garlic powder, minced onion, pink salt, and pepper to skillet then cover and cook a few more minutes, until lemons start to break apart and liquid reduces to sauce consistency (may need to add more water)
  5. Stir in steamed shrimp until coated with sauce
  6. Transfer to plate and top with more pink salt and pepper

Cinnamon Meringue Puffs

Cinnamon Meringue Puffs

Dietary
Oil Free
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
130
Servings
1 batch
Ingredients

1 c. egg whites
1/2 tsp. cinnamon
6 packets stevia
1/8 tsp. xanthan gum, optional

Directions
  1. Preheat oven to 350 degrees and line baking sheet with parchment paper
  2. Pour egg whites into bowl and mix with hand mixer until eggs for stiff peaks (Be patient with this b/c it's the most important step!)
  3. Gently stir in cinnamon, stevia, and xanthan gum (if desired, to help puffs keep their shape when baking)
  4. Spoon by the tablespoon onto baking sheet
  5. Bake for 12 minutes, or until golden on top
  6. Sprinkle with additional cinnamon, if desired

Sangria

Sangria

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
210
Servings
10
Ingredients

1 bottle wine of choice (red, white, sparkling, etc)
1 pint each raspberries, blackberries, strawberries (or other fruits of choice: peaches, plums, apricots, mangos, etc)
1 small orange or big tangerine
1 cup (8oz) cognac
1 cup (8oz) Fruit-infused Liquor* of choice (Avoid store bought fruit liquors like amaretto or schnapps, due to added sugars)
2 -3 stevia packets (or liquid stevia), to taste

Directions
  1. Peel orange/tangerine, pull apart into sections, then break each section into 2-3 bits
  2. Add piece to large pitcher along with berries and 2 packets stevia then mash slightly
  3. Add liquors and stir
  4. Taste and adjust sweetness (Should be strong alcohol and notably sweet, but NOT syrupy or oversweet)
  5. Add bottle of red wine, stir and refrigerate at least 4-6 hours (Tastes better the longer it marinates)

Fruit-infused Liquor

Fruit-infused Liquor

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
97
Servings
17 (1.5 oz shot/serving)
Ingredients

1 bottle (750 ml) Ciroc vodka (or other hard liquor of choice)
2 c chopped fruit of choice (lemons, blueberries, strawberries, cherries, pineapple, raspberries, limes, japapenos, etc)
additional add-ins of choice, if desired (citrus peels, minced ginger, fresh herbs, split vanilla beans, whole cloves, whole star anise, whole cinnamon sticks, peppercorns, etc)
stevia, to taste

Directions
  1. Place chopped fruit, and any additional add-ins desired, into 1- 1 1/2 quart mason jar
  2. Pour vodka into jar
  3. Screw lid onto jar
  4. Sit in undisturbed dark place on the kitchen counter at least 3-14 days (The longer the better)
  5. Separate fruit from vodka by straining into a large pyrex measuring cup with pour spout (Line strainer with cheesecloth first if there is a lot of sediment at bottom of mason jar from fruit/add-ins)
  6. Add stevia, to taste
  7. Pour back into liquor bottle
  8. Store in freezer 

Shakshouka

Shakshouka

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
303
Servings
2
Ingredients

1 T olive oil or coconut oil
2 cloves garlic, minced
1 onion, coarsley chopped 
1  bell pepper, coarsley chopped 
1 (28 ounce) can whole peeled plum tomatoes with juice
1 t paprika, or to taste
2 slices pickled jalapeno pepper, finely chopped
4 eggs
red pepper flakes, optional
pink salt, to taste

Directions
  1. Heat oil in a deep skillet over medium heat
  2. Stir in garlic, onion, and bell pepper
  3. Cook and stir until onion is soft and translucent, about 5 minutes
  4. Stir in  canned tomatoes, paprika and jalapenos, using the back of a spoon to break up the tomatoes
  5. Simmer for 25 minutes (*Sauce may be made ahead of time and reheated in skillet. Also, may use a store-bought no sugar added tomato sauce, if desired)
  6. Crack an egg into a small bowl, then gently slip the egg into the tomato sauce
  7. Repeat with remaining eggs
  8. Cook until egg whites are firm and the yolks have thickened but are not hard, 2 1/2 to 3 minutes (If sauce gets dry, add a few tablespoons water) 
  9. Spoon out sauce equally into 2 bowls/plates
  10. Remove eggs with slotted spoon and place on top of sauce
  11. Top with pink salt and red pepper flakes, if desired

(Great served with a slice of Focaccia Flax Bread, Cauliflower Tortillas, or other bread of choice for dipping)

Sprouted Almond Cheese

Sprouted Almond Cheese

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
75
Servings
16 (2T/serving)
Ingredients

2 c raw, unpasteurized almonds (must get these from farmer's market or local farm stand -- commercially available almonds from grocery store are chemically or heat pasteurized and are not raw. They will not sprout)
1/2 t probiotics 
2 T nutritional yeast
2 cloves garlic, finely minced (up to 4 cloves if you like very strong garlic)
1 small shallot, minced, optional
2 T coconut aminos 
1 t black pepper 
1 t pink salt

Directions
  1. Rinse 2 cups raw unpasteurized almonds
  2. Put in glass bowl or mason jar and cover with filtered water
  3. Soak almonds in water, on kitchen counter at room temperature, for 24-30 hours (This allows raw almonds to sprout - you will see a tiny white sprout between the two halves of the almond)
  4. Put almonds in food processor or blender with 1 1/2 cups water and process until creamy
  5. Add 1/2 tsp probiotics and mix in food processor again
  6. Put colander over bowl and put cheesecloth over colander then pour almond mixture into cheesecloth
  7. Pull up all 4 edges and tie together
  8. Pour liquid (collected in glass bowl under colander) into a glass mason jar and set it aside. (This is almond cream. You'll need 3 T for this recipe and can make almond milk with remainder)
  9. Place another, smaller bowl filled with water on top of the almond-filled cheesecloth (This bowl is a weight, intended to squeeze out all the excess almond cream)
  10. Wait 30 minutes and collect more almond cream from the bottom bowl, pouring into your mason jar
  11. Return weighted bowl on top and wait another 12 hours (on counter at room temperature)
  12. Open cheesecloth and pour contents into clean glass bowl
  13. Mix in: minced garlic, nutritional yeast, coconut aminos, black pepper, pink salt, and 3 T almond cream (collected liquid) with a fork to incorporate all ingredients
  14. Cover and refrigerate cheese for up to 1 week

(To make almond milk with leftover almond cream: add equal parts almond cream and water, refrigerate and consume within 1 week)

Turkey Sausage

Dietary
Oil Free

Hot Garlic Tomatoes & Brussel Sprouts

Hot Garlic Tomatoes & Brussel Sprouts

Dietary
Oil Free
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
140
Servings
1
Ingredients

8 oz brussel sprouts, steamed
8 oz grape tomatoes
2 T apple cider vinegar
2 T water
1 t minced garlic
1 1/2 t hot sauce, divided
1/2 t Bragg's liquid aminos
stevia, if desired

Directions
  1. Brown garlic in apple cider vinegar and water in skillet over med-high heat
  2. Stir in brussel sprouts, tomatoes, 1 t hot sauce, and liquid aminos (stevia may be added for a sweeter sauce)
  3. Place lid on skillet and cook, stirring occasionally, until tomatoes are soft and start to break open
  4. Transfer to plate and drizzle with remaining 1/2 t hot sauce
    (Shown served with Old Bay Cod for a total of 288 calories)

Ranch Celery Noodles

Ranch Celery Noodles

Dietary

Ingredients

1 t Ranch Seasoning

Directions
  1. Bring large saucepan 3/4 full of water to a boil
  2. Slice celery into very thin strips
  3. Boil celery for about 20 minutes, until very soft and noodle-like
  4. Strain water out in collander then return noodles to saucepan
  5. Stir in Ranch Seasoning

Honey Mustard Chicken w/ Celery Noodles

Honey Mustard Chicken w/ Celery Noodles

Dietary
Oil Free
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
205
Servings
1
Ingredients

8 oz celery

2 T Simple Girl Sweet Mustard Dressing
1 T yellow mustard
1 T dijon mustard
8-16 drops stevia
1/4 t garlic powder

Directions
  1. Fill large saucepan 1/2 full and bring to a boil
  2. Slice celery into long, thin strips

Cinnamon Glazed Apple Duo

Cinnamon Glazed Apple Duo

Dietary
Oil Free
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
105
Servings
1
Ingredients

1 apple, divided
1/4-1/2 c water
1/2 t (or more) pumpkin pie spice
1 dropperful SweetLeaf vanilla creme stevia
1 t (or more) cinnamon
 

Directions
  1. Add 1/4 c water to skillet over med-high heat
  2. Core apple and divide into quarters 
  3. Chop 1/4 apple coarsely and set aside
  4. Cut remaining 3/4 apple into very thin slices
  5. Add apple slices, pumpkin pie spice, and vanilla stevia to skillet 
  6. Cover and cook, stirring occasionally, until apple slices are softened
  7. While apple slices are cooking, combine chopped 1/4 apple with cinnamon in ziploc bag or tupperware
  8. Shake until chopped apples are well coated with cinnamon
  9. Transfer cooked apple slices to plate (leave liquid in skillet) and top with cinnamon coated apples
  10. Add additional water to skillet, if needed, and stir in leftover cinnamon
  11. Cook, uncovered, until liquid reduces to sauce consistency
  12. Drizzle cinnamon sauce over plated apples

Personal Veggie Lasagna

Personal Veggie Lasagna

Dietary
Oil Free
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
320
Servings
1
Ingredients

8 oz zucchini
8 oz tomato sauce, 1/4 c reserved
4 oz yellow heirloom tomatoes, chopped
1 c cottage cheese, divided
1/4 t minced garlic
1/4 t minced onion
1/4 t garlic powder
1/8 t chives
1/2 t parsley
1/4 t oregano
1/8 t basil

Directions
  1. Preheat oven to 375 degrees
  2. Use a mandolin to slice 1/2 of the zucchini into very thin strips, like lasagna noodles, and set aside
  3. Chop remaining 4 oz of zucchini and place in a bowl with 3/4 c tomato sauce, tomatoes, minced garlic, minced onion, chives, 1/8 t garlic powder, and 1/2 c cottage cheese
  4. Stir until well combined, then set aside
  5. Spread reserved 1/4 c tomato sauce evenly on bottom of meatloaf pan (Use loaf pan with a lifting trivet if you have one)
  6. Cover sauce layer with zucchini strips
  7. Spread 1/2 c sauce mixture evenly over zucchini strips
  8. Repeat layers of zucchini then sauce, finishing with a zucchini layer
  9. Combine remaining 1/2 c cottage cheese with parsley, oregano, 1/4 t garlic powder, and basil in a bowl
  10. Spread evenly over top zucchini layer
  11. Cover pan with foil then bake for 30 minutes
  12. Remove foil and bake an additional 5 minutes
  13. May want to let lasagna stand for a few minutes before removing from pan

Dietary
Oil Free
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
195
Servings
1
Ingredients

Creamy No-tato Soup

Creamy No-tato Soup

Dietary
Oil Free
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
75
Servings
1
Ingredients

Homemade Old Bay Seasoning Recipe

The history of Old Bay seasoning for seafood is a tale as old as time. Created in the late 1800s, it has been used to prepare some of America's favorite dishes since its inception and continues to be popular today. When you think about your all-time favorite dish with shrimp or crab cakes on top, many people will say their go-to meal includes this delicious sauce that not only enhances flavor but also helps bring back memories full of childhood nostalgia.

Jump To Recipe

Spicy, tasty, and actually kind of healthy.

Old Bay seasoning is the perfect way to spice up seafood dishes of all types. It not only tastes great, but it also contains a healthy amount of sodium and vitamin C!

Old bay seasoning is a staple in most kitchens because no dish can be boring when you add this unique ingredient from Maryland. The recipe for Old Bay's secret flavor comes down to three ingredients: celery salt, paprika powder, and ground mustard seed; making an already tasty meal even better with its extra kick that will leave your taste buds begging for more!

Old Bay seasoning is a spice mix with eight spices that can be used for seafood, soups, or sauces. It has been around since 1933 and was originally created in Maryland by two German immigrant brothers of the Bayer family when they were looking to create an all-purpose flavoring blend without salt as one of the ingredients during Prohibition

Old Bay Seasoning is a spice mixture made up of multiple different herbs/spices which are mostly commonly used on crustaceans like crabs and shrimp but also pairs well with other foods such as hamburgers. The recipe was first developed in Baltimore back during prohibition where it served more purposes than just its culinary uses (namely because Baltimore's water had high levels iron).

Flavor for your favorite seafoods

People love using old bay seasoning in their dishes because it has the perfect amount of spices and flavor. The best way to use it is on crabs, as well as other seafood like clams or shrimp.

Old Bay seasoning is a key ingredient in many dishes, and it's not just for seafood. Old Bay can be used as an all-purpose poultry rub or sprinkled on ribs before grilling.

Old bay seasoning was introduced to the American public back in 1945 by spice company McCormick & Co., but its roots are much older than that - sailors began using this blend of herbs and spices centuries ago when they started trading with Asia via colonial routes like Maryland where I grew up!

Old Bay seasoning is a great way to give your food a kick, and it's specifically designed for seafood dishes.

Old Bay seasoning has been around since the 1940s with its signature red color that represents old bay leaves being ground up into spices after months of drying. The herbs found in Old Bay spice are black pepper, cayenne pepper (for heat), paprika (to add more flavor along with adding some orangey tones) as well as celery salt among others!

It's Also Good on Burgers

Seasoning is an essential part of cooking, but some people like to experiment with different flavor combinations and spices. For example, you can add old bay seasoning on burgers for a more tangy taste or throw in salt and herbs if you're looking for something fresh tasting.

Old Bay seasoning is a popular American spice mixture that originated as many others have in the bay area of Baltimore, Maryland. It's often used on hamburgers to provide them with more flavor and taste.

Old Bay seasoning is a classic American spice that has become associated with hamburgers. Most famously, it can be found on the Wendy's Bacon Double Cheeseburger as well as their Spicy Chicken Sandwich, but if you're looking to try it in your home kitchen for grilling season then this easy recipe will guide you through how to do so!

Dietary
Oil Free
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
8
Servings
16 (1/2 T per serving)

Directions

  2. Store in airtight container

Steak Day Stew

Steak Day Stew

Dietary
Oil Free
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
235
Servings
1
Ingredients

3.5 oz steak (larger steak may be depending on Phase)
1 large tomato, chopped into bite sized pieces or 3/4 c canned diced tomatoes (again, more may be used depending on Phase)
water
1 clove minced garlic
onion power, to taste
garlic powder, to taste
pink salt and pepper, to taste
italian seasoning, to taste

Directions
  1. Heat crockpot to High
  2. Cut steak into bite sized pieces and add to crockpot
  3. Add tomato and garlic
  4. Pour water until 1" above steak
  5. Stir in spices
  6. Place lid on crockpot and cook about 4 hours

Egg White Flatbread

Egg White Flatbread

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
140
Servings
1
Ingredients

3/4 c liquid egg whites (or 4 egg whites)
2 T coconut flour
choice of spices, optional (oregano, garlic powder, italian seasoning, rosemary, thyme, etc)
1 T Nutritional Yeast, if cheesy taste is desired (*Add an additional 20 calories)

Directions
  1. Grease skillet with butter or coconut oil and heat to med-low
  2. Whisk egg whites with coconut flour in a bowl
  3. Add in spices of choice and nutritional yeast, if desired, and whisk again
  4. Pour mixure into skillet and spread evenly
  5. Cover with lid and cook for 3-4 minutes (until top starts to bubble)
  6. Flip and cook, covered, another 2 minutes
  7. Remove from skillet

Jamaican Jerk Chicken

Jamaican Jerk Chicken

Dietary
Oil Free
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
170
Servings
12 (4 oz raw portion each)
Ingredients

2 T ground thyme
1 T ground rosemary
1 T ground allspice
2 inch section fresh ginger, peeled
1 1⁄2 T pink salt
1 1⁄2 t onion powder
1 1⁄2 t black pepper
1 1⁄2 t ground cinnamon
3⁄4 t ground nutmeg
3⁄4 t garlic powder
3⁄4 t paprika
1 t crushed red pepper flakes (or more, to taste)
12 bay leaves (finely crumbled)
2 T powdered sweet leaf stevia
3 lbs boneless, skinless chicken breast
2 limes, juice of

 

Directions
  1. Put chicken breast and juice from 2 limes in zip lock bag then set aside
  2. Combine all other ingredients (everything but chicken & lime juice) in small mixing bowl and mix well
  3. Coat chicken with dry seasoning/spice mixture (The idea here is to get as much as possible to stick to the chicken)
  4. Refrigerate for 3 - 24 hours, then remove from refrigerator and allow to come to near room temperature
  5. Grill chicken over hot direct fire, like outdoor BBQ (Don't worry about the black, it's supposed to be there. About 30-40% of the outside of the meat should end up black, but it will not be burned or bitter) 
  6. Once seared, remove to the indirect heat area of the grill and cook to 165* internal temperature

Thanksgiving Dinner Bowl

Thanksgiving Dinner Bowl

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
465
Servings
2
Ingredients

8 oz ground turkey
1-2 t minced garlic
1 small yellow onion, sliced
1/2 T coconut oil
1 stalk celery (whole head of celery), chopped
1 1/2 c green beans
1/2 c cranberries
1/2 c canned pumpkin puree
1/2-1 t cinnamon
pink salt, to taste
1/2 c pecans

Directions
  1. Brown turkey with garlic in skillet over medium-high heat then drain and set aside
  2. Melt coconut oil in skillet
  3. Stir in onions, celery, and green beans then cover and allow to cook until softened
  4. Stir in cranberries, cinnamon, pumpkin, and turkey then cover and cook a few more minutes
  5. Remove from heat and stir in pink salt and pecans
  6. Transfer to 2 plates/bowls

ABC Cake

ABC Cake

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
105
Servings
8
Ingredients

4 eggs 
1/2 c canned pumpkin puree
2 t stevia extract (more or less, to taste)
2 t vanilla extract
3 large (or 4 small), very ripe bananas 
1/8 t pink salt
1 t cinnamon
1 t pumpkin pie spice
1 bag (1.2 oz) Trader Joe's freeze-dried Fuji apple slices, crushed (or 2 Fuji apples, chopped)
 

Directions
  1. Preheat oven to 350 degrees
  2. Grease 9" cake pan 
  3. Place all ingredients, except apples, into blender or food processor
  4. Process until smooth
  5. Stir in apples
  6. Pour into cake pan
  7. Bake for 55-60 minutes, until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean
  8. Allow cake to cool completely in pan before removing
  9. Slice and serve once cooled
  10. Can be stored, loosely covered, at room temperature for up to 3 days

Chicken Teriyaki Pineapple

Chicken Teriyaki Pineapple

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
342
Servings
2
Ingredients

1 whole pineapple
8 oz cooked chicken breast, chopped into bite sized pieces
12 oz green beans
2 T coconut aminos (or more)
1 T Braggs liquid aminos (or more)
1/8-1/4 t xanthan gum
pink salt and pepper, to taste

Directions
  1. Slice pineapple in half, lengthwise
  2. Score inside of one pineapple half with knife, remove pinapple chunks (be sure to discard core), and store for another recipe 
  3. Score inside of other pineapple half with knife, remove pineapple chunks, and place in skillet over med-high heat
  4. Set pineapple rinds onto 2 plates to use as bowls
  5. Add green beans to skillet, cover, and let simmer until beans are soft
  6. Remove lid and stir in chicken, coconut aminos, and liquid aminos
  7. Replace lid and allow to simmer a few minutes, until heated through
  8. With tongs, equally portion green beans, pineapple, and chicken into each pineapple bowl
  9. Whisk xanthan gum into liquid remaining in skillet
  10. Remove from heat and let thicken for a minute or two
  11. Pour sauce over each pineapple bowl
  12. Sprinkle with pink salt and pepper, if desired

Chai Apple Cookies

Chai Apple Cookies

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
90
Servings
20
Ingredients

1 c almond butter
1/2 c unsweetened apple sauce
1 egg
2 T coconut flour
1 t baking soda
1 t cinnamon
1/4 t pink salt
1/4 t ground cloves
1/4 t ginger
pinch of nutmeg
1/2 large apple, peeled and finely diced

Directions
  1. Preheat oven to 350 degrees
  2. Line baking sheets with parchment paper
  3. Mix almond butter, egg, and apple sauce in large bowl with hand mixer (or in food processor)
  4. Add in coconut flour, baking soda, and spices then blend until combined
  5. Fold in diced apple with spatula
  6. Spoon about 1 T batter at a time onto 2 baking sheets and spread into 20 circles
  7. Bake 8-12 minutes, until edges of cookies are slightly firm or dry to the touch and top of cookies no longer look wet
  8. Remove from oven and let cool for 5 minutes on baking sheet
  9. Transfer to wire cooling rack to finish cooling

Homemade Lipstick

Homemade Lipstick

Dietary
Oil Free
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Ingredients

1 T lip balm (NutriMost Lip Balm or Vaseline Lip Therapy)
1 t mineral eyeshadow, color of choice

Directions
  1. Place about a tablespoon of lip balm in a microwave-safe bowl
  2. Place the bowl in the microwave and heat it until it melts and becomes runny
  3. Add 1 teaspoon of eyeshadow powder then stir it up to distribute the color throughout (Add more eyeshadow for a more saturated lipstick look (darker/opaque) or add less eyeshadow for a tinted lipgloss look (lighter/translucent)
  4. Pour mixture into container(s) (Use an old lipstick or chapstick tube, a cosmetics pot, or any other container with a lid)
  5. Place in refrigerator or freezer and let the mixture harden before you use it

Almond Coconut Candy

Almond Coconut Candy

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
170
Servings
25
Ingredients

Bars:
1 c shredded unsweetened coconut
2 c almonds
1/2 c almond butter
2/3 c coconut oil, melted
1 T coconut flour
1/2 t pink salt
1 T stevia
1 T vanilla extract

Topping:
1/3 c coconut oil, melted
2 T unsweetened cocoa powder
stevia, to taste

Directions
  1. Line a 9×9” baking pan with wax paper
  2. Pulse almonds in food processor, until coarsely chopped
  3. Add shredded coconut, almond butter, 2/3 c coconut oil, coconut flour, pink salt, vanilla, and stevia then pulse until combined
  4. Transfer into baking pan and smooth out to the corners
  5. Refrigerate until set (about 1 hour)
  6. Combine 1/3 c coconut oil with cocoa powder and stevia 
  7. Pour coconut oil chocolate over almond base and spread with a spoon/spatula until evenly coated
  8. Place bars back in refrigerator for approximately 5 minutes, until chocolate is solid but still a little soft 
  9. Cut into 25 squares and store in a plastic container in the fridge

Squash Flax Pizza Crust

Squash Flax Pizza Crust

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
207
Servings
6
Ingredients

1 egg
1/2 c egg whites
2 T coconut oil, melted
2 c shredded squash (zucchini and/or yellow squash)
2 dropperfuls stevia
2 t oregano
1 t garlic powder
1/2 t pink salt
1 t baking powder
1 c flax meal
2 T coconut flour

Directions
  1. Preheat oven to 425 degrees and line pizza pan with parchment paper
  2. Steam shredded squash then drain ALL liquid from it by wringing in a dishtowel or cheesecloth
  3. Place in bowl and stir in egg, egg white, coconut oil, pink salt, oregano, baking powder, and garlic powder
  4. Stir in flax meal and coconut flour until well combined
  5. Transfer dough to pizza pan
  6. Use a spatula to spread dough into a circle about 10 inches in daimeter and 1 cm thick (You may want to leave the edges slightly thicker for crust effect)
  7. Bake for 15 minutes
  8. Remove from oven and add desired toppings
  9. Bake another 5 minutes

1 dropperful stevia
sprinkle of pink salt

Directions
  1. Combine all ingredients for Dark Chocolate Layer in measuring cup with pour spout
  2. Pour into ice cube tray (fill 4 cubes about 2/3 each)
  3. Place in freezer until solidified 5-10 minutes
  4. Combine all ingredients for Almond Chocolate Layer
  5. Pour into ice cube tray over solidified Dark Chocolate Layer
  6. Return to freezer until solidifed

Kale Almond Chicken Salad

Kale Almond Chicken Salad

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
339
Servings
2
Ingredients

6 oz cooked chicken breast, cut into bite sized pieces
4 c kale
15 grape tomatoes, quartered
2 T minced garlic
2 T apple cider vinegar
1 t coconut oil
1/4 c slivered almonds
6 drops stevia
1 t lemon pepper
1 T dried minced onion
2 T hemp hearts
pink salt, to taste

Directions
  1. Melt cocont oil in saucepan over med-high heat
  2. Add garlic and cook 1-2 minutes
  3. Add in kale, minced onion, stevia, lemon pepper, and apple cider vinegar
  4. Cover with lid and cook 3 minutes then stir and cook another 3 minutes
  5. Remove from heat and stir in almonds, tomatoes, hemp hearts, and chicken
  6. Sprinkle with pink salt
  7. Serve warm or cold

Cake Batter Nice Cream

Dietary
Sugar Free

Servings

Ingredients

Coconut Flour Yogurt Pizza Crust

Coconut Flour Yogurt Pizza Crust

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
272
Servings
2
Ingredients

4 eggs
1/4 c coconut flour
1/4 c plain yogurt
1 t onion powder
1 t oregano
1 t basil
1/3 c shredded parmesan cheese
2 cloves minced garlic
1/4 tsp pink salt

Directions
  1. Line baking sheet or pizza pan with parchment paper
  2. Preheat oven to 400 degrees
  3. Whip eggs in a large bowl with yogurt and salt
  4. Add coconut flour and whip until smooth   
  5. Stir in onion powder, oregano, basil, garlic, and parmesan cheese
  6. Gently pour about 1/2 the batter onto paper lined pan
  7. Use spatula to spread the batter into a thin 8″ circle
  8. Bake for 10 minutes
  9. Remove pan from oven, add pizza sauce, cheese and other toppings as desired
  10. Place back in the oven on broil for about 8 minutes more
  11. Repeat this process with the remaining half of the coconut flour batter

Oil Free
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving

Pina Colada Chicken

Pina Colada Chicken

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
382
Servings
1
Ingredients

4 chicken tenders
1/4 cup shredded, unsweetened coconut
1/4 c egg whites (or 1 egg)
2 t coconut oil
1/2 c unsweetened, crushed pineapple

Directions
  1. Dip chicken pieces in egg
  2. Heat coconut oil in frying pan
  3. Coat egg dipped chicken in shredded coconut, pressing down to even out the thickness of the chicken
  4. Saute coated chicken in 1 tsp coconut oil until browned, turn over and brown on other side using remainder of coconut oil
  5. In a separate pan, heat crushed pineapple until juice slightly thickens
     

Pumpkin Turkey Chili

Pumpkin Turkey Chili

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
450
Servings
4
Ingredients

2 c pumpkin puree
2 c edamame
1 large onion, chopped
2-3 T minced garlic
4 T pumpkin pie spice
1 lb ground turkey
2 c Swanson chicken stock
2 c unsweetened almond milk
2 T coconut oil
2 dropperfuls stevia

Directions
  1. Melt coconut oil in large saucepan over med-high heat
  2. Add chopped onions, garlic, and turkey and cook until turkey is cooked through
  3. Stir in chicken stock, pumpkin, almond milk, edamame, stevia, and pumpkin pie spice
  4. Place lid on saucepan, reduce heat, and cook another 10-15 minutes, stirring occasionally

Pumpkin Bread

Pumpkin Bread

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
183
Servings
10
Ingredients

1 1/2 c almond flour
1/4 c coconut flour
1 1/2 t baking powder
1 1/2 t baking soda
1/2 t pink salt
1 1/2 t pumpkin pie spice
1 c pumpkin puree
1/2 c unsweetened applesauce
1/3 c water
1 t lemon juice
3 T coconut oil, melted
2 eggs
1 t vanilla

Directions
  1. Preheat oven to 350 degrees
  2. Grease 9x4 loaf pan
  3. Whisk together almond flour, coconut flour, baking soda, baking powder, salt, and pumpkin pie spice in large bowl
  4. In another bowl, whisk together pumpkin puree, lemon juice, applesauce, water, coconut oil, eggs, and vanilla
  5. Slowly add flour mixture to pumpkin mixture and stir until blended
  6. Pour batter into loaf pan and bake 50-60 minutes, or until cooked through and toothpick inserted in center comes out clean

Eggs In Clouds

Eggs In Clouds

Dietary
Oil Free
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
140
Servings
1
Ingredients

2 eggs, separated
1/2-1 t chives (or other spices)
pink salt and pepper, to taste

*Add-Ins: nutritional yeast, parmesan cheese, cheddar cheese (*PHASE 4/BEYOND ONLY)

Directions
  1. Preheat oven to 375 degrees and line baking sheet with parchment paper
  2. Whip egg whites with hand mixer until stiff peaks form
  3. Fold in chives (and any additional add-ins if in P4/Beyond)
  4. Scoop whites onto parchment paper into 2 mounds
  5. Press spoon into center of each mound to make indent
  6. Place one yolk into each indent
  7. Bake in oven for 8-12 minutes (depending how runny you want your yolk)
  8. Remove from oven and top with pink salt and pepper

Zoodles with Quick Tomato Sauce

Zoodles with Quick Tomato Sauce

Dietary
Oil Free
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
150
Servings
1
Ingredients

8 oz zucchini
1 container (7.5 oz) grape tomatoes
2 T tomato paste
1/2 t minced garlic
1 t Italian seasoning
1/8 t garlic powder
1/8 t onion powder
pink salt, to taste
1/8-1/4 c water + water for boiling zoodles

Directions
  1. Bring water to boil in medium saucepan
  2. Sprialize zucchini and place in boiling water
  3. After zucchini noodles are cooked to desired consistency, remove from heat and strain
  4. In second saucepan, combine 1/8 c water, garlic, grape tomatoes, and spices and bring to a boil then cover and reduce heat 
  5. Cook sauce ingredients until tomatoes start to pop open, stirring occasionally
  6. Stir in tomato paste and extra water, if needed
  7. Pour sauce over zoodles and serve

Vanilla (or Chocolate) Almond Forgotten Cookies

Vanilla (or Chocolate) Almond Forgotten Cookies

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
16
Servings
48
Ingredients

1 c lquid egg whites
1 scoop vanilla whey protein powder
1/2 t xanthan gum
1/2 c chopped almonds
1/2-1 T unsweetened cocoa powder, optional
1 packet stevia

Directions
  1. Preheat oven to 350 degrees and line baking sheets with parchment paper or greased foil
  2. Beat egg whites in bowl with hand mixer until stiff peaks form
  3. Slowly add in protein powder while continuing to run mixer
  4. Add xanthan gum and mix another minute
  5. Fold in stevia, almonds, and cocoa powder (if desired)
  6. Drop 48 heaping teaspoons onto baking sheets 
  7. Place in oven and turn it off
  8. Leave in oven overnight (or for ~12 hours)

Kelly's Swedish Butter Cookies

Kelly's Swedish Butter Cookies

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
70
Servings
20
Ingredients

1/2 c coconut flour
1 scoop vanilla whey protein powder
1/2 t baking soda
1/4 t pink salt
2 egg yolks
2 t vanilla extract
1/4 c butter, room temp
1/4 c coconut oil
stevia, to taste (~1-2 t)

Directions
  1. Combine coconut flour, protein powder, baking soda, and salt in mixing bowl.
  2. Add in egg yolks, butter, vanilla, coconut oil, and stevia and mix with hand mixer until combined, pausing to press mixture together with hands occasionally.
  3. Lay a piece of plastic wrap onto counter and place dough it.
  4. Form a rectangular log that is 20 cm long.
  5. Wrap plastic wrap around log and place in refrigerator for 30 minutes.
  6. Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
  7. Remove dough log from refrigerator and slice into 20 cookies, 1 cm thick each.
  8. Place on parchment lined cookie sheet.
  9. Bake for 12-14 minutes or until slightly browned around edges.
  10. Remove from oven and allow to cool on cookie sheet for 10 minutes.

Chocolate Nut Crunch Muffins / Cupcakes

Chocolate Nut Crunch Muffins / Cupcakes

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
145
Servings
12
Ingredients

Cake
1 c almonds
2 medium ripe bananas 
2 eggs
1 t vanilla
2 t stevia extract
1/4 c unsweetened cocoa powder
1/2 t baking soda
1 t apple cider vinegar

Frosting
1 T almond butter
1 dropperful stevia
1/2 c plain greek yogurt
1/2 T cocoa powder
1/8 t xanthan gum, optional

Directions
  1. Preheat oven to 400 degrees and line muffin pan with liners
  2. Place almonds in food processor and pulse until very finely chopped
  3. Add bananas and process until combined
  4. Add eggs, vanilla, stevia, cocoa powder, baking soda, vinegar and process until combined, scraping sides with spatula as needed
  5. Pour batter into muffin pan
  6. Bake for 15 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean
  7. Whisk all frosting ingredients together
  8. Frost cupcakes once completely cooled

Dietary

Low Carb
Calories per serving

Top layer:

Strawberries & Cream Sorbet with Chocolate Strawberry Sauce

Strawberries & Cream Sorbet with Chocolate Strawberry Sauce

Dietary
Oil Free
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
75
Servings
1
Ingredients

5 oz frozen strawberries
1 dropperful SweetLeaf vanilla creme stevia
2-3 T water
3 oz strawberries, chopped
2 dropperfuls SweetLeaf chocolate stevia

 

Directions
  1. Place frozen strawberries in food processor with vanilla stevia and process until combined
  2. Scrape sides down and add water as needed until desired consistency is reached
  3. Transfer to bowl and place in freezer
  4. Heat small saucepan over medium-high heat
  5. Add chopped strawberries, 1 T water, and 2 dropperfuls chocolate stevia
  6. Cook and mash with fork until well combined
  7. Pour sauce into small bowl and place in fridge or freezer until cooled
  8. Drizzle sauce over sorbet

Peach Vanilla Paleo Bagels

Peach Vanilla Paleo Bagels

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
269
Servings
6
Ingredients

1 1/2 c almond flour
1/4 c flax meal
1 T coconut flour
1 t baking soda
1/4 t pink salt
4 eggs
2 T apple cider vinegar
1 large peach, diced
1 packet SweetLeaf stevia
cinnamon, to taste
1 dropperful Sweetleaf vanilla creme stevia
1 dropperful Sweetleaf english toffee stevia
1/2 T coconut oil

Directions
  1. Preheat oven to 350 degrees
  2. Grease donut pan and dust with coconut flour
  3. Mix diced peach with stevia packet and cinnamon
  4. Heat coconut oil in skillet and cook peaches
  5. Pulse almond flour, flax meal, coconut flour, baking soda, and salt in food processor
  6. Add eggs, vinegar, half of the cooked peaches, and vanilla stevia and process until combined
  7. Place batter and rest of cooked peaches in ziploc bag, snip off corner, and pipe into donut pan
  8. Bake for 20-25 minutes or until toothpick inserted into center comes out clean
  9. Remove from oven and allow to cool in pan for 1 hour

Dietary

Low Carb
Calories per serving
60
Servings
2
Ingredients

2 c frozen peaches
1/2-1 t cinnamon
2 dropperfuls SweetLeaf vanilla creme stevia

Directions
  1. Place frozen peaches in food processor and pulse until broken up
  2. Scrape mixture off sides with spatula
  3. Add stevia and cinnamon
  4. Continue to process until sorbet consistency is reached, stopping to scrape with spatula as needed
  5. Scoop into 2 bowls
  6. Sprinkle with cinnamon

Tuna Zoodle Casserole Skillet

Tuna Zoodle Casserole Skillet

Dietary
Oil Free
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
220
Servings
1
Ingredients

1 can albacore tuna
8 oz zucchini
1 T minced garlic
1 T apple cider vinegar
2 T dijon mustard
1/2 t onion powder
1 t italian seasoning
1/2 t thyme
pink salt and pepper, to taste

Directions
  1. Heat vinegar in skillet over medium heat and add undrained tuna and garlic
  2. Use a potato peeler to cut zucchini into strips then cut into thirds
  3. Stir zucchini into skillet and place lid on top for 3-5 minutes
  4. Remove lid and stir in mustard, onion powder, italian seasoning, and thyme
  5. Place lid on top again and cook until zucchini is tender
  6. Drain liquid then season with pink salt and pepper

BBQ Mahi Mahi on Mushroom Bun

BBQ Mahi Mahi on Mushroom Bun

Dietary
Oil Free
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
195
Servings
1
Ingredients

2 large portabello mushroom caps
1 T Bragg's liquid aminos
5 oz Mahi Mahi
1/2 t Simple Girl BBQ Seasoning

Directions
  1. Preheat oven to 350 degrees and line baking sheet with parchment paper
  2. Brush both sides of mushroom caps with liquid aminos
  3. Sprinkle BBQ Seasoning on both sides of mahi mahi
  4. Place mushrooms and fish on baking sheet
  5. Bake for 10 minutes then flip mushrooms and mushrooms over and bake another 10 minutes
  6. Remove from oven and cut fish in half
  7. Sandwich fish between the two mushroom caps

Cajun Shrimp Pepper Nachos

Cajun Shrimp Pepper Nachos

Dietary
Oil Free
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
220
Servings
1
Ingredients

6 oz cooked shrimp
1 t McCormick Cajun Seasoning
1/4 c water
8 oz (2 small) bell peppers, cut into 4-6 slices
4 oz bell peppers, chopped
1/4 t onion powder
pink salt, to taste

Directions
  1. Heat water in skillet over med-high heat
  2. Add 4 oz chopped peppers and cook until softened
  3. Stir in onion powder and cajun seasoning and cook until water is reduced
  4. Cut shrimp into into bite sized pieces and stir into cooked peppers
  5. Arrange pepper slices on plate and scoop shrimp mixture into each slice 
  6. Sprinkle with pink salt

Thanksgiving Baked Chicken or Turkey

Thanksgiving Baked Chicken or Turkey

Dietary
Oil Free
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
170
Servings
1
Ingredients

3.5 oz chicken or turkey breast
½ c Swanson chicken stock
1 T chopped onion

pinch of marjoram
pinch of thyme
pink salt and pepper, to taste 

Directions
  1. Preheat oven to 375 degrees
  2. Mix spices together in small bowl
  3. Dip meat into broth and coat with spices 
  4. Transfer to baking dish

Easy Gravy

Easy Gravy

Dietary
Oil Free
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
15
Servings
2
Ingredients

1 c Swanson chicken stock
1 T minced onion
1 clove of garlic crushed and minced
1 t garlic powder
1/8 t rosemary
1/8 t sage
1/8 t thyme
pinch of nutmeg
pink salt and pepper, to taste
1/4 t xanthan gum

Directions
  1. In a small frying pan combine stock, onion, garlic and spices
  2. Bring to a boil and reduce down until slightly thickened, deglazing with a little water periodically
  3. Remove from heat and whisk in xanthan gum
