Sweet & Sour Turkey Meatballs

Sweet & Sour Turkey Meatballs

Dietary
Oil Free
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
165
Servings
1
Ingredients

3.5 oz ground turkey
2 T minced onion
1 clove of garlic crushed and minced
pinch of garlic powder
pinch of onion powder
pinch of cayenne pepper
1/4 c lemon juice
1 T Bragg’s liquid aminos
stevia, to taste 
1/4 t xanthan gum, optional

Directions
  1. Combine ground turkey with minced garlic, onion and spices
  2. Heat lemon juice in small saucepan
  3. Add aminos and stevia to taste
  4. Form small meatballs and add to saucepan
  5. Place lid on top and simmer for about 10 minutes, flipping meatballs halfway through
  6. Remove meatballs from saucepan and stir in xanthan gum to thicken sauce, if desired

Salted Bittersweet Coconut Chocolate Chip Cookies

Salted Bittersweet Coconut Chocolate Chip Cookies

Dietary
Low Carb
Calories per serving
145
Servings
27
Ingredients

1/3 c coconut flour
2 c almond flour
2/3 c unsweetened shredded coconut 
1 T pink salt
2 large eggs
1/2 c almond butter
1 t vanilla
2 T coconut oil, melted
1/4 c raw honey
1/4 c water
1/2 c plus 27 bittersweet chocolate chips 

Directions
  1. Preheat oven to 350 degrees
  2. Line baking sheet with parchment paper
  3. Mix wet ingredients together except water 
  4. Mix dry ingredients together except chocolate chips and pink salt.
  5. Mix wet ingredients into dry until dough is stiff
  6. Add water until moist but still firm
  7. Fold in chocolate chips except the 27
  8. Pinch dough into 27 pieces and place on baking sheet 
  9. Flatten out each cookie with back of fork
  10. Place a chocolate chip into center of each cookie
  11. Bake for 12 minutes
  12. Remove from oven and sprinkle with pink salt

Bison Feta Zucchini Burger

Bison Feta Zucchini Burger

Dietary

Low Carb

2

Directions

  2. Wring liquid from grated zucchini and onion in a dish towel

Crispy Cauliflower Buffalo "Wings"

Crispy Cauliflower Buffalo "Wings"

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
111
Servings
4
Ingredients

1 medium head cauliflower, chopped into bite-size pieces
1/2 c coconut flour
1/2 c water
1 t garlic powder
1/2 t pink salt
1 t melted coconut butter/oil or butter
2/3 c hot sauce

Directions
  1. Preheat oven to 450ºF
  2. In a medium-sized bowl, combine flour, water, garlic powder, and salt
  3. Whisk together until combined and breadcrumb-like consistency batter
  4. Toss cauliflower into batter, making sure to coat each piece completely, then place battered cauliflower on a lightly greased, nonstick baking sheet
  5. Bake for 15 minutes, tossing halfway through
  6. In the meantime, combine melted butter and hot sauce in a large bowl, regularly stirring
  7. When cauliflower is done, remove it from oven and gently toss it in hot sauce mixture
  8. Place cauliflower back on baking sheet and cook for an additional 25 minutes until it becomes crispy
  9. Allow cauliflower to cool for 15 minutes before serving

Mushroom Stroganoff

Mushroom Stroganoff

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
165
Servings
2
Ingredients

1 T coconut oil
16 oz sliced mushrooms
2 T minced garlic
2 T minced onion
2 T nutritional yeast
pink salt and pepper, to taste
2 t grated parmesan cheese

Directions
  1. Melt coconut oil over med-high heat in skillet
  2. Add mushrooms, garlic, and onions and cook until mushrooms are soft
  3. Stir in nutritional yeast and pepper and continue to heat until liquid cooks down
  4. Remove from heat and stir in parmesan cheese and pink salt

*Excellent served on top of zucchini or cucumber "noodles"

Cajun Coconut Shrimp

Cajun Coconut Shrimp

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
412
Servings
1
Ingredients

1.5 t cajun seasoning
1/8 t pink salt
1/8 t pepper
1 t sesame oil
1 egg
3 T unsweetened shredded coconut
7 oz raw tail-on shrimp

Directions
  1. Preheat air fryer to 180 degrees C or oven to 350 degrees F
  2. In a small bowl, whisk egg, cajun seasoning, oil, salt and pepper
  3. Place shredded coconut in separate small bowl
  4. Dip shrimp into egg mixture, then press one shrimp at a time in the shredded coconut until well coated
  5. Place shrimp on parchment lined baking sheet or in parchment lined air fryer basket
  6. Cook shrimp for 10 minutes, then flip and bake for another 5 minutes until slightly browned

    *Excellent served with Curry Lime Dipping Sauce

Chocolate Nut Butter Cake

Chocolate Nut Butter Cake

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
260
Servings
8
Ingredients

1 c. nut butter of choice (if using peanut butter, this is a P5/6 recipe)
2 medium ripe bananas 
2 eggs
1 tsp. vanilla
2 tsp. liquid stevia (or more if sweeter cake is desired)
1/4 c. unsweetened cocoa powder
1/2 tsp. baking soda
1 tsp. apple cider vinegar

Directions
  1. Preheat oven to 400 degrees and grease 8" cake pan.
  2. Place all ingredients into food processor.
  3. Blend until well mixed.
  4. Pour batter into cake pan.
  5. Bake for 25-30 minutes, or until toothpick inserted in center of cake comes out clean.

Vegan Cheese Sauce

Vegan Cheese Sauce

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
62
Servings
4
Ingredients

1 t garlic powder
6 T Bragg's Nutritional Yeast
1 t onion powder
1 T coconut oil
2 t dijon mustard
3/4 c unsweetened almond milk
1 T coconut flour
pink salt and pepper, to taste
1/4 t xanthan gum

Directions
  1. Melt coconut oil in saucepan over med-high heat
  2. Whisk coconut flour and almond milk together in small bowl then add to saucepan
  3. Whisk in nutritional yeast and reduce heat to med-low
  4. Stir in mustard and spices and whisk frequently while cooking another 5 minutes until sauce has thickened
  5. Remove from heat and whisk in xanthan gum

Nacho Kale Chips

Nacho Kale Chips

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
112
Servings
4
Ingredients

1 large bunch kale
1 T olive oil
4 T Braggs nutritional yeast
pink salt

Directions
  1. Break kale into chip sized pieces
  2. Toss kale in olive oil
  3. Sprinkle with pink salt and nutritional yeast and stir to coat thoroughly
  4. Place single layer of kale in basket of air fryer
  5. Cook for 5 minutes at 200 degrees, then toss and cook another 5 minutes (or until crispy) 
    *May be baked in oven on parchment paper at 275 degrees for 20 minutes, turning kale halfway through, instead of in air fryer
  6. Repeat until all the kale is cooked
  7. Store in brown paper bag, tupperware, or ziplock bag

Cottage Cheese Tzatziki

Cottage Cheese Tzatziki

Dietary
Oil Free
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
85
Servings
4
Ingredients

1 1/2 c. Daisy cottage cheese
8 oz. cucumber, shredded
1 T. minced garlic
2 T. lemon juice
1 T. dill
pink salt and pepper, to taste

Directions
  1. Place shredded cucumber in collander in dish towel and wring out as much water as possible
  2. Add cottage cheese, garlic, lemon juice, dill, salt and pepper to food processor
  3. Process until smooth and creamy
  4. Add in cucumber and pulse/process until well combined
  5. Serve immediately (does not store well for more than a few hours in the fridge b/c water from the cucumbers starts to settle on the bottom)

    *If using this as a P2 recipe, you may have 2 servings of Tzatziki along with 4 oz cucumber slices to count as your protein and veggie (194 calories)

No-tato Tomato Salad

No-tato Tomato Salad

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
60
Servings
2
Ingredients

10 oz radishes
2 T full-fat plain greek yogurt
2 T Daisy cottage cheese
6 grape tomatoes
1 t apple cider vinegar
3 t dijon mustard
1.5 t dill
pink salt and pepper, to taste

Directions
  1. Chop radishes into small cubes
  2. Boil in a medium saucepan until soft when piercing with a fork
  3. Drain with collander and rinse with cold water
  4. Transfer to bowl
  5. Slice tomatoes into rounds and add to bowl
  6. Stir in yogurt, cottage cheese, apple cider vinegar, mustard, dill, salt and pepper

Cabbage Shrimp Stirfry with Egg

Cabbage Shrimp Stirfry with Egg

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
365
Servings
1
Ingredients

Buffalo Chicken Quinoa Salad

Buffalo Chicken Quinoa Salad

Dietary
Low Carb
Calories per serving
222
Servings
5
Ingredients

½ c quinoa
1 c water
1 (12.5 oz) can chicken breast in water (or 1.5 c cooked chicken breast)
1 c chopped celery
1 c shredded carrots
1 c shredded cabbage (red or green)
¼ c goat cheese crumbles
½ c hot sauce
2 T olive oil

Directions
  1. Place quinoa and water in small saucepan and bring to boil
  2. Cover with lid and reduce to simmer for 15 minutes
  3. Combine chicken, celery, carrots, cabbage, and goat cheese in bowl
  4. Combine hot sauce and olive oil together then pour over bowl
  5. Fluff quinoa with fork after cooked then stir into bowl
  6. Serve warm or cold

Creamed Spinach

Creamed Spinach

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
150
Servings
1
Ingredients

5 c baby spinach
2 T nutritional yeast
1/4 c plain kefir
1/4-1/2 t garlic powder
pink salt and pepper, to taste
1/4-1/2 t xanthan gum

Directions
  1. Steam spinach in saucepan with about 1/4 c water then drain
  2. Stir in nutritional yeast, kefir, garlic powder, pink salt, and pepper
  3. Remove from heat and stir in 1/4 t xanthan gum (stir in additional xanthan gum if you desire a thicker sauce)

Cheeseburger Scalloped No-tatoes

Cheeseburger Scalloped No-tatoes

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
401
Servings
2
Ingredients

8 oz lean ground beef
1/4 c onion, minced
16 oz bag radishes
1 T coconut oil
1 c unsweetened almond milk
1 T coconut flour
6 T nutritional yeast
2 t dijon mustard
1/4 t garlic powder
1/4 t onion powder
1/4 -1/2 t pink salt
pepper, to taste

Directions
  1. Slice radishes thin, size of scalloped potato slices
  2. Place in NuWave oven on foil and cook for 10-15 minutes (or bake at 350 for 15-20 minutes)
  3. Brown beef and onions in skillet over med-high heat
  4. Melt coconut oil in small saucepan
  5. Whisk almond milk and coconut flour together then stir into coconut oil
  6. Stir in nutritional yeast then bring to a simmer
  7. Stir in dijon mustard, garlic powder, onion powder, pink salt, and pepper
  8. Simmer for 5 minutes
  9. Remove radishes from oven and stir into beef and onions
  10. Pour sauce into skillet and cook down until non-soupy consistency is reached

Dietary
Oil Free
Sugar Free
Low Carb

Chocolate Chip Cookies

Chocolate Chip Cookies

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
55
Servings
36
Ingredients

4 bananas, mashed
1/2 c flax meal
1/2 c coconut flour
1/4 c almond butter
2/3 c unsweetened applesauce
1 t vanilla
1/4 c cocoa powder
1/4 c coconut oil
stevia, to taste

Directions
  1. Line baking sheets with parchment paper
  2. Melt coconut oil
  3. Mix in cocoa powder and stevia
  4. Pour into square or rectangular tupperware container then place into freezer
  5. Combine bananas, flax meal, coconut flour, almond butter, applesauce, vanilla, and stevia (if desired) in food processor until mixed together
  6. Remove coconut oil chocolate from freezer and pop out of tupperware onto sheet of saran wrap or foil
  7. Wrap chocolate in saran wrap or foil then break into small pieces with fingers or crush with spoon
  8. Stir chocolate piece into cookie dough
  9. Chill dough in refrigerator for 30 minutes
  10. Preheat oven to 350 degrees
  11. Spoon out scoops of 1 tablespoon dough (yields 3 dozen)
  12. Bake for 15 minutes

Double Chocolate Glazed Donuts

Double Chocolate Glazed Donuts

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
255
Servings
8
Ingredients

Donuts:
1/4 c coconut flour
1/4 c flax meal
2 T cocoa powder
4 eggs
1/2 c coconut oil
1/4 t baking soda
1/4 t pink salt
1 t stevia extract

Glaze:
1/4 c coconut oil
2 T cocoa powder
1/2 t stevia extract

Directions
  1. Preheat oven to 350 degrees
  2. Grease donut pan
  3. Combine coconut flour, flax meal, cocoa powder, baking soda, salt, and stevia in small bowl
  4. Whisk eggs in mixing bowl
  5. Stir dry mixture into eggs
  6. Stir in coconut oil
  7. Pour into donut pan
  8. Bake for 20 minutes
  9. Combine all glaze ingredients and set aside
  10. Remove donuts from oven and allow to cool completely
  11. Drizzle glaze over each donut
  12. Place in refrigerator until glaze is hardened

Apple Pie Loaf

Dietary
Low Carb
Calories per serving
180
Servings
10

Cheesesteak Stuffed Peppers

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
560
Servings
4
Ingredients

3 T olive oil 
pink salt and pepper, to taste

Directions
  1. Preheat oven to 400 degrees
  2. Prebake peppers on parchment line baking sheet for 10 minutes
  3. Slice pepperin half lengthwise, remove ribs and seeds

Crockpot Apple Butter

Crockpot Apple Butter

Dietary
Oil Free
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
30
Servings
24 (2 T/serving)
Ingredients

3 lbs apples
1 t cinnamon
1/2 t ginger
1/4 t cloves
1/4 c water

Directions
  1. Heat crockpot to low
  2. Chop and core apples then place into crockpot
  3. Add spices and water to apples and cover with lid
  4. Cook for 6 hours
  5. Transfer apples to blender/food processor (or use an immersion blender) to puree
  6. Transfer back to crockpot
  7. Loosely cover with lid, allowing steam to escape, and cook 6-8 more hours (or until mixture is reduced by nearly half)
  8. Transfer to glass jar(s) and store in refrigerator for up to 2 weeks
  9. Note: You may use 3 servings (6T) if you want to count this as your fruit in P2 or you may use 1 serving (2T) along with ½ of an apple cut into slices

Nut Flour Hamburger Buns

Nut Flour Hamburger Buns

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
525
Servings
4
Ingredients

1 1/2 c raw cashews
3 eggs
3/4 t apple cider vinegar
1/4 c unsweetened almond milk
1/4 c coconut oil, softened
1/3 c coconut flour
1/3 c almond flour
1 t pink salt
1 t baking soda
1 egg yolk
2 t unsweetened almond milk
1 t sesame seeds or chia seeds

Directions
  1. Preheat the oven to 325 degrees
  2. Line baking sheet with parchment paper
  3. Place cashews in food processor and process for 10 seconds, until ground course 
  4. Add the eggs, vinegar, milk, and coconut oil and process until smooth, about 30 seconds 
  5. Add flours, salt, and baking soda and process again until smooth, sticky dough has formed
  6. Using wet hands, shape the dough into 4 buns
  7. Place the egg yolk and 2 t almond milk in a small bowl and whisk
  8. Brush dough with the egg wash and sprinkle with seeds
  9. Place buns on a baking sheet and bake for 25 minutes

Carrot Cake Custard

Carrot Cake Custard

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
215
Servings
4
Ingredients

1/3 c liquid egg whites
2 eggs

1/2 c canned coconut cream
4 t pumpkin pie spice
2 t vanilla extract
1 t stevia

Directions

  5. Bake for 40 minutes or until a knife comes out clean

Raisin Paste

Raisin paste is great if you are on a budget and want a great substitute for date paste, or just love this delicious low sugar sweetener. Get started now by getting out those Sun-Maid raisins. We used a Vitamix blender in this video but we also recommend any food processor that you think will do the job.

Jump To Recipe

What is Raisin Paste

Raisin paste is made from raisins that you soak in hot water. After about 10 minutes you then blend them until they have very fine creamy texture... almost like peanut butter. Since raisins have a decent amount of natural sugar they are fairly sweet. This makes raisin paste great for adding sweetness to your desserts without adding the calories. Try a scoop on top of vanilla ice cream or on one of your favorite breads. You can also use raisin paste in baked goods like muffins or scones to sweeten them up. I could see adding this raisin paste recipe to the center of a croissant, making this recipe a great substitute for medjool dates in baking. One of my all time favorite ways to use this raisin paste recipe is to add it to a nice healthy green smoothie in order to make it more sweet. 

Health benefits of using Raisin Paste

Raisins have natural sugars and good carbohydrates, and tons of fiber giving the body a quick boost of dietary energy. 2 oz. of raisins contains 1 gram of Iron. Iron is an essential mineral in blood oxygen circulation and immune system support. Potassium is also a component of the paste. It's good for the muscles, nervous system and helps with lowering your blood pressure. They also contain Iron, Calcium and tons of antioxidants that can help remove free radicals from your blood and may prevent damage to your cells.

 

Raisins are a healthy date substitute

Let's face it dates are expensive. Raisins are not. You know what else you don't have to do with raisins? You don't have to take out the pits. No sticky hands, no pairing knife... you get the picture. But are raisins actually a "good" substitute for dates? Meaning there has to be a reason why healthy folks have been recommending dates right? Here is a good breakdown from Pink Villa that compares dates vs. raisins: Date vs Raisins: Health benefits and the difference between the two. Shockingly, the takeaway from the article is that raisins are actually healthier. This makes them one of natures best dates substitute. The main reason being that raisins have a higher content of iron, vitamin C, vitamin B2, copper, and potassium. Wow, there you have it. You can save a bunch of money using raisins instead of dates in your recipes now too!

You can use raisins as a replacement for dates in recipe

News flash: Medjool dates are healthy! Chalked full of natural sugar, while maintaining a low/medium glycemic index score due to high fiber content. On top of that, they are really low in fat and have a ton of vitamins and nutrition. However, they are often quite expensive, which often sends people looking for a replacement for dates in recipe. Specifically, they are looking for a medjool dates substitute. That's why you see a lot of raisin paste recipes these days... like this one!

So look no further, you have come to the right place. You no longer have to type in to google: "raisin paste where to buy", because you can now make it yourself. Thanks for taking the time to learn how to make this super easy raisin paste recipe! We hope you share this with your friends. My son even made this recipe and he had a blast do so. Please check out his channel on YouTube or watch the video above. It's super cute.

Raisin Paste

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
18
Servings
36 (2 teaspoons/serving)
Ingredients
  • 1 1/2 c raisins
  • hot water
Directions
  1. Place raisins in bowl
  2. Pour water over raisins, just enough to cover them
  3. Wait 10 minutes
  4. Reserve ¼ cup raisin water and drain
  5. Transfer to food processor
  6. Process until you have a thick paste
  7. Add water, one tablespoon at a time, until you have a smooth peanut butter like consistency
  8. Store in the refrigerator up to 3 weeks (Can also freeze raisin paste into cubes and be kept in the freezer for months
    * Can use 2 teaspoons of raisin paste for each date called for in most recipes

  2. Microwave for 1 minute 30 seconds (or bake at 375 degrees for 10 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean)

Onion Crackers (or Flatbread)

Onion Crackers (or Flatbread)

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
40
Servings
30
Ingredients

3 large sweet white onions (2.5-3 pounds of walla walla, vidalia, maui sweets, etc.)
1 c ground sunflower seeds 
1 c ground chia seeds (or ground flax seeds)
1/3 c olive oil
3 1/2 T coconut aminos (or Bragg’s liquid aminos)
1/2 t pink salt

Directions
  1. Preheat oven to 125 degrees
  2. Peel & chop onions
  3. Transfer to food processor and pulse until small, but not mushy
  4. Add ground flax (or chia) seeds & ground sunflower seeds
  5. Pulse a few times to incorporate
  6. Add olive oil, coconut aminos, and salt
  7. Pulse to incorporate
  8. Spread onto dehydrator teflex sheets or parchment paper at about 1/4″ thickness
  9. Dehydrate for 1 hour at 125 degrees, then reduce to 115 degrees and dry for another 8-24 hours, flipping over once and discarding teflex or parchment
  10. Once dough starts drying out and holding together, score with a knife into 30 pieces

Key Lime Pie Bites (Bombs)

Key Lime Pie Bites (Bombs)

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
170
Servings
12
Ingredients

Crust:
1 c almond flour

Filling:
¼ c coconut oil

Peach Iced Tea

Peach Iced Tea

Dietary
Oil Free
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
5
Servings
16 (8 oz/serving)
Ingredients

1 large, ripe peach
1 gallon water 
4 - 6 tea bags - white tea, pear, peach, or similar bags of white/light tea (not green tea, oolong, or black tea)
3 dropperfuls of plain stevia (or to taste)

Directions
  1. Fill large pot with water
  2. Add whole peach (with skin and pit - drop the whole thing in the pot)
  3. Bring to a boil
  4. Turn heat down so it is boiling but not bubbling over, and cook for about 30 minutes
  5. Cut up peach, discarding pit, and return coarsely diced peach and skin to pot
  6. Simmer another 10 minutes or until peach starts to fall apart
  7. Add 4-6 tea bags of any light or white tea
  8. Turn off burner and steep 10 minutes 
  9. Remove tea bags & discard
  10. In small batches, transfer liquid and solid bits of peach to blender or nutri bullet
  11. Blend thoroughly, in batches, until well pureed
  12. Pour into a 1-gallon container
  13. Add 3 dropperfuls of plain stevia and enough water to fill up the gallon
  14. Chill and serve over ice

Banana Bread Muffins

Banana Bread Muffins

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
121
Servings
12
Ingredients

4 ripe bananas
4 eggs
1/2 cup almonds
2 T coconut oil
1 t vanilla
1/2 c coconut flour
2 t cinnamon
1/2 t pumpkin pie spice
1 t baking powder
1 t baking soda
1/4 t salt

Directions
  1. Preheat oven to 350 degrees 
  2. Line a muffin tins with cups (or grease a bread pan for banana bread)
  3. In power blender, add almonds and coconut oil
  4. Process until almond butter consistency is reached
  5. Add bananas, eggs, and vanilla and process until combined
  6. Add in the coconut flour, cinnamon, nutmeg, baking powder, baking soda, and salt, scraping down the sides with a spatula
  7. Distribute the batter evenly into the lined muffin tins, filling each about two-thirds of the way full or into bread pan
  8. Bake for 20-25 minutes (35-40 minutes for loaf) or until a toothpick comes out clean
  9. Serve warm or store in the refrigerator in a resealable bag

Moroccan Fish with Apples & Onions

Moroccan Fish with Apples & Onions

Dietary
Oil Free
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
290
Servings
1
Ingredients

1 (5 oz) onion
1 apple
4.5 oz cod (or other fish of choice)
1 T Bragg's liquid aminos or coconut aminos
1 t Moroccan spices
1/2 t Pumpkin pie spice/cinnamon
Pink salt, to taste

Directions
  1. Preheat oven to 400 degrees
  2. Remove paper skin from onion & slice off the top
  3. Poke holes in top with a knife
  4. Place onion in small baking dish & slowly dribble with liquid aminos (You don't want the liquid in the baking dish; you want it in the onion)
  5. Cover with tin foil & place in oven for 45 minutes
  6. Drizzle fish with liquid aminos then liberally sprinkle with Moroccan spices on both sides
  7. Place in small baking dish
  8. Cut up half the apple into small chunks and place around and on top of fish
  9. Dust lightly with pumpkin pie spice and/or cinnamon
  10. Cover with tin foil
  11. Cut up the other half of the apple in similar chunks & sprinkle lightly with pink salt then set aside
  12. When the 45 minutes is done, leave the onion in the oven and place the fish/apple dish in as well
  13. Bake 15 minutes then remove both dishes from oven
  14. Cut the onion into pieces on a plate
  15. Carefully remove fish and apples with a fish spatula and place on top of onions
  16. Sprinkle uncooked apple pieces on top

Dietary
Oil Free
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
n/a
Servings
n/a
Ingredients

1 bar Simply Ivory soap (or other bar soap of choice)
3 qts water

Directions
  1. Grate/shred bar of soap into water in large saucepan over med-high heat
  2. Heat while stirring constantly until soap is completely dissovled

Coconut Snowball Bites (Bombs)

Coconut Snowball Bites (Bombs)

Dietary
Low Carb
Calories per serving
113
Servings
14
Ingredients

1/2 cup coconut oil
3/4 cup canned coconut milk, full fat
3/4 cup shredded unsweetened coconut, divided
1 tsp vanilla extract
1 tsp pumpkin pie spice
3 dropperfuls stevia

Directions
  1. In double broiler, combine coconut oil, coconut milk, vanilla, pumpkin pie spice, and stevia
  2. Heat until melted and mixed together
  3. Stir in 1/4 c shredded coconut
  4. Place mixture in refrigerator for about 30 minutes (until moldable, but not solid)
  5. Spoon out mixture by heaping tablespoon at a time
  6. Roll into balls
  7. Roll ball in remaining 1/2 c shredded coconut to coat 
  8. Place in refrigerator or freezer until hardened and for storage

Chickpea Pizza Crust

Chickpea Pizza Crust

Dietary
Low Carb
Calories per serving
278 (without toppings)
Servings
8
Ingredients

1 1/2 c shredded mozzarella cheese
1 1/2 c almond flour
1/4 c garbanzo bean (chickpea) flour
1/4 c flax meal
1 t onion powder
1/2 t garlic powder
1/2 t pink salt
2 eggs
1/4 c olive oil
1/2 c water

Directions
  1. Preheat oven to 350 degrees
  2. Shred cheese - or pulse it in a food processor until it becomes granular
  3. In large bowl, combine mozzarella, almonds, garbanzo bean flour, flax meal, onion powder, garlic powder, and salt
  4. Stir in eggs, oil, and water and mix thoroughly
  5. Spread a sheet of parchment paper over a baking sheet/pizza stone (If using a baking pan, it's easier to use the back of the pan) 
  6. Place dough on parchment paper and lay a second sheet of parchment paper on top of dough
  7. Flatten with a rolling pin into a 14" round
  8. Carefully remove top layer of parchment paper
  9. Use a spoon or hands to form a crust edge
  10. Bake for 20 minutes
  11. Remove from oven and top with sauce and pizza toppings
  12. Bake for an additional 10 minutes or until cheese is melted

Cauliflower Crust Stromboli

Cauliflower Crust Stromboli

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
530
Servings
1
Ingredients

1 small head cauliflower (3 c cauliflower rice)
1 egg
1 c freshly shredded mozzarella cheese (divided)
1/2 t pink salt
1/2 t oregano
1/4 t pepper
1/4 c tomato sauce
1/4 c chicken breast (or other meat/toppings of choice)
Parmesan cheese, optional

Directions
  1. Preheat oven to 450°F
  2. Line a baking sheet with parchment paper, grease then set aside
  3. In a food processor, rice cauliflower florets
  4. Transfer cauliflower rice (3 cups) to a microwave-safe dish and microwave on high for 8 minutes, until cooked or steam on stovetop
  5. Place cauliflower rice in a tea towel and twist it to squeeze as much moisture as possible
  6. Transfer cauliflower rice to a mixing bowl, add egg, 1/2 c mozzarella, oregano, salt and pepper and mix well
  7. Spread cauliflower mixture onto lined baking sheet and form into a large rectangle
  8. Bake for 10 minutes 
  9. Remove from oven
  10. Spread tomato sauce over most of the dough, leaving a 2-inch border on one side
  11. Spread 1/4 c mozzarella, then the meat/toppings, then the remaining cheese.
  12. With large spatula lift the longer sides of the crust and roll into stromboli shape 
  13. Flip seam down and tuck/fold the shorter side to close the stromboli.
  14. Cut slats in the top 
  15. Sprinkle with grated Parmesan and oregano, if desired
  16. Bake for an additional 12 minutes
  17. Cool a few minutes before slicing and serving

Spinach-Cauli Cup Eggs

Spinach-Cauli Cup Eggs

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
85
Servings
12
Ingredients

1 small head cauliflower 
4 oz spinach

Pink salt and pepper, to taste
12 eggs

Directions
  1. Preheat oven to 400 degrees
  2. Boil cauliflower until just about soft, drain
  3. In a food processor blend cauliflower, spinach and mozzarella cheese
  4. Place about 1/4 to 1/3 cup mixture in a cupcake tin
  5. Press mixture up the sides of cupcake tin to form a cup

Salted Dark Chocolate Truffles

Salted Dark Chocolate Truffles

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
45
Servings
3
Ingredients

1 T coconut oil, melted
pink salt, to taste
1 T unsweetened cacao/cocoa powder
1-3 t unsweetened almond milk
stevia, to taste

Directions
  1. Place liners into 3 mini muffin tins
  2. Combine coconut oil, 1/2 T cocoa powder, a couple shakes of pink salt, and stevia 
  3. Pour just enough of mixute into each muffin tin so bottom is covered
  4. Place muffin tray into freezer
  5. Combine remaining 1/2 T cocoa powder and stevia, to taste in small dish
  6. Stir in enough almond milk that mixture thickens into a paste-like, creamy chocolate
  7. Remove muffin tray from freezer
  8. Spoon a small dallop on chocolate paste into each muffin tin
  9. Pour remaining melted chocolate mixture into each muffin tin so paste is completely covered
  10. Return tray to freezer until outside chocolate has hardened
  11. Store in refrigerator until ready to eat

Black & White Coconut Flour Cake

Black & White Coconut Flour Cake

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
230
Servings
8
Ingredients

1/2 c coconut flour
1/2 t baking powder
1/4 t pink salt
4 eggs
1 t vanilla stevia
1/3 c coconut oil, warmed until melted 
2 T unsweetened almond milk
2 t vanilla extract
1 c coconut cream (can refrigerated overnight)
1 oz cream cheese (softened)
3 T unsweetened cocoa powder
stevia, to taste

Directions
  1. Preheat oven to 350 degrees
  2. Grease small round cake pan
  3. In a large bowl, whisk coconut flour, baking powder, and salt until blended
  4. Whisk in eggs, stevia, coconut oil, almond milk, and vanilla until completely smooth
  5. Pour batter into cake pan
  6. Bake 35 minutes or until golden and a toothpick inserted in the center comes out clean
  7. Whip coconut cream with hand mixer in small bowl until stiff peaks are formed
  8. Whip in cream cheese
  9. Stir in stevia and cocoa powder
  10. Place frosting in fridge until ready to put on cake
  11. Transfer cake pan to wire rack and cool completely before frosting

Chai Pumpkin Bar

Chai Pumpkin Bar

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
155
Servings
24
Ingredients

1 c almond butter
1 c canned pumpkin
2 ripe bananas
4 eggs
3 Chai tea bags
1 T coconut oil
5 T coconut flour
1/2 T pumpkin pie spice
1/4 t cloves
1/8 t ginger
1 t baking powder
1 t baking soda
pinch of pink salt
8 oz cream cheese, softened
1 c coconut cream (can refrigerated overnight)
2 t vanilla extract
3 dropperfuls stevia (or vanilla stevia)
1/4 t ginger
1/4 t cloves
1/2 t cinnamon

Directions
  1. Preheat oven to 350 degrees 
  2. Combine almond butter, pumpkin, eggs, and bananas in food processor/blender
  3. Cut tea bags open and pour into mixture along with coconut oil, pie spice, cloves, ginger, baking soda, baking powder, salt, and coconut flour
  4. Process until well combined
  5. Pour into greased 13x9 inch casserole dish
  6. Bake for 25 minutes or until toothpick inserted comes out clean
  7. Remove and allow to cool completely before frosting
  8. Whip coconut cream in bowl with hand mixer until stiff peaks form
  9. In separate bowl, cream together cream cheese, ginger, cloves, cinnamon, vanilla, and stevia
  10. Fold whipped coconut cream into cream cheese mixture
  11. Spread frosting onto pumpkin bar with a spatula
  12. Refrigerate until ready to serve

Low Carb
Calories per serving

Servings

Rainbow Citrus Slaw

Rainbow Citrus Slaw

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
138
Servings
6
Ingredients

8 carrots, shredded
1 zucchini, shredded
6 stalks celery, shredded
1/4 c chopped red onion (optional)
4 T parsley
1 t celery seed
1 c avocado
1/4 c lime juice
1 T olive oil
1 T apple cider vinegar
1 c plain kefir
1/2 t pink salt
1/4 t pepper
1/4 t liquid stevia

Directions
  1. Combine carrots, zucchini, celery, parsley, celery seed, and onion (if desired) in a medium mixing bowl
  2. Place avocado, lime juice, olive oil, vinegar, kefir, salt, pepper, and stevia in blender or Magic Bullet and pulse until dressing is smooth and creamy

  4. Cover and place in fridge until ready to eat

Cherry Pecan Bites (Bombs)

Cherry Pecan Bites (Bombs)

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
225
Servings
8
Ingredients

Almond Joy Bites (Bombs)

Almond Joy Bites (Bombs)

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
185
Servings
24
Ingredients

Coconut filling:
1 c coconut oil 
2/3 c unsweetened coconut flakes
3 dropperfuls coconut stevia
24 almonds

Chocolate coating:
1 c coconut oil 
3 T cocoa powder 
3 T almond butter 
2 dropperfuls chocolate stevia

Directions
  1. On stovetop, melt 4 chocolate coating ingredients together (co, cocoa powder, almond butter, stevia).
  2. Transfer to pitcher with pour spout and barely fill bottom of 24 mini muffin tins with small amount.
  3. Chill muffin tin with chocolate in fridge about 10 min, keeping remaining chocolate out. 
  4. Mix together 3 coconut filling ingredients (co, coconut flakes, stevia) in food processor then set aside. 
  5. When chocolate is set in muffin tins, remove from fridge and top with a spoonful of coconut filling.
  6. Plase a single whole almond on top of coconut filling.
  7. Chill for 10 minutes in fridge.
  8. Pour remaining chocolate on top of each muffin tin.
  9. Chill in fridge 10 min.
  10. Remove from fridge and pop each bite out of tin.
  11. Store in Tupperware in fridge. (Thaw before eating)

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
175
Servings
4
Ingredients

Base:

Topping:
1/2 c almond flour

1 t cinnamon 
1 1/2 T coconut oil, room temp

Directions

Dietary

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving

Servings
16
Ingredients

Spinach Pizza Crust

Spinach Pizza Crust

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
397
Servings
1 crust
Ingredients

2 c spinach (fresh or frozen)
1 egg 
1 c freshly shredded mozzarella cheese
pink salt and pepper, to taste
additional spices (optional)
 

Directions
  1. Preheat oven to 425 degrees
  2. Line pizza pan with parchment paper 
  3. If using frozen spinach: defrost then place in tea towel or cheese cloth and wring out as much water as possible
  4. In blender or food processor blend spinach until it is well pureed
  5. Add egg and pulse until combined
  6. Add cheese, salt, pepper, and other spices and pulse until just combined
  7. Spread evenly on prepared pizza pan
  8. Bake for 15 minutes or until edges are browned and crispy
  9. Flip crust and bake for an additional 5-7 minutes
  10. (After baking crust, top with sauce, cheese and choice of toppings then return to oven to bake until cheese is melted)

Mock Pancake Syrup

Mock Pancake Syrup

Dietary
Oil Free
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
10
Servings
1 batch
Ingredients

1 c. warm water
1 dropperful SweetLeaf English Toffee stevia
1/2 tsp. cinnamon

Directions
  1. Over medium heat, combine water, stevia, and cinnamon in small saucepan with whisk.

Coconut Flour Flax Pancakes

Coconut Flour Flax Pancakes

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
250
Servings
1
Ingredients

4 T egg whites
1 egg
1/4 c unsweetened almond milk
1/8 t baking soda + 1/2 t vinegar (or 1/2 t baking powder)
1/4 t cinnamon
1/2 t vanilla, if desired
2 T flax meal
2 T coconut flour

Directions
  1. Heat skillet to med-high 
  2. Whisk eggs and almond milk in liquid measuring cup with pour spout until well combined
  3. Stir in baking soda/vinegar (or baking powder), cinnamon, and vanilla, if desired
  4. Stir in coconut flour annd flax meal
  5. Lightly grease skillet
  6. Pour pancake sized amount of batter into skillet
  7. Allow to cook on one side until fluffy and bubbly in center
  8. Flip and cook on other side

*These are AWESOME served with Coconut Butter spread on top and Mock Pancake Syrup!

Coconut Flour Banana Pancakes

Coconut Flour Banana Pancakes

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
217
Servings
1
Ingredients

1 banana
1 egg
1 T egg whites
1 T coconut flour

  5. Stir in coconut flour
  6. Lightly grease skillet
  7. Pour pancake sized amount of batter into skillet
  8. Allow to cook on one side until fluffy and bubbly in center
  9. Flip and cook on other side

Carrot Cake Muffins

Carrot Cake Muffins

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
159
Servings
24
Ingredients

2 c almond flour
1/4 c shredded unsweetened coconut
2 t baking soda
1 t pink salt
1 T cinnamon
1 c raisins
3 ripe bananas
3 eggs
1 t apple cider vinegar
1/4 c coconut oil
2 large carrots, shredded
1 c coarsely chopped walnuts

Directions
  1. Preheat oven to 350 degrees
  2. Line muffin tins
  3. Combine almond flour, coconut, baking soda, salt, and cinnamon in large mixing bowl with whisk
  4. Place raisins, bananas, eggs, vinegar, and coconut oil in bowl of food processor and process until smooth
  5. Add flour mixture to food processor and pulse until just combined
  6. Transfer batter to large mixing bowl
  7. Fold in carrots and nuts
  8. Fill muffin tins about 2/3 full
  9. Bake about 25 mintures
  10. Cool on wire rack
  11. Store, covered, in refrigerator

Veggie Quiche

Veggie Quiche

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
255
Servings
8
Ingredients

1 Coconut Flour Pie Crust
1.5 c sliced mushrooms (fresh or frozen)
1.5 c chopped green peppers (fresh or frozen)
1/2 6oz bag baby spinach
4 eggs
3/4 c unsweetened almond milk
5 oz chevre goat cheese
3 oz mozzarella cheese, shredded
1/2 T coconut oil
1 t minced garlic
1 T parsley
1/2 t pink salt
1/2 t pepper
additional spices (optional)

Directions
  1. Preheat oven to 400 degrees
  2. Melt coconut oil in skillet
  3. Add mushrooms, peppers, and spinach and cook until soft
  4. Drain liquid from skillet and set aside
  5. Whisk eggs, milk, parsley, garlic, salt, black pepper, and any additional spices in a bowl
  6. Gently combine goat cheese into veggie mixture 
  7. Spread veggie/cheese mixture in prepared pie crust
  8. Pour egg mixture evenly over the filling
  9. Top with shredded mozzarella cheese
  10.  Bake in preheated oven until the quiche is lightly puffed and browned, 45 to 50 minutes (Toothpick inserted into the center of the filling should come out clean)
  11. Cool for 30 minutes before serving

Coconut Flour Pie Crust

Coconut Flour Pie Crust

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
185
Servings
8
Ingredients

1/2 c. coconut oil
2 eggs
1/4 tsp. pink salt
3/4 c. coconut flour
1-2 dropperfuls SweetLeaf stevia

Directions
  1. Preheat oven to 400 degrees.
  2. Melt coconut oil.
  3. In medium bowl, mix oil, eggs, stevia, and salt together with a fork.

Vanilla Cacao Nib Layer Cake w/ Chocolate Frosting

Vanilla Cacao Nib Layer Cake w/ Chocolate Frosting

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
315
Servings
8
Ingredients

1 c cashew flour (or almond flour)
1/4 c coconut flour
1/8 t salt
1/2 t baking soda
2 eggs
1/3 c unsweetened applesauce
1/3 c coconut oil
1/3 c canned coconut milk 
1 T pure vanilla extract
2 T cacao nibs
1 batch Chocolate Cream Cheese Frosting

Directions
  1. Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
  2. Grease 2 (7 inch) round cake pans or line with parchment paper.
  3. Combine cashew/almond flour, coconut flour, salt, and baking soda in a bowl.
  4. In separate mixing bowl, beat eggs lightly.
  5. Add applesauce, coconut oil, coconut milk, and vanilla and beat lightly.
  6. Add dry ingredients and mix until just combined, being careful not to over mix.
  7. Pour batter into cake pans.
  8. Bake 35-40 minutes, until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
  9. Flip cakes over onto cooling rack and remove from pans.
  10. Allow to cool fully while making Chocolate Cream Cheese Frosting.
  11. Transfer bottom cake layer onto plate and frost top.
  12. In small bowl, mix stevia and cacao nibs together.
  13. Sprinkle 1 1/2 tablespoons cacao nibs on top of frosting.
  14. Place top cake layer on top and frost top. Frost sides of cake and smooth frosting.
  15. Sprinkle remaining cacao nibs in center of cake.

Chocolate Cream Cheese Frosting

Chocolate Cream Cheese Frosting

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
50
Servings
12
Ingredients

1/2 c cream cheese, softened
1/4 c coconut cream
3 T unsweetened cocoa powder
2 tsp powdered SweetLeaf stevia
2 T unsweetened almond milk
1/4 t xanthan gum

Directions
  1. Mix cream cheese and almond milk with hand mixer until smooth
  2. Add cocoa powder, coconut cream, and stevia and mix until well combined
  3. Add xanthan gum and mix another minute
  4. Store unused portions of frosting in refrigerator

Almond Flax Crackers

Almond Flax Crackers

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
295
Servings
8 (8 crackers per serving)
Ingredients

2 cups almond flour
1 cup flax meal
2 tsp each of cumin, garlic powder, onion powder, oregano, black pepper and salt
2 eggs
2 Tbsp olive oil 
 

Directions
  1. Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
  2. Combine almond flour, flax meal and spices.
  3. Whisk egg and pour over flour mixture.
  4. Add olive oil.
  5. Stir or hand roll until dough forms.
  6. Roll dough into large ball and place on parchment lined baking sheet.
  7. Cover with another layer of parchment paper and roll out to 1/4" thick
  8. Score 8 rows of 8 squares. 
  9. Bake for 15 minutes or until golden brown.
  10. Let cool, break into squares.

Raspberry Torte

Raspberry Torte

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
225
Servings
8
Ingredients

1/2 cup coconut flour
6 eggs
1/2 cup coconut oil
2 tsp stevia
1/2 tsp vanilla exract 
1/2 cup water
1/4 tsp salt
1/4 tsp baking soda
3/4 cup frozen raspberries

Directions
  1. Preheat oven to 350.
  2. Line 9" springform cake pan with parchment paper.
  3. In large bowl, mix coconut flour, eggs, coconut oil, stevia, vanilla, water, salt, and baking soda.
  4. Blend with hand mixer until smooth.

  7. Remove from oven and allow to cool.

Vanilla Bug Repellent

Vanilla Bug Repellent

Dietary
Oil Free
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
n/a
Servings
Varies
Ingredients

1-2 T Pure Vanilla extract (imitation WILL NOT work)
1-2 T water
1-2 drops each: peppermint essential oil, citronella essential oil, lemongrass (or lemon eucalyptus) essential oil*

Directions

*OMIT ESSENTIAL OILS FROM RECIPE IF IN PHASE 2

Mix spray:

  1. Mix pure vanilla extract and water together in small container or spray bottle
  2. Add drops of essential oil to boost the repellent's power (if in P4 or Beyond)
  3. Screw on top of container/bottle and shake well

Application:

  1. Dip cotton balls into liquid and apply or spray directly onto skin
  2. Reapply as needed (each application will last about a half hour)

Lemon Balm Bug Spray

Lemon Balm Bug Spray

Dietary
Oil Free
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
n/a
Servings
Varies
Ingredients

Handful of fresh lemon balm leaves
Pinch each of: basil, catnip and mint
Witch hazel
1 drop each of: basil essential oil, citronella essential oil, lemongrass (or lemon eucalyptus) essential oil (OMIT if in P2)

*** MUST OMIT ESSENTIAL OILS FROM RECIPE IF IN PHASE 2 ***

Directions

*** MUST OMIT ESSENTIAL OILS FROM RECIPE IF IN PHASE 2 ***

Infuse witch hazel:

  1. Stuff full a glass jar of the lemon balm leave, basil, catnip, and mint
  2. Pour witch hazel over them, almost to the top of jar
  3. Cap the jar and set in a cool, dark cupboard for 1-2 weeks
  4. Strain and store out of heat and light
     

Mix spray:

  1. Fill a small spray bottle halfway with lemon balm infused witch hazel
  2. Fill rest of bottle with water, but not quite to top
  3. Add drops of essential oil, to boost the spray’s power (if in P4 or Beyond)
  4. Screw the spritzer top onto the bottle and shake well


Application:

  1. Shake thoroughly before each application and spritz on and around you
  2. Reapply as needed (each application will last 1-2 hours)
     

Storage:

  1. Once you’ve mixed up a batch with water, try to use it up within a few weeks
  2. Undiluted infused witch hazel will last at least six months to a year, or longer

Almond Butter Cups

Almond Butter Cups

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
125
Servings
10
Ingredients

Bottom Layer:
2 T melted coconut oil
4 T smooth almond butter
1/2 t vanilla stevia 

Top Layer:
2 T melted coconut oil
4 T smooth almond butter
1/4 c unsweetened cocoa powder
1 t vanilla stevia

Directions

Bottom layer:

  1. Stir until smooth.
  2. Set 10 muffin pan liners (or mini muffin pan liners) onto tray or plate.
  3. Pour 1 T of "Bottom Layer" recipe into each muffin cup liner.
  4. Put in freezer for 5 minutes.

Top Layer:

  1. Stir until smooth.
  2. Remove pan with the bottom layer from the freezer.
  3. Pour 1 T of "Top Layer" mixture to each muffin cup liner.
  4. Put the tray back in freezer for 15 minutes.

Apple Pie Sorbet

Apple Pie Sorbet

Dietary
Oil Free
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
100
Servings
2
Ingredients

2 apples
2 T lemon juice
1 dropperful English Toffee SweetLeaf stevia
1/4 t cinnamon
3/4 c water

Directions
  1. Cut, core and coarsely slice apples.
  2. Place apples in a saucepan along with lemon juice, stevia, cinnamon and water.
  3. Boil for approximately 3-5 minutes or until soft.
  4. Remove apple mixture from heat and cool.
  5. Place in food processor and puree until smooth.
  6. Strain and transfer to a small container.
  7. Place in the freezer.
  8. Once completely frozen, remove from freezer and place in food processor to puree again.
  9. Return to freezer until ready to use.

Dark Chocolate Silk Pie

Dark Chocolate Silk Pie

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
350
Servings
16
Ingredients

Crust:
1/2 c coconut oil, melted
2 eggs
1/4 t pink salt
3/4 c coconut flour
1-2 dropperfuls SweetLeaf stevia

Filling:
1 c coconut oil
3/4 c unsweetened cocoa powder
1 c coconut milk
10 dropperfuls SweetLeaf stevia or 1 T stevia extract
1/4 t pink salt
1 t vanilla extract
2 ripe avocados

Topping:
1 can coconut milk (refrigerated overnight)
1 t vanilla extract
1 dropperful SweetLeaf stevia
1/4-1/2 t xanthan gum

Directions

Crust:

  1. Preheat oven to 400 degrees.
  2. In medium bowl, mix oil, eggs, stevia, and salt together with a fork.
  3. Add coconut flour and stir until dough holds together.
  4. Gather the dough into a ball with hands. 
  5. Flatten dough out evenly into a 9″ greased pie pan.
  6. Prick dough with a fork.
  7. Bake for 8-10 minutes or until lightly brown. 

 

Filling:

  1. In a small saucepan, melt coconut oil over low heat.
  2. Stir in cocoa powder, coconut milk, stevia, and salt, and heat until warm.
  3. Remove from heat and stir in vanilla.
  4. Scoop out the avocado into a food processor.
  5. Add chocolate sauce to food processor.
  6. Process on high for about a minute, or until smooth, scraping down the sides as needed. 
  7. Pour mixture into pie shell.
  8. Refrigerate for at least 3 hours to set before serving.


Topping:

  1. Open can of refrigerated coconut milk and scoop heavier cream from the top of the can into a mixing bowl.
  2. Add stevia and vanilla.
  3. Whip with a mixer for about a minute until light and fluffy, scraping down the sides as needed.
  4. Add in xanthan gum.
  5. Mix again until stiff peaks form. 
  6. Spoon topping on top of pie and spread evenly.

Chicken "Fried Rice"

Chicken "Fried Rice"

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
523

5

Blueberry Cauliflower Bagels

Blueberry Cauliflower Bagels

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
176
Servings
2
Ingredients

3 c "riced" cauliflower
3 T Trader Joe's Golden Roasted Milled Flax Seed with Blueberries
1 T coconut flour 
2 eggs, room temperature
¼ t baking powder
2 T blueberries 

Directions
  1. Preheat oven to 400 degrees.
  2. Combine cauliflower rice, eggs, flax meal, coconut flour, baking powder, and blueberries in large bowl.
  3. Mix well.
  4. Refrigerate cauliflower mixture for 5 minutes.
  5. Take out of fridge and stir.
  6. Using hands, form 4 even sized mounds (squeeze mixture so it holds together).
  7. Lay onto parchment paper lined baking sheet.
  8. With handle of spoon, make a big hole in middle of each mound.
  9. Bake for 16 to 18 minutes, or until it reaches a bread-like consistency.
  10. Turn broiler on high, and broil for 2 to 3 minutes, until the top is golden.
  11. Remove from oven and let cool completely.

Zucchini Bread

Zucchini Bread

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
99
Servings
8
Ingredients

1/2 c coconut flour
1 T cinnamon
½ t nutmeg
3/4 t baking soda
1/2 t pink salt
4 eggs
24-36 drops SweetLeaf stevia
1 c zucchini, shredded finely
1 ripe banana, mashed
1 T coconut oil

Directions
  1. Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
  2. Grease a bread loaf pan or line with parchment paper.
  3. Shred zucchini finely. 
  4. Place shredded zucchini in kitchen towel and squeeze all the moisture out of it.
  5. Process eggs, stevia, coconut flour, oil, and banana together in food processor.
  6. Stir cinnamon, nutmeg, salt, baking soda, and zucchini into mixture until the batter is smooth.
  7. Pour batter into loaf pan.
  8. Bake for 45-50 minutes (or until a toothpick inserted into the center comes out clean).
  9. Allow to cool. 
  10. Remove from loaf pan and slice into 8 slices.

Creamy Chicken Stir Fry

Creamy Chicken Stir Fry

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
372
Servings
1
Ingredients

1/2 c cooked chicken breast
2 T cream cheese
1/2 c bell peppers
1/2 c broccoli
1/2 c mushrooms
1/4 c grated carrots
1/4 c onion
1 T jalapeno peppers
1 T coconut oil
pink salt, to taste
1 t Chef Paul Prudhomme's Vegetable Magic Seasoning

Directions
  1. Chop all veggies into bite sized pieces.
  2. Season with vegetable magic seasoning and pink salt.
  3. Saute veggies and chicken in coconut oil until cooked through.
  4. Stir in cream cheese.

Apple Cinnamon Fritters

Apple Cinnamon Fritters

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
290
Servings
4
Ingredients

1 cup grated red apples, juice squeezed out, firmly packed (roughly 3 small red apples)
5 eggs
1/3 c unsweetened almond milk, coconut milk or other milk of choice
2/3 c almond flour
1/2 t ground cinnamon
1 T powdered stevia 
coconut oil for frying
 

Directions
  1. Place the grated apples, eggs, milk, almond flour, cinnamon and stevia into a mixing bowl and combine well using a fork.
  2. Heat some coconut oil in a frying pan on medium heat.
  3. Add two heaped tablespoons of the apple fritter batter together to make one fritter.
  4. Add as many fritters to the frying pan as possible.
  5. Cook for 4-5 minutes then flip over.
  6. Cook for another 1-2 minutes or until the fritter has cooked through.
  7. Remove from the pan and repeat with the remaining batter.

Coconut Psyllium Tortillas

Coconut Psyllium Tortillas

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
143
Servings
10
Ingredients

1 c. coconut flour
1/4 c. psyllium husk powder
1/2 c. coconut oil, softened
1/4 tsp. garlic powder
1/8 tsp. pink salt
2 c. hot water 

Directions
  1. Put all dry ingredients in a bowl and mix well. 
  2. Add coconut oil and mix thoroughly. 
  3. Pour hot water over all, then stir with a spoon until all oil is melted and ingredients are well incorporated. (Or mix together in food processor)
  4. Shape dough into a log shape and cut into 8 equal parts.
  5. Grease griddle or frying pan lightly with butter or coconut oil and heat to medium heat.
  6. Shape each part into a ball.
  7. Roll out each ball evenly on a sheet of parchment paper.
  8. Push a medium sized pan lid into the top of the dough, twist, then lift the lid up (forming a perfect circle of dough). 
  9. Carefully remove dough around circle.
  10. Set that extra dough aside. (These pieces will combine to make the other two tortillas for a total of 10) 
  11. Flip parchment paper over onto your hand then peel parchment paper off of tortilla with other hand.
  12. Place tortilla on griddle and cook until bottom begins to brown.
  13. Flip, using spatula, and cook other side.
  14. Remove from pan and set aside.
  15. Repeat with remaining dough.

Fudgy Avocado Brownies

Fudgy Avocado Brownies

Dietary
Low Carb
Calories per serving
195
Servings
12
Ingredients

1 ripe avocado
¼ cup coconut oil
1 egg
1½ c coconut sugar
2 T water
1 t vanilla extract
¾ c unsweetened cocoa powder
½ t pink salt
¼ c coconut flour

Directions
  1. Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
  2. Line 8x8" baking pan with foil, leaving an overhang over the sides of the pan.
  3. Lightly grease foil.
  4. In food processor, combine avocado, coconut oil, egg, coconut sugar, water, and vanilla.
  5. Add cocoa powder and combine until fully incorporated and smooth.
  6. Stir in coconut flour and salt until just combined.
  7. Spread batter evenly in pan and bake for about 35 minutes, until the top has just set.
  8. Allow brownies to cool completely (about 1 hour) in the pan.
  9. Once cooled, lift entire brownie out of pan using the foil overhangs.
  10. Remove foil from brownies and cut into 12 rectangles.

Sour Cream Crustless Cheesecake

Sour Cream Crustless Cheesecake

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
335
Servings
12
Ingredients

24 oz sour cream
24 oz cream cheese
3 eggs
stevia, to taste
1 t vanilla extract

Directions
  1. Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
  2. Blend all ingredients in food processor or blender.
  3. Pour into a wax paper lined spring pan.
  4. Bake for 1 hour.
  5. Turn oven off and leave door ajar for an hour.
  6. Remove from oven and refrigerate overnight.
  7. Take cake out of pan by flipping onto a plate.
  8. Remove wax paper.
  9. Blot any moisture and reflip cake.

Tuna Cakes

Tuna Cakes

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
71
Servings
12
Ingredients

4 oz can albacore tuna
1/3 cup plain Greek yogurt
3 T organic salsa
1/4 cup minced onion
2 T parsley
3 large eggs
1/4 tsp pink salt
1 cup grated cheddar cheese

Directions
  1. Preheat oven to 325* and grease 12 cup muffin pan with butter or ghee.
  2. Drain tuna and in bowl break apart into small flake pieces.
  3. Mix in Greek yogurt, salsa, onion, and parsley.
  4. In separate bowl beat eggs and salt and then add to tuna mixture.
  5. Stir and combine thoroughly.
  6. Add cheese and mix.
  7. Divide evenly into muffin pan and bake 15-17 minutes until set. (Toothpick test works on this)
  8. Let cool for 5 minutes before removing from pan.

Homemade Mayo

Homemade Mayo

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
112
Servings
20 (1T/serving)
Ingredients

1 1/4 c light olive oil, divided (not extra virgin olive oil)
1 egg
1/2 t mustard powder
1/2 t salt
1-4 T lemon juice

Directions

Cauliflower Pizza Crust

Cauliflower Pizza Crust

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
413
Servings
1 crust
Ingredients

1 small head of cauliflower - 2 to 3 cups "riced" cauliflower
1/4 teaspoon pink salt
1 teaspoon oregano 
1/2 teaspoon garlic powder
1/4 cup shredded parmesan cheese
1/4 cup mozzarella cheese
1 egg
1 egg white (or 2 T liquid egg whites)

Directions
  1. Preheat oven to 450 degrees.
  2. Place a large piece of parchment paper on cutting board and spray it with nonstick cooking oil. 
  3. Pulse cauliflower in food processor for about 30 seconds, until "riced".
  4. Microwave cauliflower in small bowl, covered, for 4 minutes or steam in saucepan.
  5. Transfer cauliflower into a clean tea towel.
  6. Allow to cool, then wrap it up in the dish towel and wring it out. (Squeeze out as much water as possible.)
  7. Transfer cauliflower into a bowl.
  8. Add all other ingredients and mix with hands.
  9. Transfer dough onto parchment paper.
  10. Form into pizza crust shape desired with hands.
  11. Slide the parchment paper onto pizza stone or baking sheet and place in oven.
  12. Bake for about 10 minutes, until crust starts to slightly brown.
  13. Remove from oven.
  14. Add toppings and return to hot oven for another 5 to 10 minutes until the cheese is melted, bubbly, and slightly golden OR wrap crust in foil and freeze to top and bake at another time.

Goat Cheese Cauliflower Pizza Crust

If you're watching your carbs, cauliflower pizza crust is a keto-friendly alternative to traditional dough. The key ingredients in this recipe are goat cheese and cauliflower. Both are low carb and sugar free and the goat cheese is high protein... perfect for satisfying the cravings that are inevitable on any diet!

Jump To Recipe

Sugar-free cauliflower pizza crust is a keto-friendly alternative to traditional dough. This is delicious if you're watching your carbs, or if you need to eliminate sugar. Goat cheese is low-carb and high in protein - perfect for satisfying the cravings that are inevitable on any diet!

Cauliflower pizza makes an excellent substitute for those who want to satisfy their craving without all the carbs or sugar.

Cauliflower Pizza Crust with Goat Cheese is also kind of swanky and great for dinner parties when you want a hip entree that will make your guests think you are healthy AND cool. 

I would recommend cauliflower rice as a substitute for any dish that you would normally use white or brown rice or white or enriched flor. Cauliflower has the same texture and is lower in carbs, so I think it's perfect for almost anything.

Side note: Cauliflower pizza crust tastes just as good - if not better! 

A whole pie of this cauliflower pizza will cost you about 360 calories, which is significantly less than an equivalent portion of traditional dough (which may be over 1000 calories).

The ratio of protein to fat on goat cheese is excellent, with 20% being protein and 80% coming from healthy fats like omega-something something? ;) It’s also super creamy because it's made out of milk solids.

If you're watching your carbs, cauliflower pizza crust can be a great option because its made from cauliflower which has less carbohydrates than wheat or white flour does. The ultimate winner here is you when you try cauliflower pizza crust on your next cheat day.

I've been substituting cauliflower rice for white grain-based carbs like bread, pasta and potatoes in my diet for a few weeks now and I have to say that the results are better than expected. Cauliflower is an excellent source of vitamins A, Bs (thiamine), E, K as well as minerals such as potassium with its low glycemic index it's also a great option if you're watching your blood sugar levels or suffering from diabetic issues.

Cauliflower has a nutty taste which means no need to add extra flavorings when using it instead of traditional flour 

Nutritionally speaking: white flour is bad because it causes inflammation  and spikes blood sugar levels. 

White rice is made of long-grain or short-grain white rice, which has a high glycemic index and can cause an insulin surge that leads to weight gain if you're not careful with portion size. Rice also contains gluten, so it's off limits for people who have celiac disease or are intolerant to gluten, as well as anyone else wanting to avoid any form of grains altogether.

Cauliflower crust pizza is low in carbs (15g per serving) and higher protein than traditional dough because cauliflower contains over 20 amino acid compounds. It's one of the few vegetables in this category since most are too starchy like potatoes or tomatoes riddled with water content which makes them hard on your digestive system. 

Cauliflower also contains over 100% of the daily recommended intake of vitamin K, which is necessary for bone and blood health.

The cauliflower crust pizza recipe in this blog post uses goat cheese to add a creaminess and distinct flavor that compliments the profile well. It's easy to take out dairy if you're vegan or lactose-intolerant by substituting with Daiya vegan cheese and using a high quality organic sauce instead.

You can be sure to enjoy your pizza without feeling bloated and stuffed afterwards.

I hope you love this cauliflower crust as much as I do! It's a party favorite and  a healthy alternative to traditional pizza crust.

Why not have some goat cheese cauliflower pizza crust for dinner tonight? It's easy to make for the whole family.

Goat Cheese Cauliflower Pizza Crust

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
361
Servings
1 crust
Ingredients

4 c raw cauliflower, riced (about one medium head)
1 egg, beaten
⅓ c soft goat cheese (chevre)
1 t dried oregano
1/2 t garlic powder
1/8 t salt

Directions
  1. Preheat your oven to 400F.
  2. Pulse raw cauliflower florets in a food processor, until a rice-like texture is achieved.
  3. Steam cauliflower in saucepan in 1" of water for 4 minutes (or microwave, covered)
  4. Drain cauliflower and transfer into a clean, thin dishtowel.
  5. Squeeze excess moisture out of cauliflower.
  6. In a large bowl, mix cauliflower, egg, goat cheese, and spices. 
  7. Press the dough out onto a baking sheet lined with greased parchment paper about 1/3" thick. 
  8. Bake for 25-30 minutes, until starting to brown.
  9. Add additional toppings (sauce, cheese, etc) and return to oven to bake 5-10 more mintutes OR wrap pizza crust in foil and freeze it for a quick "frozen pizza" to enjoy another night (just add toppings and bake at 400 for 5-10 minutes when ready to eat).

Cashew Sandwich Bread

Cashew Sandwich Bread

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
139
Servings
16
Ingredients

3/4 c cashew butter, smooth 
6 eggs
1/4 c coconut oil, melted
1/2 t apple cider vinegar
1/4 c golden flax meal
3 T coconut flour
1 t baking soda
1/2 t pink salt

Directions
  1. Preheat oven to 350°F.
  2. Line 8" x 4" loaf pan with parchment paper and grease well with coconut oil.
  3. In large bowl, blend cashew butter, eggs, coconut oil and apple cider vinegar with hand mixer or in food processor.
  4. In a separate bowl, combine flax, coconut flour, baking soda and salt.
  5. Mix dry ingredients into wet with a hand mixer.
  6. Pour into loaf pan.
  7. Bake for 35-40 minutes.
  8. Remove from oven and immediately remove from pan by pulling up on the parchment.
  9. Set on wire rack to cool completely.
  10. Store in an airtight container at room temperature 3-4 days or in the fridge 7-10 days.

Nutty Cauliflower Brownies

Nutty Cauliflower Brownies

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
75
Servings
9
Ingredients

1 c riced cauliflower
1/2 C sliced almonds 
1/2 C unsweetened cocoa powder

1/2 C unsweetened applesauce
3 eggs 
2 t stevia

Directions
  1. Preheat oven to 350 degrees
  2. In a food processor pulse cauliflower until it reaches a grain-like consistency.
  3. Add sliced almonds and cocoa powder and blend for a few seconds.
  4. Add almond milk and blend until you reach a dark purée consistency. 
  5. Add applesauce, stevia, and eggs.
  6. Pour batter into greased 8x8 pan and bake for 30-35 minutes.

Dark Chocolate Avocado Cookies

Dark Chocolate Avocado Cookies

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
65
Servings
10
Ingredients

1 ripe avocado 
1 banana
3 T. liquid egg whites
½ c. unsweetened cocoa powder
3 tsp. stevia (more or less, to taste) 
½ tsp. baking soda
2 T. chocolate chips (optional)

Directions
  1. Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
  2. Line baking sheet with parchment paper.

Cilantro Lime Cauliflower Rice

Cilantro Lime Cauliflower Rice

Dietary
Oil Free
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
60
Servings
1
Ingredients

8 oz cauliflower ('riced' in food processor)
1 tsp onion powder
1 clove garlic minced
1 tbsp cilantro finely chopped
1-2 tbsp lime juice freshly squeezed
4 drops stevia
Pink salt to taste

Directions
  1. Saute garlic over medium to medium-low heat in small amount of water.
  2. Add in riced cauliflower and saute another 5-7 minutes, adding slightly more water if needed to prevent burning.
  3. Add 1/4 cup water, stir, cover and steam on low heat for 5-7 minutes.
  4. Stir in cilantro, onion powder, lime juice, pink salt, and stevia.

Banana Chia Crackers

Banana Chia Crackers

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
190
Servings
2
Ingredients

1/4 c. chia seeds
1 c. water
1 banana, very ripe
1⁄4 tsp. pink salt
1⁄2 tsp. cinnamon

Directions
  1. Preheat oven to 145 degrees.
  2. Combine ingredients in blender and process until smooth.
  3. Allow to sit for about 20 minutes until mixture begins to gel.
  4. Spread mixture about 1/8 in thick on parchment paper.
  5. Dehydrate in oven for about 6 hours, or until fruit-leather-like consistency is achieved.
  6. Carefully peel from parchment and slice into cracker-sized pieces.
  7. Return to oven for an additional 6 hours, or until crispy.

Taco Dip with Red Pepper "Chips"

Taco Dip with Red Pepper "Chips"

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
398
Servings
2
Ingredients

Very Berry N'Oatmeal

Very Berry N'Oatmeal

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
185
Servings
1
Ingredients

Spinach Pesto

Spinach Pesto

Dietary
Oil Free
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
55
Servings
1
Ingredients

5 oz spinach
1 bunch of basil 
3 cloves garlic
1 ½ T apple cider vinegar
1 lemon, juiced
1/4 t orgeano
1/8 t pink salt
1/8 t pepper

Directions
  1. Place apple cider vinegar, lemon juice, oregano, salt and pepper in small bowl.
  2. Mix until well combined, then set aside.
  3. Place spinach, basil, and garlic into blender or food processor.
  4. Pulse a few times.
  5. Slowly add liquid mixture in a constant stream while food processor or blender is on.
  6. Stop and scrape edges of container to get mixture toward bottom.
  7. Pulse a few more times until you reached a paste-like texture.

Cinnamon Roll Cookies

Cinnamon Roll Cookies

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
90
Servings
20
Ingredients

1 3/4 c. almond flour
1/4 c. coconut flour
1/4 c. coconut oil
1/4 tsp. baking soda
1/4 tsp. salt
2 eggs
1 tsp. liquid stevia (or a few packets) 
1 T. cinnamon
7 T. Cinnamon Roll Syrup 

Directions
  1. Preheat oven to 350 degrees and line baking sheet with parchment paper.
  2. In bowl, add flours, baking soda and salt then mix to combine.
  3. Mix in eggs to incorporate well.
  4. Add coconut oil and mash it into batter well with a fork until dough-like consistency is formed.
  5. Spray two pieces of parchment with non-stick spray and put ball of dough in between.
  6. Press to flatten into rectangle, about 1/4 inch thick.
  7. Remove top piece of parchment and sprinkle cinnamon over dough to cover.
  8. Roll dough into a 10" long log, pressing gently to flatten/thin it out as you roll.
  9. Spray sharp knife with non-stick spray then cut 1/2 inch segments and place on greased sheet of parchment.
  10. Bake for 10-20 minutes.
  11. Remove from oven and tranfer to cooling rack to cool completely.
  12. Top each cookie with about 1 teaspoon of Cinnamon Roll Syrup.

Ingredients

Scalloped No-Tatoes

Scalloped No-Tatoes

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
128
Servings
6
Ingredients

16 oz radishes
1 medium zucchini
1 small head cauliflower (5 to 6 cups florets)
2 cups water
1 egg
1/4 cup ghee (or substitute butter or coconut oil)
Salt and pepper to taste

Directions
  1. Slice the radishes and zucchini into very thin rounds, approximately 1/8″ (a mandoline slicer makes this job quick and easy). 
  2. Cut the cauliflower into florets.  You can also use the cauliflower stems; cut those into small pieces.
  3. Bring the water to a simmer over medium-high heat and add the cauliflower. 
  4. Simmer the cauliflower until slightly overcooked, about 15 minutes.
  5. Meanwhile, preheat the oven to 375F.
  6. Pour the water and the cauliflower into a blender. 
  7. Add the ghee and blend on high until you have a completely smooth puree (20 seconds to a minute, depending on your blender).
  8. Beat the egg slightly in a bowl and then temper the egg by adding a spoonful of the hot cauliflower puree to the egg while stirring vigorously. (Add another spoonful the same way and then a third spoonful.)
  9. Add the tempered egg to the cauliflower puree and blend to combine. 
  10. Add salt and pepper to taste.
  11. Lay the radish and zucchini slices to the bottom of a 9″ x 9″ casserole pan or baking pan and pour the cauliflower puree over the top.  
  12. Stir to make sure the veggie slices are well coated in the sauce and then smooth out to make sure the veggie slices are all lying flat.
  13. Bake for 30 minutes, until bubbling and the veggies are soft with just a little bit of give when pierced with a knife. 
  14. To brown the top layer, broil for 3 to 5 minutes at the end.

Buffalo Apple Burgers with Garlic Cabbage Rice

Buffalo Apple Burgers with Garlic Cabbage Rice

Dietary
Oil Free
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
325
Servings
1
Ingredients

3.5 oz ground buffalo/bison
1 apple, finely chopped
1/4 t onion powder
1/4 t garlic powder
1/2 t Bragg's liquid aminos
8 oz cabbage (red or green), finely chopped
1 T minced garlic
1/8 c water
salt and pepper, to taste

Directions
  1. Preheat oven to 350 degrees and line baking sheet with foil or parchment paper
  2. Mix buffalo, apple, onion powder, garlic powder, and liquid aminos in bowl using hands until well combined
  3. Divide mixture into 2 equal mounds and flatten into burgers (could make meatballs or meatloaf instead)
  4. Place on baking sheet and bake for 15 minutes
  5. Heat water in skillet over med-high heat
  6. Saute garlic for a minute
  7. Stir in cabbage and saute until tender
  8. Add salt and pepper to taste
  9. Serve burgers on top of cabbage rice

Vegan Chocolate Chip Cookie Dough Bowl

Vegan Chocolate Chip Cookie Dough Bowl

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
150
Servings
1
Ingredients

2 T coconut flour
2 T unsweetened applesauce
8 drops liquid stevia (plain or vanilla cream)
splash vanilla extract
2-3 T unsweetened almond milk
1/2 T coconut oil, melted
1/2 T unsweetened cocoa powder

Directions

  5. Stir chocolate chunks into cookie dough.

Crab Stew

Crab Stew

Dietary
Oil Free
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
185
Servings
1
Ingredients

5 oz crabmeat 
8 oz Campari tomatoes (or cut up bigger ones or use cherry toms)

1/2 t pink salt
1/4 t dry oregano

Directions

Cauliflower Alfredo Sauce

Cauliflower Alfredo Sauce

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
220
Servings
2
Ingredients

6 cloves garlic, minced 
1 T butter, softened
1 head cauliflower 
2 teaspoons salt 
1 generous pinch of pepper, to taste. 
juice from 1/2 lemon 
1 cup vegetable broth 
1/2 cup unsweetened almond milk 
1/4 cup finely grated parmesan cheese
olive oil, to taste

Directions
  1. In a large saucepan, boil florets of cauliflower on high heat until fork tender, approximately 10 minutes.  
  2. While cauliflower is boiling, warm butter in a saucepan and add garlic.
  3. Saute on low for a few minutes until lightly golden, but do not brown.
  4. Remove from heat and set aside. 
  5. Transfer cooked cauliflower to food processor or blender.  
  6. Add garlic, vegetable broth, salt, pepper and almond milk.
  7. Blend on high for several minutes, stopping every so often to add lemon juice and parmesan cheese to taste.
  8. Blend until sauce is very smooth. 
  9. Evaluate the consistency of your sauce. (If it seems thick, add more milk. If it seems dry, add a liberal drizzle of olive oil) 
  10. Blend through. 
     

Cauliflower Tots

Cauliflower Tots

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
186
Servings
2
Ingredients

1 c cooked cauliflower florets, finely chopped 
1 large egg
1 T egg white
1/4 c minced onion
1 T parsley
1/4 c pepperjack cheese (or other cheese of choice), grated
1/4 c coconut flour
pink salt and pepper to taste
 

Directions
  1. Preheat oven to 400°F. 
  2. Line cookie sheet with parchment paper or spray with cooking spray.
  3. In a medium bowl, combine all ingredients.
  4. Spoon out packed tablespoon of mixture and roll into small oval with your hands.
  5. Place on cookie sheet.
  6. Repeat until all mixture is used, should make 20 tots.
  7. Bake 8 minutes.
  8. Flip tots over.
  9. Return to oven for another 8 minutes or until golden.

Pizza Bagels

Pizza Bagels

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
128
Servings
6
Ingredients

2 eggs
1 cup mozzarella
1 cup "riced" cauliflower
5 slices pepperoni, cut into quarters
1/2 tsp fennel seed
3/4-1 tsp garlic powder
1/2 tsp crushed red pepper
1 large slice tomato, diced

Directions
  1. Combine all your ingredients and mix well.
  2. Spoon mixture into donut pan.
  3. Bake at 400 degrees for 30 minutes.

Thai Green Fish Curry

Thai Green Fish Curry

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
798
Servings
2
Ingredients

1 t coconut oil
2 cloves garlic, crushed
2 tbsp green curry paste
1 (13.5 oz) can coconut milk
1/4 c water 
1/4 t liquid stevia
12 grape tomatoes, halved
1 lb white fish fillets, cut into bite sized pieces
2 c green beans
4 c cauliflower, riced

Directions
  1. Steam riced cauliflower in pot or microwave until tender, then portion in 2 bowls.
  2. Heat oil in a wok and stir-fry garlic until soft.
  3. Add curry paste and cook, stirring, until fragrant. 
  4. Add coconut milk, water, stevia, and tomatoes and bring to a boil. 
  5. Simmer for 10 mins.
  6. Add fish and green beans and simmer, covered, for about 5 mins or until the fish is cooked.
  7. Divide curry into bowls on top of cauliflower.

Coconut Whipped Cream Topping

Coconut Whipped Cream Topping

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
35
Servings
25 (1 T. each)
Ingredients

1 (14 oz) can coconut cream, chilled
1/4 tsp. plain or SweetLeaf vanilla cream liquid stevia
1/2 tsp. vanilla extract
1/4 - 1/2 tsp. xanthan gum (optional)

Directions
  1. Place mixing bowl & beaters or food processor bowl & blade in freezer for 5 minutes.
  2. Place coconut cream in bowl or food processor.
  3. Add stevia and vanilla.
  4. Whip or process until whipped topping consistency is reached, adding xanthan gum slowly, if desired.
  5. Store in fridge.

Carrot Cake

Carrot Cake

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
260
Servings
12
Ingredients

1 cup coconut flour
1 cup unsweetened applesauce
½ cup melted coconut oil
8 eggs, at room temperature
1 tablespoon cinnamon
1 tsp ginger
½ tsp nutmeg
½ tsp pink salt
1 tablespoon lemon juice
1 tsp baking soda
2 cups shredded carrots 
¼ cup raisins
1 (13.5 oz) can coconut milk, chilled
1/4 t plain or SweetLeaf vanilla cream liquid stevia
1/2 t vanilla extract

Directions
  1. Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
  2. Grease bundt cake pan.
  3. Combine coconut flour, applesauce, coconut oil, eggs, cinnamon, ginger, nutmeg, salt, lemon juice, and baking soda until batter forms.
  4. Stir in shredded carrots and raisins.
  5. Spoon batter into pan.
  6. Bake about 45-50 minutes until center is firm.
  7. Allow to cool in pan for 20 minutes, then transfer to a wire rack to cool completely before frosting with Coconut Whipped Topping.
  8. Store, covered, in the fridge for up to one week.

Raspberry Almond Coconut Muffins

Raspberry Almond Coconut Muffins

Dietary
Low Carb
Calories per serving
295
Servings
12
Ingredients

2 c almonds
1/2 c shredded unsweetened coconut
1 t baking powder
1/2 c coconut sugar
4 eggs
1 t vanilla bean paste
1/2 c coconut oil, melted
1/2 c fresh or frozen raspberries

Directions
  1. Preheat oven to 325 degrees 
  2. Line a 12 cup muffin tray with liners 
  3. Place almonds into a food processor and pulse until they are finely ground
  4. In a large bowl, mix together ground almonds, coconut sugar, coconut and baking powder
  5. In a separate bowl, whisk together the eggs, coconut oil and vanilla bean paste
  6. Pour the egg mixture into the bowl of almond mixture and stir until well combined
  7. Pour the mixture into the muffin cases and dot with raspberries, pushing them down into the mix slightly
  8. Bake for approximately 20 minutes or until golden on top

180

Fennel Chicken Meatballs over Cucumbers

Fennel Chicken Meatballs over Cucumbers

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
226
Servings
8
Ingredients

2 pounds chicken breast
1 pound fresh fennel 
4 cucumbers
2 T basil
2 T pink salt
1 T black pepper 
2 T paprika 
1 T onion powder 
1 T red pepper flakes 
10 garlic cloves 
 

Directions
  1. Roast fennel in 350 oven for 1 hour, then cool.
  2. Add fennel and spices to food processor.
  3. Pulse until diced and well combined.
  4. Taste and adjust spices, then remove from food processor.
  5. Add chicken breast to food processor one at a time.
  6. Pulse to grind.
  7. Add ground chicken to fennel and spices and mix thoroughly.
  8. Drop by tablespoons (about 1 oz) onto baking dish.
  9. Bake 7-10 minutes in 350 oven.
  10. Served as meatballs over sliced cucumber with Frank's Red hot and Asian Fusion Dressing

Mini Sliders with Mushroom Relish

Mini Sliders with Mushroom Relish

Dietary
Oil Free
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
235
Servings
1
Ingredients

3.5 oz lean ground beef
1/4 t McCormick Grill Mates Steakhouse Onion Burger Seasoning
8 oz baby bella mushrooms
1-2 t Bragg's liquid aminos
1 t Bragg's apple cider vinegar
1 T water
1/4 t thyme
salt and pepper, to taste
5 drops liquid stevia
spicy brown mustard, to taste

Directions
  1. Preheat oven to 400 degrees and line baking sheet with parchment paper
  2. Remove stems from 6 mushroom caps, place on baking sheet, and brush with liquid aminos on both sides
  3. Bake for 10 minutes, then flip and bake 10 minutes on other side, set aside to cool
  4. Mix Hamburger seasoning into ground beef
  5. Form into 3 burger patties
  6. Cook burger in skillet or bake in oven until desire temp is reached
  7. Chop mushroom stems and remaining mushrooms finely
  8. Heat water and apple cider vinegar in small saucepan over med-high heat then add mushrooms
  9. Stir in thyme, stevia, salt and pepper
  10. Cook, stirring occasionally, for 2-3 minutes
  11. Drain mushroom relish and place a spoonful in 3 mushroom caps
  12. Add some spicy brown on top of relish
  13. Top with burger and second mushroom cap
  14. Serve extra mushroom relish on side

Lemon Dill Zucchini Chips

Salty Pretzel Bites

Salty Pretzel Bites

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
320
Servings
5 (8 bites each)
Ingredients

3 eggs
1 1/2 cups almond flour
2 1/2 T ghee
3 T coconut flour
pink salt

Directions
  1. Preheat oven to 350 degrees and line baking sheet wiht parchment paper
  2. Mix eggs, almond flour, 2 T ghee, and coconut flour with hands until dough forms
  3. Let sit for 5 minutes
  4. Roll dough into 40 small balls and place onto baking sheet
  5. Bake 6-7 minutes
  6. Remove from oven 
  7. Turn oven up to 400 degrees

  11. Melt remaining ghee and brush onto pretzel bites
  12. Sprinkle pink salt on top
