Brownie Bites

Brownie Bites

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
60
Servings
24
Ingredients

1 cup almond flour
½ cup cocoa powder
¼ teaspoon baking soda
pinch of pink salt
½ cup coconut oil, melted (plus a little non melted for greasing)
1 teaspoon liquid stevia
⅓ cup water 
3 eggs
1 teaspoon vanilla extract

Directions
  1. Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
  2. Grease mini muffin pan.
  3. In medium bowl, combine almond flour, cocoa powder, baking soda, and salt.
  4. In small bowl, beat eggs, coconut oil, water, and stevia until combined.
  5. Pour wet ingredients into dry and thoroughly incorporate.
  6. Spoon mixture into mini muffin pan.
  7. Bake for 15 minutes or until tops have risen and toothpick inserted comes out clean.
  8. Remove from oven and let cool in pan for 5-10 minutes then transfer to cooling rack to finish cooling.

Grain-Free Pumpkin Pie

Grain-Free Pumpkin Pie

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
185
Servings
8
Ingredients

Crust:
1 cup almond flour
3 T coconut oil 
1/2 t cinnamon 
1 egg

Filling:
1 (15 ounce) can pumpkin
3 eggs
1 t liquid stevia
1 T pumpkin pie spice
1 t vanilla extract
1/4 - 1/3 c unsweetened almond milk, to thin

Directions
  1. Preheat oven to 325.
  2. Grease pie pan with extra coconut oil.
  3. Mix almond flour, coconut oil, cinnamon, and 1 egg together by hand in a medium sized bowl.
  4. Press mixture to form crust into bottom and sides of pie pan.
  5. Bake 10-15 minutes, until beginning to brown.
  6. Combine pumpkin, 3 eggs, stevia, pumpkin pie spice, and vanilla in blender or food processor. 
  7. Add milk, if needed, to thin slightly.
  8. Transfer filling to crust and spread evenly with spatula.
  9. Bake for 1 hour or until center is no longer jiggly
  10. Remove from oven and allow to cool and set.

Low Carb Cherry Crisp

The cherry crisp is a delicious dish that can be made in minutes. Crisps are usually fruit-based, and this one stands out for its use of cherries and low-carb ingredients like almond flour, and coconut flour. Cherries are one of the most popular summer fruits, and they're perfect for pies. This low-carb cherry crisp dessert is a delicious alternative to traditional pie recipes that will please all your sugar cravings! Whip up this scrumptious recipe on a hot day and enjoy it with friends and family.

Jump To Recipe

Do you love the taste of cherries and looking for a low-carb dessert to satisfy your sweet tooth? This cherry crisp is made with almond flour, coconut oil, and just 5 ingredients. It's gluten-free and only 2g net carbs per serving!

Cherry season is finally here and it's time to celebrate with a low-carb cherry crisp. This recipe takes the classic dessert and uses almond flour in place of processed carbs. The result is healthy, delicious, and satisfying enough to satisfy your cravings without breaking your diet! 
If you're looking for something new this summer then give this recipe a try!

Low Carb Cherry Crisp

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
150
Servings
6
Ingredients

3 c cherries, pitted and sliced
2 tsp almond extract
1/3 c unsweetened almond milk
1/4 c hemp hearts
1/4 c almond flour
1/4 c coconut flour
2 T coconut oil
1 T water
1 tsp cinnamon
pinch of pink salt

Directions
  1. Preheat oven to 375 degrees.
  2. Grease large baking dish.
  3. In medium bowl, combine cherries, almond extract, and milk.
  4. In another bowl combine all other ingredients and mix well until crumbly.
  5. Pour cherry mixture into baking dish.
  6. Top with crumble mixture.
  7. Bake for 20 minutes.
  8. Remove from oven and let cool before serving.

Chai Spiced Apples

Chai Spiced Apples

Dietary
Oil Free
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
95
Servings
1
Ingredients

1/3 c water
1 apple, sliced thin
1/2 t Chinese 5 Spice
12-15 drops SweetLeaf vanilla cream stevia
5-6 turns of black peppercorn shaker

Directions
  1. Heat skillet to med-high heat
  2. Add water and apples
  3. Cover and cook for 1 minute
  4. Stir in Chinese 5 Spice, stevia, and pepper
  5. Cover and cook until liquid is reduced by half and apples are tender
  6. Uncover and continue cooking, stirring occasionally, until liquid is almost gone
  7. Transfer apples to bowl or plate
  8. Pour remaining liquid over top as syrup

Coffee Crusted Fish

Coffee Crusted Fish

Dietary
Oil Free
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
135
Servings
1
Ingredients

4.5 oz cod, flounder, other fish of choice
1 T finely ground coffee 
1/4 t oregano
1/4 t garlic powder
1/4 t chili powder
1/2 t paprika
1/8 t ginger
1/2 t ground mustard
1/8 t salt
1/8 t pepper
2 T water

Directions
  1. Season each side of the fish with salt and pepper.
  2. Combine all the seasonings in a mixing bowl and mix well.
  3. Rub a heaping spoonful of the spice rub into one side of the fish.
  4. Cover and allow to sit in the refrigerator for at least 2 hours.
  5. Heat water in skillet.
  6. Add the fish with the rub side down so that this side will cook first and get nice and crispy before you have to flip the fish.
  7. Cook the fish on the rub side down for 4-5 minutes then flip and cook again for 4-5 minutes.
  8. Cooking time may vary depending on the size of your fish. (Fish is ready to turn when it begins to lift away from the bottom of the pan)
    *This could be baked in the oven on parchment lined paper for 15-20 minutes at 375 degrees instead, if desired

Fried Avocado and Egg Spring Salad

Fried Avocado and Egg Spring Salad

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
580
Servings
1
Ingredients

3 cups Spring Mix lettuce
1/2 Avocado, sliced 
2 T Coconut oil
2 eggs
1 T Apple cider vinegar
Garlic Herb spice mix
salt and pepper, to taste
crushed red pepper, to taste

Directions
  1. Melt coconut oil in skillet and fry the eggs.
  2. Remove eggs, turn heat to high until coconut oil is very hot.
  3. Place avocado in skillet and add seasoning, to taste.
  4. Cook on one side until crisp (2-3 minutes), flip and cook other side until crisp then remove from skillet.
  5. Remove skillet from heat and let oil cool slightly.
  6. Add ACV and garlic herb spice to skillet with the remainder of the coconut oil to make the dressing.
  7. Add avocado, fried eggs, and dressing to a bed of spring mix.

Vanilla Mint Pears

Vanilla Mint Pears

Dietary
Oil Free
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
55
Servings
2
Ingredients

1 pear, sliced thin
1/2 c water
1 t lemon juice
5 drops SweetLeaf vanilla cream stevia
1 regular tea bag (orange pekoe or another of your liking)
1 t dried mint (or 1 mint tea bag)

Directions
  1. Heat water in skillet over med-high heat
  2. Stir in lemon juice and stevia
  3. Add pear slices tea bag(s) and mint
  4. Bring to a boil then cover and reduce heat to low
  5. Cook for 5 minutes or until pear slices are tender when pierced with a fork
  6. Remove from heat and allow to cool
  7. Divide pears onto two plates 
  8. Spoon a little of the liquid on top of the pears

Fish Taco Stuffed Peppers

Fish Taco Stuffed Peppers

Dietary
Oil Free
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
245
Servings
2
Ingredients

10 oz grouper (or other fish)
16 oz bell peppers (I used 1 yellow, 1 red, 1 orange)
3/4 c water
1-2 T Taco Seasoning
2 T salsa, if desired

Directions
  1. Pour 1/2 c water into baking dish and preheat oven to 425 degrees
  2. Slice 2 peppers half and remove stem
  3. Place into baking dish and set aside
  4. Chop remaining pepper into small pieces
  5. Heat 1/4 c water in skillet over med-high heat
  6. Add chopped peppers and cook, then remove from heat
  7. Add fish to skillet and cook until done
  8. Add peppers back to skillet and stir in taco seasoning, to taste
  9. Stir until combined and flake fish into pieces
  10. Scoop mixture evenly into the 4 pepper halves
  11. Place into oven and bake for 35 minutes
  12. Top with 1/2 T salsa per pepper half, if desired

Ranch Cauliflower Chips

Ranch Cauliflower Chips

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
195
Servings
2
Ingredients

1 cup grated parmesan cheese
1 cup grated raw cauliflower
1/2 tsp parsley
1/2 tsp basil
1/2 tsp dill
1/2 tsp chives
1/2 tsp garlic powder
1/2 tsp onion powder
1/2 tsp pepper
 

Directions
  1. Preheat oven to 450 degrees. 
  2. Add all ingredients to a bowl.
  3. Stir.

  6. Bake at 450 degrees for 5- 7 minutes.

  8. Bake for another 5 -7 minutes.

Chocolate Avocado Cookies

Chocolate Avocado Cookies

Dietary
Low Carb
Calories per serving
115
Servings
10
Ingredients

2 oz unsweetened baker's chocolate 
1/2 T coconut oil
1/2 avocado
2 T almond butter
1/4 c honey
1 egg
1 egg white
2 T unsweetened cocoa powder
1 1/2 T almond flour

Directions
  1. Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
  2. Line baking sheet with parchment paper.
  3. Melt coconut oil and chocolate together in double broiler.
  4. In food processor, purée avocado until smooth.
  5. Add all other ingredients and pulse until combined.
  6. Place batter in fridge for one hour.
  7. Drop 10 mounds onto baking sheet and form into circles with back of spoon.
  8. Bake for 15-20 minutes.
  9. Remove from oven and allow to cool for at least 5 minutes before serving.

Paleo Cinnamon Rolls

Paleo Cinnamon Rolls

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
185
Servings
10
Ingredients

1 3/4 c. almond flour
1/4 c. coconut flour
1/4 c. coconut oil
1/4 tsp. baking soda
1/4 tsp. pink salt
2 eggs
1 tsp. stevia 
1 T. cinnamon

Directions
  1. Preheat oven to 350 degrees and line baking sheet with parchment paper.
  2. In bowl, add flours, baking soda and salt then mix to combine.
  3. Mix in eggs to incorporate well.
  4. Add coconut oil and mash it into batter well with a fork until dough-like consistency is formed.
  5. Spray two pieces of parchment with non-stick spray and put ball of dough in between.
  6. Press to flatten into rectangle, about 1/4 inch thick.
  7. Remove top piece of parchment and sprinkle cinnamon over dough to cover.
  8. Roll dough into log, pressing gently to flatten/thin it out as you roll.
  9. Spray sharp knife with non-stick spray then cut 1.5 inch segments and place on greased sheet of parchment.
  10. Bake for 10-20 minutes.
  11. Top each cinnamon roll with Cinnamon Roll Syrup or Easy Creamy Frosting, if desired.

Cinnamon Roll Syrup

Cinnamon Roll Syrup

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
9
Servings
24 (2 T per serving)
Ingredients

1 3/4 c water
1 1/2 c unsweetened applesauce
5 t butter extract
3-4 t stevia extract 
5 t cinnamon
1 t xanthan gum (or 1 t flax meal mixed with 2 t hot water)

Directions
  1. In a large bowl, whisk together the water, applesauce and extracts
  2. In a small bowl, whisk together the cinnamon and xanthan gum (or flax/water mixture)
  3. Slowly add this into the wet ingredients while whisking
  4. Once incorporated, whisk the entire mixture vigorously
  5. Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate overnight
  6. Pour mixture into blender or food processor and puree for 1-2 minutes
  7. Pour syrup into bottle/jar, tightly seal and refrigerate to store

Stevia Pancake Syrup

Stevia Pancake Syrup

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
n/a
Servings
Varies
Ingredients

3 c. water
1 T. maple extract
1/8 tsp. pink salt
¼ tsp. stevia extract or 2 tsp. SweetLeaf plain, vanilla, or English toffee liquid stevia
½ to 1 tsp. xanthan gum

Directions
  1. Combine all ingredients except xanthan gum into a medium saucepan.
  2. Sprinkle xanthan gum lightly over the surface of the syrup and whisk to incorporate.
  3. Taste and adjust flavors then turn heat up to medium.
  4. Let syrup come to a simmer and thicken.
  5. Remove from burner and allow to thicken and cool slightly.
  6. Serve warm or cold.

Banana Egg Pancakes

Banana Egg Pancakes

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
365
Servings
1
Ingredients

1 T. coconut oil
1 banana
2 eggs
1 tsp. vanilla
Dash of cinnamon

Directions
  1. Melt 1 T. coconut oil in a pan over medium heat. 
  2. Smash banana with a fork until it's nearing the liquid stage.
  3. Whisk in eggs, vanilla, and cinnamon.
  4. When the coconut oil is good and hot, pour 1/8 c. of batter into pan for each pancake.
  5. Just like traditional pancakes, wait until bubbles form before you flip them.
  6. The number of pancakes you get from this will vary depending on size of each. 
  7. Top with Stevia Pancake Syrup, Cinnamon Roll Syrup, fruit, or other toppings of choice.

Chocolate Peanut Butter Bites (Bombs)

Chocolate Peanut Butter Bites (Bombs)

Dietary
Low Carb
Calories per serving
130
Servings
10
Ingredients

Bottom Layer:
2 Tbsp melted coconut oil
1/4 cup peanut butter 
1/2 tsp vanilla stevia 

Top Layer:
2 Tbsp melted coconut oil
1/4 cup peanut butter
1/4 cup unsweetened cocoa powder
1 tsp vanilla stevia 

Directions
  1. Combine all Bottom Layer ingredients and stir until smooth.
  2. Set 10 mini muffin pan liners onto a tray or plate.
  3. Pour 1 tablespoon into each muffin cup liner.
  4. Place in freezer on a flat surface.
  5. Combine all Top Layer ingredients and stir until smooth.
  6. Remove pan with bottom layer from freezer.
  7. Add 1 tablespoon of chocolate mixture to each muffin cup liner.
  8. Place tray back in freezer for 15 minutes.

Banana Boat

Banana Boat

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
285
Servings
1
Ingredients

1 banana
1 T. chopped pecans or walnuts
1/4 tsp. coconut oil
1/8 tsp. cinnamon, plus extra for dusting bananas
1 T. almond butter 

Directions
  1. Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
  2. Melt coconut oil in a small pan over medium-high heat.
  3. Add pecans and cinnamon, cook, stirring continuously until toasted. Set aside.
  4. With peel still on, cut banana 1/2 inch deep (about half way through)
  5. Place banana on a sheet of foil.
  6. Crimp and shape foil around the banana so it will sit flat on a baking sheet.
  7. Fill banana with 1-2 tbsp almond butter and 1/2-1 tbs toasted pecans.
  8. Sprinkle with a dash of cinnamon.
  9. Bake for 10-12 minutes or until bananas are soft.
  10. Let cool slightly before eating.

Oil Free

Plantain Pancakes

Plantain Pancakes

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
181/pancake
Servings
6 pancakes
Ingredients

2 large green plantains (about 2 cups pureed)
4 eggs
2 tsp vanilla
3 Tbsp extra virgin coconut oil
1/8 tsp salt
½ tsp baking soda
Extra coconut oil for frying

Directions
  1. Peel plantains and place pieces in blender or food processor with the eggs. 
  2. Blend to form a smooth batter.
  3. Add the rest of the ingredients to the blender or food processor and process on high for an additional minute or two.
  4. Heat 1 Tbsp of coconut oil in a frying pan or on a griddle over medium-high heat. 
  5. Pour batter into the frying pan until your pancake is the desired size.
  6. Let cook 4-5 minutes on the first side, until the top looks fairly dry with little bubbles in it.
  7. Flip and cook on the second side for 1½-2 minutes.
  8. Repeat with remaining batter, adding a little more coconut oil to your pan as needed.

Creamy Coconut Butter

Creamy Coconut Butter

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
90
Servings
8 (1T per serving)
Ingredients

2 c shredded, unsweetened coconut

Directions
  1. Pulse shredded coconut in food processor or power blender for 10 minutes or until turns to smooth liquid
  2. Scrape down sides as needed and pause occasionally to prevent food processor/blender from overheating
  3. To make less grainy, strain through metal sieve (may run what is leftover in sieve through blender/processor again and re-strain)
  4. Pour into glass jar or air tight container 
  5. Store at room temp

Flax N'Oatmeal

Flax N'Oatmeal

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
218
Servings
1
Ingredients

2 Tablespoons flax meal
½ cup almond milk 
¾ cup egg whites
3 Tablespoons pumpkin puree
1¼ teaspoons cinnamon
1 teaspoon nutmeg
½ teaspoon vanilla extract
stevia, to taste

Directions
  1. Place flax meal, milk, egg whites, pumpkin, cinnamon, and nutmeg in a small sauce pan on medium heat.
  2. Use a whisk to combine and continue to whisk until mixture thickens, approximately 5-7 minutes.
  3. Once mixture is near desired thickness, add vanilla and stevia.
  4. Pour into your bowl and sprinkle a little additional cinnamon over the top.
  5. If you would like, add desired toppings such as: chopped nuts, nut butter, vanilla Greek yogurt, chopped apple, slicked banana, a few chocolate chips, etc.

Cauliflower N'Oatmeal

Cauliflower N'Oatmeal

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
450
Servings
1
Ingredients

1 cup "riced" cauliflower (finely chopped in food processor)
1/3 cup coconut milk 
2/3 cup water
2 large eggs, beaten
2 tablespoons flax meal
3 teaspoons ground cinnamon or pumpkin spice
pinch of sea salt

Directions
  1. Combine riced cauliflower, coconut milk, water, flaxseed meal, spice, and salt in a sauce pan and bring to boil.
  2. Lower the heat as soon as it starts to boil and let simmer for a while, at least until the cauliflower is soft.
  3. When the cauliflower is soft, add the eggs while heavily stirring.
  4. Remove from heat and transfer into bowl.
  5. Add additional toppings, if desired.

Directions

Steamed Cauliflower Rice

Steamed Cauliflower Rice

Dietary
Oil Free
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
60
Servings
1
Ingredients

8 oz cauliflower
2 T water

Directions
  1. Pull off the leaves and break the cauliflower into large florets
  2. Pulse florets in food processor until finely chopped
  3. Heat skillet on med-high heat
  4. Heat about 2 tablespoons of water or veggie broth in your skillet, add the cauliflower, then cover until tender, about 2 minutes
  5. If there’s still liquid in the pan, take off the lid and let it cook off before serving

COcolate (Coconut Oil Chocolate)

COcolate (Coconut Oil Chocolate)

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving

1
Ingredients

1T unsweetened cocoa/cacao powder
liquid stevia (or flavored liquid stevia), to taste

Directions

Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
90
Servings
5
Ingredients

3/4 cup shredded unsweetened coconut

1 1/2 T unsweetened cocoa powder (divided)
1 dropperful stevia

Directions
  1. ​Preheat oven to 350 degrees
  2. Pulse banana, coconut, and 1/2 T cocoa in food processor, until well combined
  3. Form mixture into 5 flattened rounds on greased cookie sheet

1
Ingredients

1 tablespoon coconut oil or butter, melted
1 egg, slightly beaten
1 tablespoon coconut milk
1 tablespoon almond meal, packed
1 tablespoon coconut flour, packed
1/8 teaspoon baking soda
Sesame seeds for topping, optional

Directions
  1. Blend oil or melted butter, egg, milk, almond meal, coconut flour, and baking soda.
  2. Pour batter into a greased 4" cake pan.
  3. Smooth top with a dampened spatula.
  4. Sprinkle with sesame seeds (if desired)
  5. Bake for 18-20 minutes in a 350 degree oven or, cook bun in the microwave. (Grease a 4" round microwave safe ramekin. Cook at full power for 55 - 60 seconds). 

Recipe credit to: freerangecookies.com

Zucchini Pizza Crust

Zucchini Pizza Crust

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
250
Servings
2
Ingredients

4 c grated zucchini 
1/2 c mozzarella cheese, shredded
5 T almond meal
3 T parmesan cheese
1 t oregano
1/2 t garlic powder
pinch of pink salt
1 egg, beaten 

Directions
  1. Preheat oven to 450 degrees
  2. Grease baking sheet
  3. Microwave zucchini in bowl for 5 minutes
  4. Drain zucchini and wring out moisture with cheesecloth or kitchen towel
  5. Add mozzarella, almond meal, parmesan, oregano, garlic powder, pink salt, and beaten egg and stir until well combined
  6. Divide crust mixture into two balls
  7. Use your fingers to press out the crust mixture into two circles on baking sheet
  8. Bake about 12-15 minutes, until firm and starting to brown

Paleo Biscuits

Paleo Biscuits

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
105
Servings
9
Ingredients

6 egg whites
3/4 cup blanched almond flour
1/4 cup coconut flour
1 teaspoon baking powder
1/4 teaspoon salt
1 1/2 tablespoons coconut oil, chilled

Directions
  1. Preheat oven to 400 degrees. 
  2. Line a baking sheet with parchment paper. 
  3. Mix almond flour, coconut flour, baking powder and salt together in a large mixing bowl. 
  4. Cut in cold coconut oil with a fork until the mixture is crumbly. 
  5. Place the bowl in the refrigerator for 10 minutes. 
  6. In a medium bowl whisk egg whites until they are very frothy. 
  7. Fold the egg whites into the chilled flour mixture until well combined. 
  8. Scoop about 1/4 cup of dough onto the baking sheet and smooth the top to form each biscuits, an ice cream scoop works well in this step. 
  9. Bake for 15-18 minutes, or until the tops are golden brown. 
  10. Serve warm or store in an airtight container in the refrigerator.

Recipe credit to: simplylivinghealthy.org

Cauliflower Bagel

Cauliflower Bagel

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
180
Servings
2
Ingredients

1 small head cauliflower, cut into small florets (should yield 3 cups of cauliflower rice) 
3 tablespoons almond flour (or flax meal)
1 tablespoon coconut flour 
2 eggs at room temperature
½ teaspoon garlic powder
½ teaspoon fine sea salt
¼ teaspoon baking powder
Pinch of ground black pepper
Poppy seeds, sesame seeds, minced garlic or minced onion for topping

Directions
  1. Preheat oven to 400°F (200°C) and place a rack in the middle.
  2. In a food processor rice the cauliflower florets (it should be evenly chopped but not completely pulverized).
  3. In a large bowl combine 3 cups of cauliflower rice, eggs, almond flour, coconut flour, baking powder, garlic powder, salt and pepper. Mix well.
  4. Refrigerate the cauliflower mixture for 5 minutes - this will allow the almond flour and coconut flour to soak up some of the moisture.
  5. Take out the fridge and give it another good stir.
  6. Line a baking sheet with parchment paper and lightly grease with olive oil.
  7. Using your hands form 4 even sized buns (squeezing the mixture so it holds together) and lay onto the lined baking sheet.
  8. Sprinkle toppings and lightly press them into the top. With the handle of a spoon/fork/knife the making a big hole in the middle of each bun.
  9. Bake in the oven for about 16 to 18 minutes, or until it reaches a bread-like consistency.
  10. Turn on the broiler on high, and broil for further 2 to 3 minutes until the top is golden.
  11. Remove from the oven and let cool completely on a rack before peeling them off the parchment paper.

Coconut Flour Wrap

Coconut Flour Wrap

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
69
Servings
1
Ingredients

3 egg whites
1/2 Tbsp coconut flour
additional seasonings (ex: garlic powder, cilantro, onion powder for savory wrap; cinnamon, cloves, stevia for a sweet wrap/crepe/roll)

Directions
  1. Blend ingredients in blender, Ninja, Magic Bullet, etc
  2. Heat large skillet on med/med-high heat.  
  3. Coat with cooking spray. 
  4. When skillet is completely heated, pour mixture on skillet and swirl pan to spread mixture over entire pan.  
  5. Cover pan.  
  6. Let cook for a minute or two; wrap may puff up, just remove lid and prepare to flip.  
  7. When wrap is set, swirl pan to be sure wrap is not sticking to pan.  
  8. Use some wrist action to flip the wrap, or a gigantron pancake flipper.  
  9. Cook another 30 seconds, slide onto plate, and create the most delicious wrap you can imagine!

Recipe credit to: clarkpharm.blogspot.com

Paleo English Muffin

Paleo English Muffin

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
160
Servings
1
Ingredients

1 egg, beaten
1 T unsweetened almond milk or coconut milk
1 T coconut flour
½ T butter or coconut oil, melted
½ t baking powder
6 drops stevia, optional
1 pinch pink salt, optional

Directions
  1. Melt butter/oil in round ceremic/glass ramekin
  2. Add all ingredients to the ramekin, except baking powder, and stir with a fork
  3. Add baking powder and stir in well
  4. Stir, scraping sides, until clump free
  5. Cook in microwave for 1 minute and 30 Seconds, or bake in oven at 400 F for 12-15 minutes, until middle is firm
  6. Loosen edges by taking knife between muffin and ramekin
  7. Cool, enough to handle, then remove from bowl and cut in half sideways
  8. Toast in buttered/oiled frying pan, until lightly browned on each side (like a pancake), using spatula to press the tops of muffin down lightly

Corn-Free Cornbread

Corn-Free Cornbread

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
120
Servings
12
Ingredients

1 c coconut flour 
1/2 t powdered stevia or 12 drops liquid stevia
1 t pink salt
3 1/2 t baking powder
5 eggs 
1/2 c unsweetened almond milk
1/3 c coconut oil

Directions
  1. Preheat oven to 400 degrees F 
  2. Grease 8x8 inch baking pan
  3. In large bowl, combine coconut flour, stevia, salt and baking powder
  4. Stir in egg, milk and oil until well combined
  5. Pour batter into pan
  6. Bake in preheated oven for 20 to 25 minutes, or until a toothpick inserted into the center of the loaf comes out clean

Dairy-free Cauliflower Pizza Crust

Dairy-free Cauliflower Pizza Crust

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
370
Servings
1
Ingredients

3 c "riced" cauliflower
1/4 t pink salt
1/2 t basil
1/2 t oregano 
1/2 t garlic powder
2 T almond meal
1 T coconut oil 
1 egg

Directions
  1. Preheat oven to 450 degrees.
  2. Place cauliflower in bowl in microwave, cover, and microwave for 4 minutes
  3. Place cooked cauliflower into kitchen towel or cheesecloth and allow to cool 
  4. Wring water out of cauliflower
  5. Place cauliflower into bowl and add spices, almond meal, and coconut oil
  6. Mix well with hands
  7. Add egg and mix again
  8. Form dough into desired crust shape on greased parchment paper
  9. Bake for 12 minutes, or until starting to brown

Cloud Bread

Cloud Bread

Dietary
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
30
Servings
10
Ingredients

3 eggs, separated
3 T cream cheese, softened (or plain greek yogurt/whole milk/coconut cream/cottage cheese)
¼ t cream of tartar
2-3 drops liquid stevia

Directions
  1. Preheat oven to 300 degrees
  2. Line cookie sheet with parchment paper and spray
  3. Separate eggs 
  4. In small bowl, mix together egg yolks, cream cheese (or yogurt/milk/coconut cream/cottage cheese) and stevia until smooth
  5. In another bowl, add cream of tartar to the egg whites
  6. Beat whites on high speed until fluffy and form very stiff peaks
  7. Fold egg yolk mixture into egg whites carefully until thoroughly mixed
  8. Scoop the mixture into 10 even rounds onto cookie sheet
  9. Bake for 30 minutes or until golden brown
  10. Remove from cookie sheets and cool on a rack/cutting board
  11. Store in a plastic baggie or container for a softer bread texture that is chewy

    *Can be made into 6 rounds instead for larger slices at 50 calories/slice

Coconut Flour Sandwich Bread

Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
160

Directions

  3. Stir in eggs, coconut oil, and vinegar, until thoroughly combined

  7. Bake 15 to 20 minutes, until edges are lightly browned

Green Onion Soup

Green Onion Soup

Dietary
Oil Free
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
75
Servings
2
Ingredients

8 oz green onions
2 c vegetable broth
2 t Bragg's Liquid Aminos
1 t parsley
4 drops stevia or 1 packet
1/2 t paprika
1/2 t salt
1/2 t dill
1/2 t thyme
1/8 t red pepper flakes or cayenne pepper
1/8 t celery seed

Directions
  1. Briefly steam green onions until tender
  2. Preheat saucepan over medium heat
  3. Chop steamed green onions
  4. Saute green onions in small amount of vegetable broth for a couple minutes
  5. Add spices and stevia and saute another 1-2 minutes
  6. Add remaining vegetable broth, reduce heat, cover and simmer 20-30 minutes (can add water if necessary)

French Onion Soup

French Onion Soup

Dietary
Oil Free
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
130
Servings
1
Ingredients

8 oz Vidalia onion
1 c sugar-free beef broth (or water)
1 t garlic powder
1 t onion salt
1/8 t pepper
water

Directions
  1. Slice onion with an apple slicer to make wedges and open up the onion
  2. Season onion with garlic powder, onion salt, and pepper
  3. Place onion on top of a foil sheet
  4. Add 1/4 c beef broth
  5. Wrap foil tightly around onion
  6. Place in baking dish and bake at 350 for 1 hour

Baked Apple

Baked Apple

Dietary
Oil Free
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
95
Servings
1
Ingredients

1 apple 
1 packet stevia 
1 tsp cinnamon
1 T water

Directions
  1. Cut apple core almost through
  2. Mix together stevia, cinnamon, and water
  3. Place apple on a sheet of foil and mold foil to "cup" the apple
  4. Pour liquid into apple core and tighten foil securely around apple
  5. Bake at 350 for 45 minutes
  6. Sprinkle extra cinnamon over top after removing from oven

Cauliflower Tortillas

Cauliflower Tortillas

Dietary
Oil Free
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
180 (30 cal/tortilla)
Servings
1 batch
Ingredients

8 oz cauliflower florets
1 egg (or 2 whole eggs and no whites)
3 egg whites
salt and pepper, to taste

Directions
  1. Preheat oven to 375 degrees and line a baking tray with parchment paper.
  2. Pulse cauliflower in food processor until you get a texture slightly finer than rice. (Once it's riced measure it to make sure you have 2 cups packed.)
  3. Place riced cauliflower in bowl and microwave for 2 minutes and stir, then another two minutes and stir again then place in a dish towel and squeeze excess water out as hard as you can.
  4. Place drained cauliflower back in bowl and add eggs, salt and pepper and mix until well combined. (Will be runny but not pure liquid)
  5. Spread mixture onto a baking sheet into 6 small fairly flat circles.
  6. Place in the oven for 10 minutes then pull out of the oven and carefully peel them off the parchment and flip them and place back in the oven for 5-7 more minutes.
  7. Place on a wire rack to cool slightly.
  8. Heat a medium sized pan over medium heat and place the tortillas into the pan pressing down slightly and brown them to your liking. 

Filet Mignon with Garlic Carmelized Onions

Filet Mignon with Garlic Carmelized Onions

Dietary
Oil Free
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
320
Servings
1
Ingredients

3.5 oz. Filet Mignon
2 Tbls. Red Wine Vinegar
2 Tbls. Balsamic Vinegar
2 Cloves Garlic, minced
1/4 tsp. Chicago Steakhouse Seasoning (Weber)
1 tsp. Fresh Rosemary Leaves, chopped finely
8 oz. sweet onion, sliced thin
1/4 c. low sodium beef broth
1/4 tsp. Roasted Garlic & Herb Seasoning (Weber)

 

Directions
  1. Preheat oven to 375 degrees.
  2. Combine vinegars and garlic to make marinade.
  3. Pierce filet mignon with knife in several places and on both sides - place in marinade turning to coat.
  4. Let rest in marinade about 20 minutes, turning half way through.
  5. Preheat skillet - remove filet mignon from marinade and sprinkle with Steakhouse seasoning and rosemary.
  6. Brown filet mignon on all sides.
  7. Remove filet mignon from skillet and turn off burner - place on foil covered baking sheet and put in preheated oven.
  8. Add broth to skillet scraping to pick up any burned bits (deglaze).
  9. Add 2 teaspones of the marinade, the sliced onions and the Roasted Garlic seasoning.
  10. Stir to combine the broth and seasonings with the onion.
  11. Bring onions to a boil and then reduce heat to medium low cooking until onions are transluscent and most of the liquid is gone.
  12. Remove filet mignon from oven when desired doneness is reached and let rest for 5 minutes.
  13. Slice filet, and top with carmelized garlic onions.

Spicy Mustard Scallops with Chard

Spicy Mustard Scallops with Chard

Dietary
Oil Free
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
195
Servings
1
Ingredients

3.5 oz. scallops
3 T. stone ground mustard
2 T. Bragg's liquid aminos
1 T. apple cider vinegar
2 T. lemon juice
2 T. chopped onion
2 cloves garlic, sliced
1/2 c. chicken stock/vegetable broth
8 oz shredded, chopped chard

 

Directions
  1. Combine aminos, vinegar, lemon juice and mustard in saute pan.
  2. Add scallops, onion, & garlic and cook about 10 minutes or until almost all the liquid is gone.
  3. Remove the scallops and add the vegetable broth.
  4. Add chard to the broth and cook stirring occasionally until chard is tender, adding a little water if needed.
  5. Top with mustard scallops.

Roasted Enoki Mushrooms

Roasted Enoki Mushrooms

Dietary
Oil Free
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
65
Servings
1
Ingredients

8 oz enoki mushrooms
choice of spices, if desired

Directions
  1. Preheat oven to 325 degrees.
  2. Chop clumpy roots off of mushrooms and rinse quickly.
  3. Separate mushrooms into individual strands and dry thoroughly.
  4. Spread mushrooms out in an even layer on a baking sheet lined with parchment paper or a silicone baking mat.
  5. Sprinkle with spices.
  6. Roast for 15 minutes, and then rotate baking sheet.
  7. Roast for another 15-20 minutes, or until mushrooms are deep golden-brown and dried.

Chicken Zucchini Poppers

Chicken Zucchini Poppers

Dietary
Oil Free
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
210
Servings
4
Ingredients

1 lb ground chicken breast

Homemade BBQ Sauce

Homemade BBQ Sauce

Dietary
Oil Free
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
10
Servings
8
Ingredients

1/2 c sugar-free tomato sauce
1 tablespoon balsamic vinegar
½ teaspoon mustard powder
1 garlic clove, minced
½ teaspoon smoked paprika
⅛ – ¼ teaspoon sea salt
Freshly ground pepper, to taste

Directions
  1. Add all ingredients to a food processor or high-powered blender.
  2. Blend until smooth, about 1 minute.
  3. Pour ingredients into a small saucepan.
  4. Cover and bring to a light boil over medium-low heat.
  5. Boil for 5 minutes.
  6. Allow to cool and store in an air-tight container for up to 2 weeks.

Egg Drop Soup

Egg Drop Soup

Dietary
Oil Free
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
130
Servings
2
Ingredients

24 oz chicken stock
1/8 tsp ground ginger
2 tbsp fresh chives, chopped
1/4 tsp salt
2 eggs
6 egg whites

Directions
  1. Pour the chicken stock into a saucepan over a medium-high heat.
  2. Add the ginger, chives and salt to the liquid and allow it to come to a boil.
  3. In a small bowl, whisk together the eggs and yolk.
  4. As the broth continues to boil, use a fork and drizzle the eggs into the pot. The eggs should cook immediately.
  5. Serve warm and enjoy!

Apple Chips

Apple Chips

Dietary
Oil Free
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
95
Servings
1
Ingredients

1 apple
choice of seasonings (Chinese 5 spice, cinnamon, pink salt, etc)

Directions
  1. Preheat oven to 250 degrees.
  2. Line two baking sheets with parchment paper and set aside.
  3. Cut apple into thin slices.
  4. Spread apple slices onto baking sheets, making sure you have no overlapping edges.
  5. Sprinkle some seasonings on top.
  6. Place in the oven to bake for 1 hour; then flip the slices and cook for another hour.
  7. Let the chips cool down and serve.

Garlic Lemon Scallops

Garlic Lemon Scallops

Dietary
Oil Free
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
100
Servings
4
Ingredients

14 oz scallops
1/4 c lemon juice
2 cloves garlic, minced
lemon pepper, to taste

Directions
  1. Preheat oven to 350 degrees
  2. Pat scallops dry with paper towels and place in 1 quart casserole dish
  3. Bake scallops in preheated oven for 5 minutes
  4. In a small bowl, combine lemon juice and garlic
  5. Remove scallops from oven
  6. Spoon lemon/garlic mixture over scallops and sprinkle generously with lemon pepper
  7. Return scallops to oven and bake until firm, about 10 minutes
  8. Serve warm

Fra Diavolo Sauce with Scallops (or Shrimp)

Fra Diavolo Sauce with Scallops (or Shrimp)

Dietary
Oil Free
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
160
Servings
2
Ingredients

3.5 oz scallops (or shrimp)
6 cloves garlic, crushed
24 oz whole peeled tomatoes with liquid, chopped
1/4-1/2 t pink salt
1 t crushed red pepper flakes
1 T chopped fresh parsley

Directions
  1. Saute garlic over medium heat in a nonstick skillet
  2. When garlic starts to sizzle, pour in tomatoes
  3. Season with salt and red pepper
  4. Bring to a boil
  5. Lower heat and simmer for 30 mins, stirring occasionally
  6. Cook scallops (or shrimp) in nonstick pan for 2 minutes, stirring frequently, or until shrimp turn pink
  7. Add shrimp to tomato mixture and stir in parsley
  8. Cook for 3-4 minutes or until the sauce just begins to bubble

Cabba-Sghetti

Cabba-Sghetti

Dietary
Oil Free
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
285
Servings
2
Ingredients

7 oz ground buffalo (or ground beef)
2 t onion powder
4 cloves garlic
4 T water
8 oz canned diced tomatoes
8 oz canned tomato sauce
1 t tomato paste
1 T basil
1 T italian seasoning
16 oz shredded cabbage
1/2 t pink salt
1/2 t pepper

Directions
  1. Over medium heat, heat 2 T water, 3 garlic cloves, and onion powder
  2. Saute until garlic is cooked
  3. Add ground buffalo and basil, salt, and pepper
  4. Stir and cook until meat is fully browned
  5. Add diced tomatoes, tomato sauce and paste
  6. Mix well
  7. Add addition spices as needed
  8. Let simmer and stir occasionally 
  9. In separate pan, add 2 T water 1 garlic clove, and saute for 1 minute
  10. Add cabbage and remaining seasoning
  11. Saute until soft
  12. Drain and put on plate
  13. Top with sauce and serve

Egg Rolls

Egg Rolls

Dietary
Oil Free
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
195
Servings
1
Ingredients

2-3 big cabbage leaves
4 oz shredded cabbage
1/8 tsp. onion salt
1/8 tsp. garlic powder
1/8 tsp. Asian spices
4 drops or 1 packet Stevia

Directions
  1. Steam big cabbage leaves for 5 minutes.

Chicken Chili

Chicken Chili

Dietary
Oil Free
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
220
Servings
1
Ingredients

8 oz shredded cabbage
2 cups Swanson chicken stock
1 tsp. cayenne pepper
1 tsp. black pepper
1 T. chili powder
1 T. cumin
3 pinches of dried chopped onions
3 oz cooked chicken breast
 

Directions
  1. In a medium saucepan add 2 cups chicken stock.
  2. Bring to boil.
  3. Add spices, cabbage and cooked chicken.
  4. Stir constantly.
  5. The liquid will begin to dissolve, so it will become less soupy.
  6. Let simmer for about 10 minutes, or until the cabbage is to your preference.

Braised Balsamic Chicken

Braised Balsamic Chicken

Dietary
Oil Free
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
205
Servings
2
Ingredients

7 oz chicken breast
1/4 tsp. garlic powder
2 T balsamic vinegar
1 T apple cider vinegar
1 (14.5 oz) can diced tomatoes
1 tsp. onion powder
1/4 tsp. basil
1/4 tsp. oregano
1/4 tsp. rosemary

Directions

Blackened Chicken

Blackened Chicken

Dietary
Oil Free
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
155
Servings
2
Ingredients

1/2 tsp. paprika
1/8 tsp. pink salt
1/4 tsp. cayenne pepper
1/4 tsp. cumin
1/4 tsp. thyme
1/8 tsp. pepper
1/8 tsp. onion powder
7 oz chicken breast 

Directions
  1. Preheat oven to 350 degrees
  2. Heat skillet over high heat 
  3. Mix together paprika, salt, cayenne, cumin, thyme, pepper, and onion powder.
  4. Coat chicken breasts evenly with spice mixture.
  5. Cook for 1 minute.
  6. Turn, and cook 1 minute on other side.
  7. Place on parchment paper lined baking sheet.
  8. Bake in oven until no longer pink in the center and the juices run clear, about 15 minutes. 

Basil Chicken

Basil Chicken

Dietary
Oil Free
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
220
Servings
1
Ingredients

4 oz finely chopped onion
1 clove garlic, chopped
8 oz chopped tomatoes
3 oz chicken breast, cooked and cubed
1/4 c. chopped fresh basil (or 1-2 T dried basil)
1/2 tsp. pink salt
1/8 tsp. hot sauce

Directions
  1. Warm large skillet to medium-high heat.
  2. Sauté onions and garlic in a little water.
  3. Stir in tomatoes, chicken, basil, salt and hot sauce.
  4. Reduce heat to medium, and cover skillet.
  5. Simmer for about 5 minutes, stirring frequently, until mixture is hot and tomatoes are soft.

Chicken Asparagus Stir Fry

Chicken Asparagus Stir Fry

Dietary
Oil Free
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
215
Servings
1
Ingredients

3.5 oz chicken breast, cut in strips
1/4 cup water
salt and pepper to taste
8 oz asparagus cut in 1" pieces
1/2 tsp ginger, grated
1 dash cayenne
1 clove garlic, minced

Directions
  1. Steam asparagus until tender, but still crisp.
  2. Set aside.
  3. Heat water in a skillet and add chicken strips, stirring, until cooked almost all the way through.
  4. Add the grated ginger, garlic, and cayenne.
  5. When the liquid is reduced by half, add in the asparagus and season with salt and pepper.
  6. Serve warm.

Oil Free

Sweet & Sour Shrimp

Sweet & Sour Shrimp

Dietary
Oil Free
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
165
Servings
1
Ingredients

3.5 oz shrimp
1 cup water
1 T lemon juice
1 orange with rind
3 teaspoons Bragg’s liquid aminos
1 tablespoon minced onion
1 clove garlic crushed and minced
Cayenne to taste
Salt and pepper to taste
Stevia to taste

Directions
  1. Boil 1 cup of water with lemon juice and orange with rind until pulp comes out of the center.
  2. Scrape out remaining pulp and discard the rind.
  3. Add onion, garlic, Bragg’s, and spices and reduce liquid by half.
  4. Add the shrimp to the sauce and sauté for 5-7 minutes until shrimp is cooked.

3.5 oz skinless boneless chicken, cut into bite sized pieces

1/2 T curry
1 t onion powder
2 cloves garlic crushed and minced or 1/2 t garlic powder
Salt & Pepper
1/2 T Bragg's liquid aminos
1/2 T apple cider vinegar
1 orange

Directions
  1. In a large frying pan, saute chicken in a little Bragg's liquid aminos over medium high heat.
  2. Cut orange into small pieces and add to pan, mashing juice out. 
  3. Add the rest of ingredients and cook until cabbage is tender adding more water or broth as necessary.
  4. Cook down until no liquid is left.
  5. Serve hot.
     

Chicken Cabbage Scramble

Chicken Cabbage Scramble

Dietary
Oil Free
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
215
Servings
1
Ingredients

3.5 oz chicken (breast or ground)
2 cloves minced garlic
8 oz chopped cabbage
1 t mustard
1/2- 1 c Swanson chicken stock
pink salt and pepper, to taste

 

Directions
  1. Saute chicken and garlic in skillet
  2. Add cabbage, mustard, stock, salt & pepper
  3. Saute until liquid is gone
  4. Serve immediately

Texas Dirty "Rice"

Texas Dirty "Rice"

Dietary
Oil Free
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
285
Servings
1
Ingredients

3.5 oz lean ground beef
8 oz cabbage, finely chopped into rice sized
1 c water
1/2 t cumin
1 T chili powder
2 t onion powder 
2 cloves garlic crushed and minced
pink salt and pepper, to taste
hot sauce, to taste

Directions
  1. In a large frying pan, brown beef over medium high heat
  2. Add all other ingredients and cook until cabbage is tender, adding more water as necessary
  3. Cook down until no liquid is left
  4. Serve hot and drizzle with hot sauce

Cucumber Dill Salad

Cucumber Dill Salad

Dietary
Oil Free
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
35
Servings
1
Ingredients

6 oz cucumber
1 T vinegar of choice
1 t dill
stevia, to taste
black pepper, to taste
pink salt, to taste

Directions
  1. Slice and quarter cucumber.
  2. Place vinegar, dill, stevia, salt and black pepper in a small bowl. 
  3. Stir in the cucumbers pieces. 
  4. Serve immediately or refrigerate for later.

Apple Cider Vinegar Dressing

Dietary

Sugar Free

Calories per serving

n/a
Ingredients

Spinach Stuffed Chicken

Spinach Stuffed Chicken

Dietary
Oil Free
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
185
Servings
1
Ingredients

3.5 oz chicken breast
1 - 1 1/4 cup water
1 T minced garlic
1 t chives
5 oz raw spinach
1 T Pompeian balsamic vinegar 
pink salt and pepper, to taste
1 t Braggs Liquid Aminos

Directions
  1. Cut chicken breast in half to make 2 cutlets
  2. Place a sheet of plastic wrap on top and pound them out to make them thinner
  3. Sprinkle both sides with salt and pepper
  4. In a separate bowl mix the minced garlic, chives and salt & pepper together along with any other spices you prefer
  5. After mixture is thoroughly mixed; spread on one side of each chicken cutlet
  6. Place spinach over each cutlet and roll semi-tightly, use a toothpick to hold cutlets together.
  7. Add 1/4 cup water to hot pan on stove
  8. Place cutlets in pan and cover with balsamic vinegar
  9. Brown each side for 3 minutes
  10. Place cutlets in small baking dish (pour excess water and balsamic vinegar on top)
  11. Add 1 cup of water to baking dish
  12. Cook in oven for 15-20 minutes or until middle is 190 degrees
  13. Top with some Braggs liquid aminos

Lemon Zest Crab Cakes

Lemon Zest Crab Cakes

Dietary
Oil Free
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
150
Servings
1
Ingredients

3.5 oz crab
1 garlic clove, minced
1 tsp. onion powder
1 T parsley
1⁄2 tsp. lemon zest
1⁄4 tsp. pink salt
1⁄4 tsp. pepper
1 tsp. dry mustard
2 lemon wedges

 

Directions
  1. Mix everything together
  2. Form into 2 small patties
  3. Place in a parchment paper lined baking dish
  4. Bake for 15 minutes at 350 degrees
  5. Top with juice from lemon wedges

Sweet & Tangy Chinese Chicken Salad

Sweet & Tangy Chinese Chicken Salad

Dietary
Oil Free
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
285
Servings
1
Ingredients

1 orange
3 oz cooked chicken breast
8 oz cabbage
1/2 c Swanson Chicken stock
1/2 T minced garlic
1/2 t dry mustard
1 T Bragg’s liquid aminos
2 t apple cider vinegar
1/4 t ginger
stevia to taste

Directions
  1. Chop cabbage
  2. Heat 1/2 cup chicken stock in skillet over medium-high heat
  3. Saute cabbage in chicken stock for approximately 5 minutes, until tender
  4. Dice chicken and orange into small pieces
  5. Add chicken, orange, and minced garlic to cabbage and cook for 1 minute
  6. Remove from heat
  7. In small bowl, combine dry mustard powder, liquid aminos, apple cider vinegar, ginger, and stevia
  8. Mix well until dissolved
  9. Pour dressing over chicken salad and mix well

Sweet Apple Chicken Salad

Sweet Apple Chicken Salad

Dietary
Oil Free
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
265
Servings
1
Ingredients

3 oz chicken, cooked and diced
1 apple, diced
8 oz celery, chopped
3 T lemon juice
1/8 t cinnamon
Dash of nutmeg
Dash of pink salt
stevia, to taste
Lemon wedge

Directions

1. Mix ingredients together, sprinkle with Stevia and cinnamon.
2. Chill for 20 minutes.
3. Serve with a wedge of lemon and enjoy

Strawberry Crepes

Strawberry Crepes

Dietary
Oil Free
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
165
Servings
1
Ingredients

1 egg
3 egg whites
12 strawberries
8-12 drops SweetLeaf vanilla creme stevia
 

Directions
  1. Mix one egg with three whites and season with stevia
  2. Mash half of the strawberries
  3. Heat until warm
  4. Slice the rest of the strawberries
  5. Cook the egg in a dry non stick skillet, flipping it once, so it cooks all the way through
  6. Line the sliced strawberries down the middle and pour the mashed strawberry syrup on top

Frozen Lemonade

Frozen Lemonade

Dietary
Oil Free
Sugar Free
Low Carb
Calories per serving
50
Servings
1
Ingredients

2 lemons (peeled and frozen)
1.5 cups ice
1/2 cup water
stevia to taste

Directions
  1. Add all ingredients to blender
  2. Blend until slushy
